    • dev - Tables supporting compilation of programs
      • dev.arch - System architecture

      • dev.htmlentity - Known HTML entity strings & codes
      • dev.include - A site where one file includes another
      • dev.license - Source code license
      • dev.linelim -

      • dev.msgfile - File in repo containing messages that should be normalized during CI
      • dev.noindent - Indicates that a file should not be automatically indented
      • dev.opt_type - Type of option (used in tool_opt)
      • dev.package - OpenACR package

      • dev.pkgkey - Keys belonging to the OpenACR package
      • dev.readme - File containing documentation

      • dev.scriptfile - Known script file
      • dev.srcfile - Source file or header (key is pathname)

    • dmmeta - Tables holding metadata (data model meta)
      • dmmeta.anonfld - Omit field name where possible (command line, enums, constants)
      • dmmeta.argvtype - Customize parsing of command lines (rarely used)
      • dmmeta.basepool - Specify pool to be used for allocating elements of a type
      • dmmeta.bitfld - Specify offset/width of a bitfield within another field
      • dmmeta.cafter - Control amc processing order for unrelated types (used in rare situations)
      • dmmeta.cascdel - Request cascading delete of referenced rows
      • dmmeta.ccmp - Generate hash function
      • dmmeta.cdflt - Specify default value for single-value types that lack fields
      • dmmeta.cextern - Externally defined ctype (a struct from system header, or from a c++ library)
      • dmmeta.cfast - FAST properties for ctype
      • dmmeta.cfmt - Specify options for printing/reading ctypes into multiple formats
      • dmmeta.cget - Generate state functions for these ctypes
      • dmmeta.charset - Generate functions to determine if a character is a member of a set
      • dmmeta.chash - Generate hash function
      • dmmeta.cppfunc - Value of field provided by this expression
      • dmmeta.cppkeyword - Built-in C++ keyword
      • dmmeta.cpptype - Specify whether a ctype can be passed by value, and other c++ options
      • dmmeta.csize - Specify size/alignment for built-in C++ types
      • dmmeta.cstr - Specify that type behaves like a string
      • dmmeta.ctype - Struct
      • dmmeta.ctypelen - Size of Ctype
      • dmmeta.dispatch - Generate code for a multi-way branch
      • dmmeta.dispatch_msg - Add message to a dispatch
      • dmmeta.dispctx - Use context with dispatch
      • dmmeta.dispfilter - Generate filter function on dispatch
      • dmmeta.dispsig - Cryptographic signature of all dispatches
      • dmmeta.dispsigcheck - Check signature of input data against executable’s version
      • dmmeta.disptrace - Generate trace fields (cycles, counts) for all dispatch branches
      • dmmeta.falias - Alias field
      • dmmeta.fastenc -
      • dmmeta.fastinstr -
      • dmmeta.fastop -
      • dmmeta.fbase - Customize imported Base fields
      • dmmeta.fbigend - Annotate field as having big-endian storage
      • dmmeta.fbitset - Generate bitset functions over integer field or array
      • dmmeta.fbuf - Buffer for reading/writing messages, works with Iohook
      • dmmeta.fbufdir - Buffer direction (in,out)
      • dmmeta.fbuftype - Buffer type
      • dmmeta.fcast - Generate implicit conversion from field to c++ expression
      • dmmeta.fcleanup - Request user-implemented function to be called at Uninit time for a field
      • dmmeta.fcmap - Bidirectional mapping between fconst values
      • dmmeta.fcmdline - Annotate field that holds process command line
      • dmmeta.fcmp - Request versionsort or case-insensitive sort for field
      • dmmeta.fcompact - Request compaction upon removal from index
      • dmmeta.fconst - Specify enum value (integer + string constant) for a field
      • dmmeta.fcurs - Request generation of custom cursor
      • dmmeta.fdec - Specify that field has an implied # of decimal places and specify formatting options
      • dmmeta.fdelay - Control elapsed time between execution of a step
      • dmmeta.ffast - FAST properties for field
      • dmmeta.fflag - Options for command-line flags
      • dmmeta.field - Specify field of a struct
      • dmmeta.findrem - Request generation of FindRemove function
      • dmmeta.finput - Describe input table of a program
      • dmmeta.fldoffset - Assert field offset - will result in compile-time error if violated
      • dmmeta.floadtuples - Request that process automatically load any input tables on startup
      • dmmeta.fnoremove - Omit any functions for removing elements from table; Table is append-only
      • dmmeta.foutput - Generate function to save index/table back to disk
      • dmmeta.fprefix - Mapping between field prefix and Reftype
      • dmmeta.fregx - Specify options for command-line regx field
      • dmmeta.fsort - Generate custom sort function for array field
      • dmmeta.fstep - Generate a main loop step to be executed whenever a field is non-empty
      • dmmeta.ftrace - Generate cycle/step counting fields for a step
      • dmmeta.ftuple -
      • dmmeta.func -
      • dmmeta.funique - This field must be unique in the table. Not needed for primary key
      • dmmeta.fuserinit - Add user-defined initialization function for field (see fcleanup)
      • dmmeta.fwddecl - Request forward declaration of a field
      • dmmeta.gconst - Import ssim table columns as fconst for a field
      • dmmeta.gstatic - Load entries for this table at startup time
      • dmmeta.gsymbol - Create C++ symbols from entries in ssim table
      • dmmeta.hashtype - Hash function type
      • dmmeta.hook - Required on Hook fields
      • dmmeta.inlary - Generate inline array of fixed or variable length (all entries fit within parent struct)
      • dmmeta.lenfld - Specify which gives length of varlen portion in bytes
      • dmmeta.listtype - Specify structure of linked list based on field prefix
      • dmmeta.llist - Options for Llist field
      • dmmeta.logcat - Log category
      • dmmeta.main - Generate Main function for namespace
      • dmmeta.msgtype - Specify message type for each eligible message, controls dispatch
      • dmmeta.nocascdel - Remove cascade delete for this index
      • dmmeta.nossimfile - Indicates that ssimfile does not exist for this ssimdb ctype
      • dmmeta.noxref - Explicitly specify that no x-ref exists between tables (don’t use unless forced)
      • dmmeta.ns - Namespace (for in-memory database, protocol, etc)
      • dmmeta.nscpp - Generate C++ code for this namespace
      • dmmeta.nsdb - Annotate ssimdb namespaces
      • dmmeta.nsfast - Whether namespace is FAST
      • dmmeta.nsinclude - Explicitly specify a C++ include file for namespace
      • dmmeta.nsjs - Generate JavaScript code for this namespace
      • dmmeta.nsproto - Annotate protocol namespace (collection of types, no state)
      • dmmeta.nstype - Namespace type
      • dmmeta.nsversion - Namespace version
      • dmmeta.nsx - Control code-generation and exception handling options for process/library
      • dmmeta.numstr - Add functions to read numbers out of a string field
      • dmmeta.pack - Request byte-packing of structure fields
      • dmmeta.pmaskfld - Specify which field holds presence mask bits (one for each field in struct)
      • dmmeta.pmaskfld_member - Explicit field-to-pmask association
      • dmmeta.pnew - Generate custom constructor (placement new), for use with binary protocols
      • dmmeta.pnewtype - Type of fbuf
      • dmmeta.printfmt - Print format
      • dmmeta.ptrary - Required for fields with reftype:Ptrary
      • dmmeta.reftype - Field type constructor (e.g. reference type)
      • dmmeta.rowid - Initialize field to row id of element
      • dmmeta.smallstr - Generated fixed-length padded or length-delimited string field
      • dmmeta.sortfld - Specify what field an index (Bheap,Atree) is sorted on
      • dmmeta.sorttype - Sort type
      • dmmeta.sqltype - Mapping of ctype -> SQL expression
      • dmmeta.ssimfile - File with ssim tuples
      • dmmeta.ssimreq - Extended constraints for ssim records
      • dmmeta.ssimsort - Define sort order for ssimfile
      • dmmeta.ssimvolatile - Types based on ssim files marked this way cannot be cross-referenced
      • dmmeta.steptype - Type of scheduler step
      • dmmeta.strfmt - Cfmt conversion type (misnomer, not necessarily a string)
      • dmmeta.strtype - Type of small string
      • dmmeta.substr - Specify that the field value is computed from a substring of another field
      • dmmeta.svtype - Table for determining ctype from separated value file
      • dmmeta.tary - Indirect linear dynamically alocated array (used for strings, arrays of data, etc)
      • dmmeta.thash - Hash index, required for fields with reftype Thash
      • dmmeta.tracefld - Trace fields
      • dmmeta.tracerec - Trace record
      • dmmeta.typefld - Specifies which field of a message carries the type
      • dmmeta.usertracefld - Add custom user trace fields to process’s trace struct
      • dmmeta.xref - Specify how to cross-reference (i.e. project, or group-by) one record with another

 250// --- abt.FDb.lpool.FreeMem
 251// Free block of memory previously returned by Lpool.
 252void abt::lpool_FreeMem(void* mem, u64 size) {
 253    size = u64_Max(size,1ULL<<4);
 254    u64 cell = algo::u64_BitScanReverse(size-1) + 1 - 4;
 255    if (mem && cell < 36) {
 256        lpool_Lpblock *temp = (lpool_Lpblock*)mem; // push  singly linked list
 257        temp->next = _db.lpool_free[cell];
 258        _db.lpool_free[cell] = temp;
 259    }
 260}
 261
 262// --- abt.FDb.lpool.AllocMem
 263// Allocate new piece of memory at least SIZE bytes long.
 264// If not successful, return NULL
 265// The allocated block is at least 1<<4
 266// The maximum allocation size is at most 1<<(36+4)
 267void* abt::lpool_AllocMem(u64 size) {
 268    void *retval = NULL;
 269    size     = u64_Max(size,1<<4); // enforce alignment
 270    u64 cell = algo::u64_BitScanReverse(size-1) + 1 - 4;
 271    if (cell < 36) {
 272        u64 i    = cell;
 273        // try to find a block that's at least as large as required.
 274        // if found, remove from free list
 275        for (; i < 36; i++) {
 276            lpool_Lpblock *blk = _db.lpool_free[i];
 277            if (blk) {
 278                _db.lpool_free[i] = blk->next;
 279                retval = blk;
 280                break;
 281            }
 282        }
 283        // if suitable size block is not found, create a new one
 284        // by requesting a block from the base allocator.
 285        if (UNLIKELY(!retval)) {
 286            i = u64_Max(cell, 21-4); // 2MB min -- allow huge page to be used
 287            retval = algo_lib::sbrk_AllocMem(1ULL<<(i+4));
 288        }
 289        if (LIKELY(retval)) {
 290            // if block is more than 2x as large as needed, return the upper half to the free
 291            // list (repeatedly). meanwhile, retval doesn't change.
 292            while (i > cell) {
 293                i--;
 294                int half = 1ULL<<(i+4);
 295                lpool_Lpblock *blk = (lpool_Lpblock*)((u8*)retval + half);
 296                blk->next = _db.lpool_free[i];
 297                _db.lpool_free[i] = blk;
 298            }
 299        }
 300    }
 301    return retval;
 302}
 303
 304// --- abt.FDb.lpool.ReserveBuffers
 305// Add N buffers of some size to the free store
 306// Reserve NBUF buffers of size BUFSIZE from the base pool (algo_lib::sbrk)
 307bool abt::lpool_ReserveBuffers(u64 nbuf, u64 bufsize) {
 308    bool retval = true;
 309    bufsize = u64_Max(bufsize, 1<<4);
 310    u64 cell = algo::u64_BitScanReverse(bufsize-1) + 1 - 4;
 311    if (cell < 36) {
 312        for (u64 i = 0; i < nbuf; i++) {
 313            u64 size = 1ULL<<(cell+4);
 314            lpool_Lpblock *temp = (lpool_Lpblock*)algo_lib::sbrk_AllocMem(size);
 315            if (temp == NULL) {
 316                retval = false;
 317                break;// why continue?
 318            } else {
 319                temp->next = _db.lpool_free[cell];
 320                _db.lpool_free[cell] = temp;
 321            }
 322        }
 323    }
 324    return retval;
 325}
 326
 327// --- abt.FDb.lpool.ReallocMem
 328// Allocate new block, copy old to new, delete old.
 329// If the new size is same as old size, do nothing.
 330// In all other cases, new memory is allocated (i.e. size reduction is not a no-op)
 331// If no memory, return NULL; old memory remains untouched
 332void* abt::lpool_ReallocMem(void* oldmem, u64 old_size, u64 new_size) {
 333    void *ret = oldmem;
 334    if (new_size != old_size) {
 335        ret = lpool_AllocMem(new_size);
 336        if (ret && oldmem) {
 337            memcpy(ret,oldmem,u64_Min(new_size,old_size));
 338            lpool_FreeMem(oldmem, old_size);
 339        }
 340    }
 341    return ret;
 342}

 344// --- abt.FDb.lpool.Alloc
 345// Allocate memory for new default row.
 346// If out of memory, process is killed.
 347u8& abt::lpool_Alloc() {
 348    u8* row = lpool_AllocMaybe();
 349    if (UNLIKELY(row == NULL)) {
 350        FatalErrorExit("abt.out_of_mem  field:abt.FDb.lpool  comment:'Alloc failed'");
 351    }
 352    return *row;
 353}

 355// --- abt.FDb.lpool.AllocMaybe
 356// Allocate memory for new element. If out of memory, return NULL.
 357u8* abt::lpool_AllocMaybe() {
 358    u8 *row = (u8*)lpool_AllocMem(sizeof(u8));
 359    if (row) {
 360        new (row) u8; // call constructor
 361    }
 362    return row;
 363}

 365// --- abt.FDb.lpool.Delete
 366// Remove row from all global and cross indices, then deallocate row
 367void abt::lpool_Delete(u8 &row) {
 368    int length = sizeof(u8);
 369    lpool_FreeMem(&row, length);
 370}

 383// --- abt.FDb.srcfile.AllocMaybe
 384// Allocate memory for new element. If out of memory, return NULL.
 385abt::FSrcfile* abt::srcfile_AllocMaybe() {
 386    abt::FSrcfile *row = (abt::FSrcfile*)srcfile_AllocMem();
 387    if (row) {
 388        new (row) abt::FSrcfile; // call constructor
 389    }
 390    return row;
 391}

 393// --- abt.FDb.srcfile.InsertMaybe
 394// Create new row from struct.
 395// Return pointer to new element, or NULL if insertion failed (due to out-of-memory, duplicate key, etc)
 396abt::FSrcfile* abt::srcfile_InsertMaybe(const dev::Srcfile &value) {
 397    abt::FSrcfile *row = &srcfile_Alloc(); // if out of memory, process dies. if input error, return NULL.
 398    srcfile_CopyIn(*row,const_cast<dev::Srcfile&>(value));
 399    bool ok = srcfile_XrefMaybe(*row); // this may return false
 400    if (!ok) {
 401        srcfile_RemoveLast(); // delete offending row, any existing xrefs are cleared
 402        row = NULL; // forget this ever happened
 403    }
 404    return row;
 405}
 406
 407// --- abt.FDb.srcfile.AllocMem
 408// Allocate space for one element. If no memory available, return NULL.
 409void* abt::srcfile_AllocMem() {
 410    u64 new_nelems     = _db.srcfile_n+1;
 411    // compute level and index on level
 412    u64 bsr   = algo::u64_BitScanReverse(new_nelems);
 413    u64 base  = u64(1)<<bsr;
 414    u64 index = new_nelems-base;
 415    void *ret = NULL;
 416    // if level doesn't exist yet, create it
 417    abt::FSrcfile*  lev   = NULL;
 418    if (bsr < 32) {
 419        lev = _db.srcfile_lary[bsr];
 420        if (!lev) {
 421            lev=(abt::FSrcfile*)abt::lpool_AllocMem(sizeof(abt::FSrcfile) * (u64(1)<<bsr));
 422            _db.srcfile_lary[bsr] = lev;
 423        }
 424    }
 425    // allocate element from this level
 426    if (lev) {
 427        _db.srcfile_n = i32(new_nelems);
 428        ret = lev + index;
 429    }
 430    return ret;
 431}
 432
 433// --- abt.FDb.srcfile.RemoveAll
 434// Remove all elements from Lary
 435void abt::srcfile_RemoveAll() {
 436    for (u64 n = _db.srcfile_n; n>0; ) {
 437        n--;
 438        srcfile_qFind(u64(n)).~FSrcfile(); // destroy last element
 439        _db.srcfile_n = i32(n);
 440    }
 441}
 442
 443// --- abt.FDb.srcfile.RemoveLast
 444// Delete last element of array. Do nothing if array is empty.
 445void abt::srcfile_RemoveLast() {
 446    u64 n = _db.srcfile_n;
 447    if (n > 0) {
 448        n -= 1;
 449        srcfile_qFind(u64(n)).~FSrcfile();
 450        _db.srcfile_n = i32(n);
 451    }
 452}
 453
 454// --- abt.FDb.srcfile.XrefMaybe
 455// Insert row into all appropriate indices. If error occurs, store error
 456// in algo_lib::_db.errtext and return false. Caller must Delete or Unref such row.
 457bool abt::srcfile_XrefMaybe(abt::FSrcfile &row) {
 458    bool retval = true;
 459    (void)row;
 460    // insert srcfile into index ind_srcfile
 461    if (true) { // user-defined insert condition
 462        bool success = ind_srcfile_InsertMaybe(row);
 463        if (UNLIKELY(!success)) {
 464            ch_RemoveAll(algo_lib::_db.errtext);
 465            algo_lib::_db.errtext << "abt.duplicate_key  xref:abt.FDb.ind_srcfile"; // check for duplicate key
 466            return false;
 467        }
 468    }
 469    // insert srcfile into index zs_srcfile_read
 470    if (true) { // user-defined insert condition
 471        zs_srcfile_read_Insert(row);
 472    }
 473    return retval;
 474}
 475
 476// --- abt.FDb.targdep.Alloc
 477// Allocate memory for new default row.
 478// If out of memory, process is killed.
 479abt::FTargdep& abt::targdep_Alloc() {
 480    abt::FTargdep* row = targdep_AllocMaybe();
 481    if (UNLIKELY(row == NULL)) {
 482        FatalErrorExit("abt.out_of_mem  field:abt.FDb.targdep  comment:'Alloc failed'");
 483    }
 484    return *row;
 485}
 486
 487// --- abt.FDb.targdep.AllocMaybe
 488// Allocate memory for new element. If out of memory, return NULL.
 489abt::FTargdep* abt::targdep_AllocMaybe() {
 490    abt::FTargdep *row = (abt::FTargdep*)targdep_AllocMem();
 491    if (row) {
 492        new (row) abt::FTargdep; // call constructor
 493    }
 494    return row;
 495}
 496
 497// --- abt.FDb.targdep.InsertMaybe
 498// Create new row from struct.
 499// Return pointer to new element, or NULL if insertion failed (due to out-of-memory, duplicate key, etc)
 500abt::FTargdep* abt::targdep_InsertMaybe(const dev::Targdep &value) {
 501    abt::FTargdep *row = &targdep_Alloc(); // if out of memory, process dies. if input error, return NULL.
 502    targdep_CopyIn(*row,const_cast<dev::Targdep&>(value));
 503    bool ok = targdep_XrefMaybe(*row); // this may return false
 504    if (!ok) {
 505        targdep_RemoveLast(); // delete offending row, any existing xrefs are cleared
 506        row = NULL; // forget this ever happened
 507    }
 508    return row;
 509}
 510
 511// --- abt.FDb.targdep.AllocMem
 512// Allocate space for one element. If no memory available, return NULL.
 513void* abt::targdep_AllocMem() {
 514    u64 new_nelems     = _db.targdep_n+1;
 515    // compute level and index on level
 516    u64 bsr   = algo::u64_BitScanReverse(new_nelems);
 517    u64 base  = u64(1)<<bsr;
 518    u64 index = new_nelems-base;
 519    void *ret = NULL;
 520    // if level doesn't exist yet, create it
 521    abt::FTargdep*  lev   = NULL;
 522    if (bsr < 32) {
 523        lev = _db.targdep_lary[bsr];
 524        if (!lev) {
 525            lev=(abt::FTargdep*)abt::lpool_AllocMem(sizeof(abt::FTargdep) * (u64(1)<<bsr));
 526            _db.targdep_lary[bsr] = lev;
 527        }
 528    }
 529    // allocate element from this level
 530    if (lev) {
 531        _db.targdep_n = i32(new_nelems);
 532        ret = lev + index;
 533    }
 534    return ret;
 535}
 536
 537// --- abt.FDb.targdep.RemoveLast
 538// Delete last element of array. Do nothing if array is empty.
 539void abt::targdep_RemoveLast() {
 540    u64 n = _db.targdep_n;
 541    if (n > 0) {
 542        n -= 1;
 543        targdep_qFind(u64(n)).~FTargdep();
 544        _db.targdep_n = i32(n);
 545    }
 546}
 547
 548// --- abt.FDb.targdep.InputMaybe
 549static bool abt::targdep_InputMaybe(dev::Targdep &elem) {
 550    bool retval = true;
 551    retval = targdep_InsertMaybe(elem) != nullptr;
 552    return retval;
 553}
 554
 555// --- abt.FDb.targdep.XrefMaybe
 556// Insert row into all appropriate indices. If error occurs, store error
 557// in algo_lib::_db.errtext and return false. Caller must Delete or Unref such row.
 558bool abt::targdep_XrefMaybe(abt::FTargdep &row) {
 559    bool retval = true;
 560    (void)row;
 561    abt::FTarget* p_target = abt::ind_target_Find(target_Get(row));
 562    if (UNLIKELY(!p_target)) {
 563        algo_lib::ResetErrtext() << "abt.bad_xref  index:abt.FDb.ind_target" << Keyval("key", target_Get(row));
 564        return false;
 565    }
 566    // insert targdep into index c_targdep
 567    if (true) { // user-defined insert condition
 568        c_targdep_Insert(*p_target, row);
 569    }
 570    abt::FTarget* p_parent = abt::ind_target_Find(parent_Get(row));
 571    if (UNLIKELY(!p_parent)) {
 572        algo_lib::ResetErrtext() << "abt.bad_xref  index:abt.FDb.ind_target" << Keyval("key", parent_Get(row));
 573        return false;
 574    }
 575    // targdep: save pointer to parent
 576    if (true) { // user-defined insert condition
 577        row.p_parent = p_parent;
 578    }
 579    return retval;
 580}

 670// --- abt.FDb.ind_target.Find
 671// Find row by key. Return NULL if not found.
 672abt::FTarget* abt::ind_target_Find(const algo::strptr& key) {
 673    u32 index = algo::Smallstr16_Hash(0, key) & (_db.ind_target_buckets_n - 1);
 674    abt::FTarget* *e = &_db.ind_target_buckets_elems[index];
 675    abt::FTarget* ret=NULL;
 676    do {
 677        ret       = *e;
 678        bool done = !ret || (*ret).target == key;
 679        if (done) break;
 680        e         = &ret->ind_target_next;
 681    } while (true);
 682    return ret;
 683}
 684
 685// --- abt.FDb.ind_target.GetOrCreate
 686// Find row by key. If not found, create and x-reference a new row with with this key.
 687abt::FTarget& abt::ind_target_GetOrCreate(const algo::strptr& key) {
 688    abt::FTarget* ret = ind_target_Find(key);
 689    if (!ret) { //  if memory alloc fails, process dies; if insert fails, function returns NULL.
 690        ret         = &target_Alloc();
 691        (*ret).target = key;
 692        bool good = target_XrefMaybe(*ret);
 693        if (!good) {
 694            target_RemoveLast(); // delete offending row, any existing xrefs are cleared
 695            ret = NULL;
 696        }
 697    }
 698    vrfy(ret, tempstr() << "abt.create_error  table:ind_target  key:'"<<key<<"'  comment:'bad xref'");
 699    return *ret;
 700}
 701
 702// --- abt.FDb.ind_target.InsertMaybe
 703// Insert row into hash table. Return true if row is reachable through the hash after the function completes.
 704bool abt::ind_target_InsertMaybe(abt::FTarget& row) {
 705    ind_target_Reserve(1);
 706    bool retval = true; // if already in hash, InsertMaybe returns true
 707    if (LIKELY(row.ind_target_next == (abt::FTarget*)-1)) {// check if in hash already
 708        u32 index = algo::Smallstr16_Hash(0, row.target) & (_db.ind_target_buckets_n - 1);
 709        abt::FTarget* *prev = &_db.ind_target_buckets_elems[index];
 710        do {
 711            abt::FTarget* ret = *prev;
 712            if (!ret) { // exit condition 1: reached the end of the list
 713                break;
 714            }
 715            if ((*ret).target == row.target) { // exit condition 2: found matching key
 716                retval = false;
 717                break;
 718            }
 719            prev = &ret->ind_target_next;
 720        } while (true);
 721        if (retval) {
 722            row.ind_target_next = *prev;
 723            _db.ind_target_n++;
 724            *prev = &row;
 725        }
 726    }
 727    return retval;
 728}
 729
 730// --- abt.FDb.ind_target.Remove
 731// Remove reference to element from hash index. If element is not in hash, do nothing
 732void abt::ind_target_Remove(abt::FTarget& row) {
 733    if (LIKELY(row.ind_target_next != (abt::FTarget*)-1)) {// check if in hash already
 734        u32 index = algo::Smallstr16_Hash(0, row.target) & (_db.ind_target_buckets_n - 1);
 735        abt::FTarget* *prev = &_db.ind_target_buckets_elems[index]; // addr of pointer to current element
 736        while (abt::FTarget *next = *prev) {                          // scan the collision chain for our element
 737            if (next == &row) {        // found it?
 738                *prev = next->ind_target_next; // unlink (singly linked list)
 739                _db.ind_target_n--;
 740                row.ind_target_next = (abt::FTarget*)-1;// not-in-hash
 741                break;
 742            }
 743            prev = &next->ind_target_next;
 744        }
 745    }
 746}
 747
 748// --- abt.FDb.ind_target.Reserve
 749// Reserve enough room in the hash for N more elements. Return success code.
 750void abt::ind_target_Reserve(int n) {
 751    u32 old_nbuckets = _db.ind_target_buckets_n;
 752    u32 new_nelems   = _db.ind_target_n + n;
 753    // # of elements has to be roughly equal to the number of buckets
 754    if (new_nelems > old_nbuckets) {
 755        int new_nbuckets = i32_Max(algo::BumpToPow2(new_nelems), u32(4));
 756        u32 old_size = old_nbuckets * sizeof(abt::FTarget*);
 757        u32 new_size = new_nbuckets * sizeof(abt::FTarget*);
 758        // allocate new array. we don't use Realloc since copying is not needed and factor of 2 probably
 759        // means new memory will have to be allocated anyway
 760        abt::FTarget* *new_buckets = (abt::FTarget**)abt::lpool_AllocMem(new_size);
 761        if (UNLIKELY(!new_buckets)) {
 762            FatalErrorExit("abt.out_of_memory  field:abt.FDb.ind_target");
 763        }
 764        memset(new_buckets, 0, new_size); // clear pointers
 765        // rehash all entries
 766        for (int i = 0; i < _db.ind_target_buckets_n; i++) {
 767            abt::FTarget* elem = _db.ind_target_buckets_elems[i];
 768            while (elem) {
 769                abt::FTarget &row        = *elem;
 770                abt::FTarget* next       = row.ind_target_next;
 771                u32 index          = algo::Smallstr16_Hash(0, row.target) & (new_nbuckets-1);
 772                row.ind_target_next     = new_buckets[index];
 773                new_buckets[index] = &row;
 774                elem               = next;
 775            }
 776        }
 777        // free old array
 778        abt::lpool_FreeMem(_db.ind_target_buckets_elems, old_size);
 779        _db.ind_target_buckets_elems = new_buckets;
 780        _db.ind_target_buckets_n = new_nbuckets;
 781    }
 782}
 783

 786// If out of memory, process is killed.

 789    if (UNLIKELY(row == NULL)) {
 790        FatalErrorExit("abt.out_of_mem  field:abt.FDb.target  comment:'Alloc failed'");
 791    }
 792    return *row;
 793}

 800        new (row) abt::FTarget; // call constructor
 801    }
 802    return row;
 803}

 805// --- abt.FDb.target.InsertMaybe
 806// Create new row from struct.
 807// Return pointer to new element, or NULL if insertion failed (due to out-of-memory, duplicate key, etc)
 808abt::FTarget* abt::target_InsertMaybe(const dev::Target &value) {
 809    abt::FTarget *row = &target_Alloc(); // if out of memory, process dies. if input error, return NULL.
 810    target_CopyIn(*row,const_cast<dev::Target&>(value));
 811    bool ok = target_XrefMaybe(*row); // this may return false
 812    if (!ok) {
 813        target_RemoveLast(); // delete offending row, any existing xrefs are cleared
 814        row = NULL; // forget this ever happened
 815    }
 816    return row;
 817}

 819// --- abt.FDb.target.AllocMem
 820// Allocate space for one element. If no memory available, return NULL.
 821void* abt::target_AllocMem() {
 822    u64 new_nelems     = _db.target_n+1;
 823    // compute level and index on level
 824    u64 bsr   = algo::u64_BitScanReverse(new_nelems);
 825    u64 base  = u64(1)<<bsr;
 826    u64 index = new_nelems-base;
 827    void *ret = NULL;
 828    // if level doesn't exist yet, create it
 829    abt::FTarget*  lev   = NULL;
 830    if (bsr < 32) {
 831        lev = _db.target_lary[bsr];
 832        if (!lev) {
 833            lev=(abt::FTarget*)abt::lpool_AllocMem(sizeof(abt::FTarget) * (u64(1)<<bsr));
 834            _db.target_lary[bsr] = lev;
 835        }
 836    }
 837    // allocate element from this level
 838    if (lev) {
 839        _db.target_n = i32(new_nelems);
 840        ret = lev + index;
 841    }
 842    return ret;
 843}

 845// --- abt.FDb.target.RemoveLast
 846// Delete last element of array. Do nothing if array is empty.
 847void abt::target_RemoveLast() {

 849    if (n > 0) {
 850        n -= 1;

 852        _db.target_n = i32(n);
 853    }
 854}

 863// --- abt.FDb.target.XrefMaybe
 864// Insert row into all appropriate indices. If error occurs, store error
 865// in algo_lib::_db.errtext and return false. Caller must Delete or Unref such row.
 866bool abt::target_XrefMaybe(abt::FTarget &row) {
 867    bool retval = true;
 868    (void)row;
 869    // insert target into index ind_target
 870    if (true) { // user-defined insert condition
 871        bool success = ind_target_InsertMaybe(row);
 872        if (UNLIKELY(!success)) {
 873            ch_RemoveAll(algo_lib::_db.errtext);
 874            algo_lib::_db.errtext << "abt.duplicate_key  xref:abt.FDb.ind_target"; // check for duplicate key
 875            return false;
 876        }
 877    }
 878    abt::FNs* p_target = abt::ind_ns_Find(row.target);
 879    if (UNLIKELY(!p_target)) {
 880        algo_lib::ResetErrtext() << "abt.bad_xref  index:abt.FDb.ind_ns" << Keyval("key", row.target);
 881        return false;
 882    }
 883    // target: save pointer to target
 884    if (true) { // user-defined insert condition
 885        row.p_ns = p_target;
 886    }
 887    return retval;
 888}

 890// --- abt.FDb.ind_targsrc.Find
 891// Find row by key. Return NULL if not found.
 892abt::FTargsrc* abt::ind_targsrc_Find(const algo::strptr& key) {
 893    u32 index = algo::Smallstr100_Hash(0, key) & (_db.ind_targsrc_buckets_n - 1);
 894    abt::FTargsrc* *e = &_db.ind_targsrc_buckets_elems[index];
 895    abt::FTargsrc* ret=NULL;
 896    do {
 897        ret       = *e;
 898        bool done = !ret || (*ret).targsrc == key;
 899        if (done) break;
 900        e         = &ret->ind_targsrc_next;
 901    } while (true);
 902    return ret;
 903}

 905// --- abt.FDb.ind_targsrc.GetOrCreate
 906// Find row by key. If not found, create and x-reference a new row with with this key.
 907abt::FTargsrc& abt::ind_targsrc_GetOrCreate(const algo::strptr& key) {
 908    abt::FTargsrc* ret = ind_targsrc_Find(key);
 909    if (!ret) { //  if memory alloc fails, process dies; if insert fails, function returns NULL.
 910        ret         = &targsrc_Alloc();
 911        (*ret).targsrc = key;
 912        bool good = targsrc_XrefMaybe(*ret);
 913        if (!good) {
 914            targsrc_RemoveLast(); // delete offending row, any existing xrefs are cleared
 915            ret = NULL;
 916        }
 917    }
 918    vrfy(ret, tempstr() << "abt.create_error  table:ind_targsrc  key:'"<<key<<"'  comment:'bad xref'");
 919    return *ret;
 920}

 922// --- abt.FDb.ind_targsrc.InsertMaybe

 924bool abt::ind_targsrc_InsertMaybe(abt::FTargsrc& row) {
 925    ind_targsrc_Reserve(1);
 926    bool retval = true; // if already in hash, InsertMaybe returns true
 927    if (LIKELY(row.ind_targsrc_next == (abt::FTargsrc*)-1)) {// check if in hash already
 928        u32 index = algo::Smallstr100_Hash(0, row.targsrc) & (_db.ind_targsrc_buckets_n - 1);
 929        abt::FTargsrc* *prev = &_db.ind_targsrc_buckets_elems[index];
 930        do {
 931            abt::FTargsrc* ret = *prev;
 932            if (!ret) { // exit condition 1: reached the end of the list
 933                break;
 934            }
 935            if ((*ret).targsrc == row.targsrc) { // exit condition 2: found matching key
 936                retval = false;
 937                break;
 938            }
 939            prev = &ret->ind_targsrc_next;
 940        } while (true);
 941        if (retval) {
 942            row.ind_targsrc_next = *prev;
 943            _db.ind_targsrc_n++;
 944            *prev = &row;
 945        }
 946    }
 947    return retval;
 948}

 952void abt::ind_targsrc_Remove(abt::FTargsrc& row) {
 953    if (LIKELY(row.ind_targsrc_next != (abt::FTargsrc*)-1)) {// check if in hash already
 954        u32 index = algo::Smallstr100_Hash(0, row.targsrc) & (_db.ind_targsrc_buckets_n - 1);
 955        abt::FTargsrc* *prev = &_db.ind_targsrc_buckets_elems[index]; // addr of pointer to current element
 956        while (abt::FTargsrc *next = *prev) {                          // scan the collision chain for our element
 957            if (next == &row) {        // found it?
 958                *prev = next->ind_targsrc_next; // unlink (singly linked list)
 959                _db.ind_targsrc_n--;
 960                row.ind_targsrc_next = (abt::FTargsrc*)-1;// not-in-hash
 961                break;
 962            }
 963            prev = &next->ind_targsrc_next;
 964        }
 965    }
 966}

 968// --- abt.FDb.ind_targsrc.Reserve
 969// Reserve enough room in the hash for N more elements. Return success code.
 970void abt::ind_targsrc_Reserve(int n) {
 971    u32 old_nbuckets = _db.ind_targsrc_buckets_n;
 972    u32 new_nelems   = _db.ind_targsrc_n + n;
 973    // # of elements has to be roughly equal to the number of buckets
 974    if (new_nelems > old_nbuckets) {
 975        int new_nbuckets = i32_Max(algo::BumpToPow2(new_nelems), u32(4));
 976        u32 old_size = old_nbuckets * sizeof(abt::FTargsrc*);
 977        u32 new_size = new_nbuckets * sizeof(abt::FTargsrc*);
 978        // allocate new array. we don't use Realloc since copying is not needed and factor of 2 probably
 979        // means new memory will have to be allocated anyway
 980        abt::FTargsrc* *new_buckets = (abt::FTargsrc**)abt::lpool_AllocMem(new_size);
 981        if (UNLIKELY(!new_buckets)) {
 982            FatalErrorExit("abt.out_of_memory  field:abt.FDb.ind_targsrc");
 983        }
 984        memset(new_buckets, 0, new_size); // clear pointers
 985        // rehash all entries
 986        for (int i = 0; i < _db.ind_targsrc_buckets_n; i++) {
 987            abt::FTargsrc* elem = _db.ind_targsrc_buckets_elems[i];
 988            while (elem) {
 989                abt::FTargsrc &row        = *elem;
 990                abt::FTargsrc* next       = row.ind_targsrc_next;
 991                u32 index          = algo::Smallstr100_Hash(0, row.targsrc) & (new_nbuckets-1);
 992                row.ind_targsrc_next     = new_buckets[index];
 993                new_buckets[index] = &row;
 994                elem               = next;
 995            }
 996        }
 997        // free old array
 998        abt::lpool_FreeMem(_db.ind_targsrc_buckets_elems, old_size);
 999        _db.ind_targsrc_buckets_elems = new_buckets;
1000        _db.ind_targsrc_buckets_n = new_nbuckets;
1001    }
1002}
1003
1004// --- abt.FDb.targsrc.Alloc
1005// Allocate memory for new default row.
1006// If out of memory, process is killed.
1007abt::FTargsrc& abt::targsrc_Alloc() {
1008    abt::FTargsrc* row = targsrc_AllocMaybe();
1009    if (UNLIKELY(row == NULL)) {
1010        FatalErrorExit("abt.out_of_mem  field:abt.FDb.targsrc  comment:'Alloc failed'");
1011    }
1012    return *row;
1013}
1014
1015// --- abt.FDb.targsrc.AllocMaybe
1016// Allocate memory for new element. If out of memory, return NULL.
1017abt::FTargsrc* abt::targsrc_AllocMaybe() {
1018    abt::FTargsrc *row = (abt::FTargsrc*)targsrc_AllocMem();
1019    if (row) {
1020        new (row) abt::FTargsrc; // call constructor
1021    }
1022    return row;
1023}
1024
1025// --- abt.FDb.targsrc.InsertMaybe
1026// Create new row from struct.
1027// Return pointer to new element, or NULL if insertion failed (due to out-of-memory, duplicate key, etc)
1028abt::FTargsrc* abt::targsrc_InsertMaybe(const dev::Targsrc &value) {
1029    abt::FTargsrc *row = &targsrc_Alloc(); // if out of memory, process dies. if input error, return NULL.
1030    targsrc_CopyIn(*row,const_cast<dev::Targsrc&>(value));
1031    bool ok = targsrc_XrefMaybe(*row); // this may return false
1032    if (!ok) {
1033        targsrc_RemoveLast(); // delete offending row, any existing xrefs are cleared
1034        row = NULL; // forget this ever happened
1035    }
1036    return row;
1037}
1038
1039// --- abt.FDb.targsrc.AllocMem
1040// Allocate space for one element. If no memory available, return NULL.
1041void* abt::targsrc_AllocMem() {
1042    u64 new_nelems     = _db.targsrc_n+1;
1043    // compute level and index on level
1044    u64 bsr   = algo::u64_BitScanReverse(new_nelems);
1045    u64 base  = u64(1)<<bsr;
1046    u64 index = new_nelems-base;
1047    void *ret = NULL;
1048    // if level doesn't exist yet, create it
1049    abt::FTargsrc*  lev   = NULL;
1050    if (bsr < 32) {
1051        lev = _db.targsrc_lary[bsr];
1052        if (!lev) {
1053            lev=(abt::FTargsrc*)abt::lpool_AllocMem(sizeof(abt::FTargsrc) * (u64(1)<<bsr));
1054            _db.targsrc_lary[bsr] = lev;
1055        }
1056    }
1057    // allocate element from this level
1058    if (lev) {
1059        _db.targsrc_n = i32(new_nelems);
1060        ret = lev + index;
1061    }
1062    return ret;
1063}
1064
1065// --- abt.FDb.targsrc.RemoveLast
1066// Delete last element of array. Do nothing if array is empty.
1067void abt::targsrc_RemoveLast() {
1068    u64 n = _db.targsrc_n;
1069    if (n > 0) {
1070        n -= 1;
1071        targsrc_qFind(u64(n)).~FTargsrc();
1072        _db.targsrc_n = i32(n);
1073    }
1074}
1075
1076// --- abt.FDb.targsrc.InputMaybe
1077static bool abt::targsrc_InputMaybe(dev::Targsrc &elem) {
1078    bool retval = true;
1079    retval = targsrc_InsertMaybe(elem) != nullptr;
1080    return retval;
1081}
1082
1083// --- abt.FDb.targsrc.XrefMaybe
1084// Insert row into all appropriate indices. If error occurs, store error
1085// in algo_lib::_db.errtext and return false. Caller must Delete or Unref such row.
1086bool abt::targsrc_XrefMaybe(abt::FTargsrc &row) {
1087    bool retval = true;
1088    (void)row;
1089    abt::FTarget* p_target = abt::ind_target_Find(target_Get(row));
1090    if (UNLIKELY(!p_target)) {
1091        algo_lib::ResetErrtext() << "abt.bad_xref  index:abt.FDb.ind_target" << Keyval("key", target_Get(row));
1092        return false;
1093    }
1094    // insert targsrc into index c_targsrc
1095    if (true) { // user-defined insert condition
1096        c_targsrc_Insert(*p_target, row);
1097    }
1098    // insert targsrc into index ind_targsrc
1099    if (true) { // user-defined insert condition
1100        bool success = ind_targsrc_InsertMaybe(row);
1101        if (UNLIKELY(!success)) {
1102            ch_RemoveAll(algo_lib::_db.errtext);
1103            algo_lib::_db.errtext << "abt.duplicate_key  xref:abt.FDb.ind_targsrc"; // check for duplicate key
1104            return false;
1105        }
1106    }
1107    // targsrc: save pointer to target
1108    if (true) { // user-defined insert condition
1109        row.p_target = p_target;
1110    }
1111    return retval;
1112}

1192
1193// --- abt.FDb.syscmddep.XrefMaybe
1194// Insert row into all appropriate indices. If error occurs, store error
1195// in algo_lib::_db.errtext and return false. Caller must Delete or Unref such row.
1196bool abt::syscmddep_XrefMaybe(abt::FSyscmddep &row) {
1197    bool retval = true;
1198    (void)row;
1199    abt::FSyscmd* p_child = abt::ind_syscmd_Find(row.child);
1200    if (UNLIKELY(!p_child)) {
1201        algo_lib::ResetErrtext() << "abt.bad_xref  index:abt.FDb.ind_syscmd" << Keyval("key", row.child);
1202        return false;
1203    }
1204    // insert syscmddep into index c_prior
1205    if (true) { // user-defined insert condition
1206        c_prior_Insert(*p_child, row);
1207    }
1208    abt::FSyscmd* p_parent = abt::ind_syscmd_Find(row.parent);
1209    if (UNLIKELY(!p_parent)) {
1210        algo_lib::ResetErrtext() << "abt.bad_xref  index:abt.FDb.ind_syscmd" << Keyval("key", row.parent);
1211        return false;
1212    }
1213    // insert syscmddep into index c_next
1214    if (true) { // user-defined insert condition
1215        c_next_Insert(*p_parent, row);
1216    }
1217    // syscmddep: save pointer to child
1218    if (true) { // user-defined insert condition
1219        row.p_child = p_child;
1220    }
1221    // syscmddep: save pointer to parent
1222    if (true) { // user-defined insert condition
1223        row.p_parent = p_parent;
1224    }
1225    return retval;
1226}

1308// --- abt.FDb.syscmd.XrefMaybe
1309// Insert row into all appropriate indices. If error occurs, store error
1310// in algo_lib::_db.errtext and return false. Caller must Delete or Unref such row.
1311bool abt::syscmd_XrefMaybe(abt::FSyscmd &row) {
1312    bool retval = true;
1313    (void)row;
1314    // insert syscmd into index ind_syscmd
1315    if (true) { // user-defined insert condition
1316        bool success = ind_syscmd_InsertMaybe(row);
1317        if (UNLIKELY(!success)) {
1318            ch_RemoveAll(algo_lib::_db.errtext);
1319            algo_lib::_db.errtext << "abt.duplicate_key  xref:abt.FDb.ind_syscmd"; // check for duplicate key
1320            return false;
1321        }
1322    }
1323    // insert syscmd into index ind_running
1324    if (row.pid != 0) { // user-defined insert condition
1325        bool success = ind_running_InsertMaybe(row);
1326        if (UNLIKELY(!success)) {
1327            ch_RemoveAll(algo_lib::_db.errtext);
1328            algo_lib::_db.errtext << "abt.duplicate_key  xref:abt.FDb.ind_running"; // check for duplicate key
1329            return false;
1330        }
1331    }
1332    return retval;
1333}
1334
1335// --- abt.FDb._db.ReadArgv
1336// Read argc,argv directly into the fields of the command line(s)
1337// The following fields are updated:
1338//     abt.FDb.cmdline
1339//     algo_lib.FDb.cmdline
1340void abt::ReadArgv() {
1341    command::abt &cmd = abt::_db.cmdline;
1342    algo_lib::Cmdline &base = algo_lib::_db.cmdline;
1343    int needarg=-1;// unknown
1344    int argidx=1;// skip process name
1345    int anonidx=0;
1346    algo::strptr nextanon = command::abt_GetAnon(cmd, anonidx);
1347    tempstr err;
1348    algo::strptr attrname;
1349    bool isanon=false; // true if attrname is anonfld (positional)
1350    algo_lib::FieldId baseattrid;
1351    command::FieldId attrid;
1352    bool endopt=false;
1353    int whichns=0;// which namespace does the current attribute belong to
1354    for (; argidx < algo_lib::_db.argc; argidx++) {
1355        algo::strptr arg = algo_lib::_db.argv[argidx];
1356        algo::strptr attrval;
1357        algo::strptr dfltval;
1358        bool haveval=false;
1359        bool dash=elems_N(arg)>1 && arg.elems[0]=='-'; // a single dash is not an option
1360        // this attribute is a value
1361        if (endopt || needarg>0 || !dash) {
1362            attrval=arg;
1363            haveval=true;
1364        } else {
1365            // this attribute is a field name (with - or --)
1366            // or a -- by itself
1367            bool dashdash = elems_N(arg) >= 2 && arg.elems[1]=='-';
1368            int skip = int(dash) + dashdash;
1369            attrname=ch_RestFrom(arg,skip);
1370            if (skip==2 && elems_N(arg)==2) {
1371                endopt=true;
1372                continue;// nothing else to do here
1373            }
1374            // parse "-a:B" arg into attrname,attrvalue
1375            algo::i32_Range colon = TFind(attrname,':');
1376            if (colon.beg < colon.end) {
1377                attrval=ch_RestFrom(attrname,colon.end);
1378                attrname=ch_FirstN(attrname,colon.beg);
1379                haveval=true;
1380            }
1381            // look up which command (this one or the base) contains the field
1382            whichns=0;
1383            needarg=-1;
1384            // look up parameter information in base namespace (needarg will be -1 if lookup fails)
1385            if (algo_lib::FieldId_ReadStrptrMaybe(baseattrid,attrname)) {
1386                needarg = algo_lib::Cmdline_NArgs(baseattrid,dfltval,&isanon);
1387            }
1388            if (needarg<0) {
1389                whichns=1;
1390                // look up parameter information in this namespace (needarg will be -1 if lookup fails)
1391                if (command::FieldId_ReadStrptrMaybe(attrid,attrname)) {
1392                    needarg = command::abt_NArgs(attrid,dfltval,&isanon);
1393                }
1394            }
1395            if (attrval == "" && dfltval != "") {
1396                attrval=dfltval;
1397                haveval=true;
1398            }
1399            if (needarg<0) {
1400                err<<"abt: unknown option "<<Keyval("value",arg)<<eol;
1401            } else {
1402                if (isanon) {
1403                    if (attrname == nextanon) { // treat named anon (positional) argument as unnamed
1404                        attrname = ""; // treat it as unnamed
1405                    } else if (nextanon != "") { // disallow out-of-order anon (positional) args
1406                        err<<"abt: error at "<<algo::strptr_ToSsim(arg)<<": must be preceded by [-"<<nextanon<<"]"<<eol;
1407                    }
1408                }
1409            }
1410        }
1411        // look up anon field name based on index
1412        // anon fields are only allowed in the leaf ns, never base
1413        if (ch_N(attrname) == 0) {
1414            attrname = nextanon;
1415            nextanon = command::abt_GetAnon(cmd, ++anonidx);
1416            command::FieldId_ReadStrptrMaybe(attrid,attrname);
1417            whichns=1;
1418        }
1419        if (ch_N(attrname) == 0) {
1420            err << "abt: too many arguments. error at "<<algo::strptr_ToSsim(arg)<<eol;
1421        }
1422        // read value into currently selected arg
1423        if (haveval) {
1424            bool ret=false;
1425            // it's already known which namespace is consuming the args,
1426            // so directly go there
1427            if (whichns == 0) {
1428                ret=algo_lib::Cmdline_ReadFieldMaybe(base, attrname, attrval);
1429            }
1430            if (whichns==1) {
1431                ret=command::abt_ReadFieldMaybe(cmd, attrname, attrval);
1432                switch(attrid.value) {
1433                    default:break;
1434                }
1435            }
1436            if (!ret) {
1437                err<<"abt: error in "
1438                <<Keyval("option",attrname)
1439                <<Keyval("value",attrval)<<eol;
1440            }
1441            needarg--;
1442            if (needarg <= 0) {
1443                attrname="";// forget which argument was being filled
1444            }
1445        }
1446    }
1447    bool dohelp = false;
1448    bool doexit=false;
1449    if (algo_lib::_db.cmdline.help) {
1450        dohelp = true;
1451        doexit = true;
1452        algo_lib::_db.exit_code = 1; // help exits with non-zero status code
1453    } else if (algo_lib::_db.cmdline.version) {
1454        // -ver output goes to stdout
1455        prlog(algo::gitinfo_Get());
1456        doexit = true;
1457    } else if (algo_lib::_db.cmdline.signature) {
1458        ind_beg(algo_lib::_db_dispsigcheck_curs,dispsigcheck,algo_lib::_db) {
1459            // dispsig goes to stdout
1460            dmmeta::Dispsigcheck out;
1461            dispsigcheck_CopyOut(dispsigcheck,out);
1462            prlog(out);
1463        }ind_end
1464        doexit = true;
1465    }
1466    if (!dohelp) {
1467    }
1468    // dmmeta.floadtuples:abt.FDb.cmdline
1469    if (!dohelp && err=="") {
1470        algo_lib::ResetErrtext();
1471        if (!abt::LoadTuplesMaybe(cmd.in,true)) {
1472            err << "abt.load_input  "<<algo_lib::DetachBadTags()<<eol;
1473        }
1474    }
1475    if (err != "") {
1476        algo_lib::_db.exit_code=1;
1477        prerr(err);
1478        doexit=true;
1479    }
1480    if (dohelp) {
1481        prlog(abt_help);
1482    }
1483    if (doexit) {
1484        _exit(algo_lib::_db.exit_code);
1485    }
1486    algo_lib::ResetErrtext();
1487}
1488
1489// --- abt.FDb._db.MainLoop
1490// Main loop.
1491void abt::MainLoop() {
1492    algo::SchedTime time(algo::get_cycles());
1493    algo_lib::_db.clock          = time;
1494    do {
1495        algo_lib::_db.next_loop.value = algo_lib::_db.limit;
1496        abt::Steps();
1497    } while (algo_lib::_db.next_loop < algo_lib::_db.limit);
1498}
1499
1500// --- abt.FDb._db.Step
1501// Main step
1502void abt::Step() {
1503}
1504
1505// --- abt.FDb._db.InitReflection
1506// Load statically available data into tables, register tables and database.
1507static void abt::InitReflection() {
1508    algo_lib::imdb_InsertMaybe(algo::Imdb("abt", abt::InsertStrptrMaybe, NULL, abt::MainLoop, NULL, algo::Comment()));
1509
1510    algo::Imtable t_trace;
1511    t_trace.imtable         = "abt.trace";
1512    t_trace.ssimfile        = "";
1513    t_trace.size            = sizeof(abt::trace);
1514    t_trace.comment.value   = "";
1515    t_trace.c_RowidFind     = trace_RowidFind;
1516    t_trace.NItems          = trace_N;
1517    t_trace.Print           = (algo::ImrowPrintFcn)abt::trace_Print;
1518    algo_lib::imtable_InsertMaybe(t_trace);
1519
1520
1521    // -- load signatures of existing dispatches --
1522    algo_lib::InsertStrptrMaybe("dmmeta.Dispsigcheck  dispsig:'abt.Input'  signature:'c19adc35633653a85ee5ea1cc7565d6328cf53e5'");
1523}
1524
1525// --- abt.FDb._db.InsertStrptrMaybe
1526// Parse strptr into known type and add to database.
1527// Return value is true unless an error occurs. If return value is false, algo_lib::_db.errtext has error text
1528bool abt::InsertStrptrMaybe(algo::strptr str) {
1529    bool retval = true;
1530    abt::TableId table_id(-1);
1531    value_SetStrptrMaybe(table_id, algo::GetTypeTag(str));
1532    switch (value_GetEnum(table_id)) {
1533        case abt_TableId_dev_Targdep: { // finput:abt.FDb.targdep
1534            dev::Targdep elem;
1535            retval = dev::Targdep_ReadStrptrMaybe(elem, str);
1536            retval = retval && targdep_InputMaybe(elem);
1537            break;
1538        }
1539        case abt_TableId_dev_ToolOpt: { // finput:abt.FDb.tool_opt
1540            dev::ToolOpt elem;
1541            retval = dev::ToolOpt_ReadStrptrMaybe(elem, str);
1542            retval = retval && tool_opt_InputMaybe(elem);
1543            break;
1544        }
1545        case abt_TableId_dev_Target: { // finput:abt.FDb.target
1546            dev::Target elem;
1547            retval = dev::Target_ReadStrptrMaybe(elem, str);
1548            retval = retval && target_InputMaybe(elem);
1549            break;
1550        }
1551        case abt_TableId_dev_Targsrc: { // finput:abt.FDb.targsrc
1552            dev::Targsrc elem;
1553            retval = dev::Targsrc_ReadStrptrMaybe(elem, str);
1554            retval = retval && targsrc_InputMaybe(elem);
1555            break;
1556        }
1557        case abt_TableId_dev_Syscmddep: { // finput:abt.FDb.syscmddep
1558            dev::Syscmddep elem;
1559            retval = dev::Syscmddep_ReadStrptrMaybe(elem, str);
1560            retval = retval && syscmddep_InputMaybe(elem);
1561            break;
1562        }
1563        case abt_TableId_dev_Syscmd: { // finput:abt.FDb.syscmd
1564            dev::Syscmd elem;
1565            retval = dev::Syscmd_ReadStrptrMaybe(elem, str);
1566            retval = retval && syscmd_InputMaybe(elem);
1567            break;
1568        }
1569        case abt_TableId_dev_Cfg: { // finput:abt.FDb.cfg
1570            dev::Cfg elem;
1571            retval = dev::Cfg_ReadStrptrMaybe(elem, str);
1572            retval = retval && cfg_InputMaybe(elem);
1573            break;
1574        }
1575        case abt_TableId_dev_Uname: { // finput:abt.FDb.uname
1576            dev::Uname elem;
1577            retval = dev::Uname_ReadStrptrMaybe(elem, str);
1578            retval = retval && uname_InputMaybe(elem);
1579            break;
1580        }
1581        case abt_TableId_dev_Compiler: { // finput:abt.FDb.compiler
1582            dev::Compiler elem;
1583            retval = dev::Compiler_ReadStrptrMaybe(elem, str);
1584            retval = retval && compiler_InputMaybe(elem);
1585            break;
1586        }
1587        case abt_TableId_dev_Arch: { // finput:abt.FDb.arch
1588            dev::Arch elem;
1589            retval = dev::Arch_ReadStrptrMaybe(elem, str);
1590            retval = retval && arch_InputMaybe(elem);
1591            break;
1592        }
1593        case abt_TableId_dev_Targsyslib: { // finput:abt.FDb.targsyslib
1594            dev::Targsyslib elem;
1595            retval = dev::Targsyslib_ReadStrptrMaybe(elem, str);
1596            retval = retval && targsyslib_InputMaybe(elem);
1597            break;
1598        }
1599        case abt_TableId_dev_Syslib: { // finput:abt.FDb.syslib
1600            dev::Syslib elem;
1601            retval = dev::Syslib_ReadStrptrMaybe(elem, str);
1602            retval = retval && syslib_InputMaybe(elem);
1603            break;
1604        }
1605        case abt_TableId_dev_Include: { // finput:abt.FDb.include
1606            dev::Include elem;
1607            retval = dev::Include_ReadStrptrMaybe(elem, str);
1608            retval = retval && include_InputMaybe(elem);
1609            break;
1610        }
1611        case abt_TableId_dmmeta_Ns: { // finput:abt.FDb.ns
1612            dmmeta::Ns elem;
1613            retval = dmmeta::Ns_ReadStrptrMaybe(elem, str);
1614            retval = retval && ns_InputMaybe(elem);
1615            break;
1616        }
1617        default:
1618        break;
1619    } //switch
1620    if (!retval) {
1621        algo_lib::NoteInsertErr(str); // increment error counter
1622    }
1623    return retval;
1624}
1625
1626// --- abt.FDb._db.LoadTuplesMaybe
1627// Load all finputs from given directory.
1628bool abt::LoadTuplesMaybe(algo::strptr root, bool recursive) {
1629    bool retval = true;
1630    if (FileQ(root)) {
1631        retval = abt::LoadTuplesFile(root, recursive);
1632    } else if (root == "-") {
1633        retval = abt::LoadTuplesFd(algo::Fildes(0),"(stdin)",recursive);
1634    } else if (DirectoryQ(root)) {
1635        retval = retval && abt::LoadTuplesFile(algo::SsimFname(root,"dmmeta.ns"),recursive);
1636        retval = retval && abt::LoadTuplesFile(algo::SsimFname(root,"dmmeta.dispsigcheck"),recursive);
1637        retval = retval && abt::LoadTuplesFile(algo::SsimFname(root,"dev.uname"),recursive);
1638        retval = retval && abt::LoadTuplesFile(algo::SsimFname(root,"dev.tool_opt"),recursive);
1639        retval = retval && abt::LoadTuplesFile(algo::SsimFname(root,"dev.target"),recursive);
1640        retval = retval && abt::LoadTuplesFile(algo::SsimFname(root,"dev.syslib"),recursive);
1641        retval = retval && abt::LoadTuplesFile(algo::SsimFname(root,"dev.targsyslib"),recursive);
1642        retval = retval && abt::LoadTuplesFile(algo::SsimFname(root,"dev.targsrc"),recursive);
1643        retval = retval && abt::LoadTuplesFile(algo::SsimFname(root,"dev.targdep"),recursive);
1644        retval = retval && abt::LoadTuplesFile(algo::SsimFname(root,"dev.syscmd"),recursive);
1645        retval = retval && abt::LoadTuplesFile(algo::SsimFname(root,"dev.syscmddep"),recursive);
1646        retval = retval && abt::LoadTuplesFile(algo::SsimFname(root,"dev.include"),recursive);
1647        retval = retval && abt::LoadTuplesFile(algo::SsimFname(root,"dev.compiler"),recursive);
1648        retval = retval && abt::LoadTuplesFile(algo::SsimFname(root,"dev.cfg"),recursive);
1649        retval = retval && abt::LoadTuplesFile(algo::SsimFname(root,"dev.arch"),recursive);
1650    } else {
1651        algo_lib::SaveBadTag("path", root);
1652        algo_lib::SaveBadTag("comment", "Wrong working directory?");
1653        retval = false;
1654    }
1655    return retval;
1656}
1657
1658// --- abt.FDb._db.LoadTuplesFile
1659// Load all finputs from given file.
1660// Read tuples from file FNAME into this namespace's in-memory database.
1661// If RECURSIVE is TRUE, then also load these tuples into any parent namespaces
1662// It a file referred to by FNAME is missing, no error is reported (it's considered an empty set).
1663// Function returns TRUE if all records were parsed and inserted without error.
1664// If the function returns FALSE, use algo_lib::DetachBadTags() for error description
1665bool abt::LoadTuplesFile(algo::strptr fname, bool recursive) {
1666    bool retval = true;
1667    algo_lib::FFildes fildes;
1668    // missing files are not an error
1669    fildes.fd = OpenRead(fname,algo::FileFlags());
1670    if (ValidQ(fildes.fd)) {
1671        retval = LoadTuplesFd(fildes.fd, fname, recursive);
1672    }
1673    return retval;
1674}
1675
1676// --- abt.FDb._db.LoadTuplesFd
1677// Load all finputs from given file descriptor.
1678bool abt::LoadTuplesFd(algo::Fildes fd, algo::strptr fname, bool recursive) {
1679    bool retval = true;
1680    ind_beg(algo::FileLine_curs,line,fd) {
1681        if (recursive) {
1682            retval = retval && algo_lib::InsertStrptrMaybe(line);
1683        }
1684        retval = retval && abt::InsertStrptrMaybe(line);
1685        if (!retval) {
1686            algo_lib::_db.errtext << eol
1687            << fname << ":"
1688            << (ind_curs(line).i+1)
1689            << ": " << line << eol;
1690            break;
1691        }
1692    }ind_end;
1693    return retval;
1694}
1695
1696// --- abt.FDb._db.LoadSsimfileMaybe
1697// Load specified ssimfile.
1698bool abt::LoadSsimfileMaybe(algo::strptr fname, bool recursive) {
1699    bool retval = true;
1700    if (FileQ(fname)) {
1701        retval = abt::LoadTuplesFile(fname, recursive);
1702    }
1703    return retval;
1704}

1706// --- abt.FDb._db.Steps
1707// Calls Step function of dependencies
1708void abt::Steps() {
1709    algo_lib::Step(); // dependent namespace specified via (dev.targdep)
1710}

1712// --- abt.FDb._db.XrefMaybe
1713// Insert row into all appropriate indices. If error occurs, store error
1714// in algo_lib::_db.errtext and return false. Caller must Delete or Unref such row.
1715bool abt::_db_XrefMaybe() {
1716    bool retval = true;
1717    return retval;
1718}
1719
1720// --- abt.FDb.ind_syscmd.Find
1721// Find row by key. Return NULL if not found.
1722abt::FSyscmd* abt::ind_syscmd_Find(i64 key) {
1723    u32 index = ::i64_Hash(0, key) & (_db.ind_syscmd_buckets_n - 1);
1724    abt::FSyscmd* *e = &_db.ind_syscmd_buckets_elems[index];
1725    abt::FSyscmd* ret=NULL;
1726    do {
1727        ret       = *e;
1728        bool done = !ret || (*ret).syscmd == key;
1729        if (done) break;
1730        e         = &ret->ind_syscmd_next;
1731    } while (true);
1732    return ret;
1733}
1734
1735// --- abt.FDb.ind_syscmd.GetOrCreate
1736// Find row by key. If not found, create and x-reference a new row with with this key.
1737abt::FSyscmd& abt::ind_syscmd_GetOrCreate(i64 key) {
1738    abt::FSyscmd* ret = ind_syscmd_Find(key);
1739    if (!ret) { //  if memory alloc fails, process dies; if insert fails, function returns NULL.
1740        ret         = &syscmd_Alloc();
1741        (*ret).syscmd = key;
1742        bool good = syscmd_XrefMaybe(*ret);
1743        if (!good) {
1744            syscmd_RemoveLast(); // delete offending row, any existing xrefs are cleared
1745            ret = NULL;
1746        }
1747    }
1748    vrfy(ret, tempstr() << "abt.create_error  table:ind_syscmd  key:'"<<key<<"'  comment:'bad xref'");
1749    return *ret;
1750}
1751
1752// --- abt.FDb.ind_syscmd.InsertMaybe
1753// Insert row into hash table. Return true if row is reachable through the hash after the function completes.
1754bool abt::ind_syscmd_InsertMaybe(abt::FSyscmd& row) {
1755    ind_syscmd_Reserve(1);
1756    bool retval = true; // if already in hash, InsertMaybe returns true
1757    if (LIKELY(row.ind_syscmd_next == (abt::FSyscmd*)-1)) {// check if in hash already
1758        u32 index = ::i64_Hash(0, row.syscmd) & (_db.ind_syscmd_buckets_n - 1);
1759        abt::FSyscmd* *prev = &_db.ind_syscmd_buckets_elems[index];
1760        do {
1761            abt::FSyscmd* ret = *prev;
1762            if (!ret) { // exit condition 1: reached the end of the list
1763                break;
1764            }
1765            if ((*ret).syscmd == row.syscmd) { // exit condition 2: found matching key
1766                retval = false;
1767                break;
1768            }
1769            prev = &ret->ind_syscmd_next;
1770        } while (true);
1771        if (retval) {
1772            row.ind_syscmd_next = *prev;
1773            _db.ind_syscmd_n++;
1774            *prev = &row;
1775        }
1776    }
1777    return retval;
1778}
1779
1780// --- abt.FDb.ind_syscmd.Remove
1781// Remove reference to element from hash index. If element is not in hash, do nothing
1782void abt::ind_syscmd_Remove(abt::FSyscmd& row) {
1783    if (LIKELY(row.ind_syscmd_next != (abt::FSyscmd*)-1)) {// check if in hash already
1784        u32 index = ::i64_Hash(0, row.syscmd) & (_db.ind_syscmd_buckets_n - 1);
1785        abt::FSyscmd* *prev = &_db.ind_syscmd_buckets_elems[index]; // addr of pointer to current element
1786        while (abt::FSyscmd *next = *prev) {                          // scan the collision chain for our element
1787            if (next == &row) {        // found it?
1788                *prev = next->ind_syscmd_next; // unlink (singly linked list)
1789                _db.ind_syscmd_n--;
1790                row.ind_syscmd_next = (abt::FSyscmd*)-1;// not-in-hash
1791                break;
1792            }
1793            prev = &next->ind_syscmd_next;
1794        }
1795    }
1796}
1797
1798// --- abt.FDb.ind_syscmd.Reserve
1799// Reserve enough room in the hash for N more elements. Return success code.
1800void abt::ind_syscmd_Reserve(int n) {
1801    u32 old_nbuckets = _db.ind_syscmd_buckets_n;
1802    u32 new_nelems   = _db.ind_syscmd_n + n;
1803    // # of elements has to be roughly equal to the number of buckets
1804    if (new_nelems > old_nbuckets) {
1805        int new_nbuckets = i32_Max(algo::BumpToPow2(new_nelems), u32(4));
1806        u32 old_size = old_nbuckets * sizeof(abt::FSyscmd*);
1807        u32 new_size = new_nbuckets * sizeof(abt::FSyscmd*);
1808        // allocate new array. we don't use Realloc since copying is not needed and factor of 2 probably
1809        // means new memory will have to be allocated anyway
1810        abt::FSyscmd* *new_buckets = (abt::FSyscmd**)abt::lpool_AllocMem(new_size);
1811        if (UNLIKELY(!new_buckets)) {
1812            FatalErrorExit("abt.out_of_memory  field:abt.FDb.ind_syscmd");
1813        }
1814        memset(new_buckets, 0, new_size); // clear pointers
1815        // rehash all entries
1816        for (int i = 0; i < _db.ind_syscmd_buckets_n; i++) {
1817            abt::FSyscmd* elem = _db.ind_syscmd_buckets_elems[i];
1818            while (elem) {
1819                abt::FSyscmd &row        = *elem;
1820                abt::FSyscmd* next       = row.ind_syscmd_next;
1821                u32 index          = ::i64_Hash(0, row.syscmd) & (new_nbuckets-1);
1822                row.ind_syscmd_next     = new_buckets[index];
1823                new_buckets[index] = &row;
1824                elem               = next;
1825            }
1826        }
1827        // free old array
1828        abt::lpool_FreeMem(_db.ind_syscmd_buckets_elems, old_size);
1829        _db.ind_syscmd_buckets_elems = new_buckets;
1830        _db.ind_syscmd_buckets_n = new_nbuckets;
1831    }
1832}
1833

1847}

2007
2008// --- abt.FDb.ind_srcfile.Remove
2009// Remove reference to element from hash index. If element is not in hash, do nothing
2010void abt::ind_srcfile_Remove(abt::FSrcfile& row) {
2011    if (LIKELY(row.ind_srcfile_next != (abt::FSrcfile*)-1)) {// check if in hash already
2012        u32 index = algo::Smallstr200_Hash(0, row.srcfile) & (_db.ind_srcfile_buckets_n - 1);
2013        abt::FSrcfile* *prev = &_db.ind_srcfile_buckets_elems[index]; // addr of pointer to current element
2014        while (abt::FSrcfile *next = *prev) {                          // scan the collision chain for our element
2015            if (next == &row) {        // found it?
2016                *prev = next->ind_srcfile_next; // unlink (singly linked list)
2017                _db.ind_srcfile_n--;
2018                row.ind_srcfile_next = (abt::FSrcfile*)-1;// not-in-hash
2019                break;
2020            }
2021            prev = &next->ind_srcfile_next;
2022        }
2023    }
2024}
2025
2026// --- abt.FDb.ind_srcfile.Reserve
2027// Reserve enough room in the hash for N more elements. Return success code.
2028void abt::ind_srcfile_Reserve(int n) {
2029    u32 old_nbuckets = _db.ind_srcfile_buckets_n;
2030    u32 new_nelems   = _db.ind_srcfile_n + n;
2031    // # of elements has to be roughly equal to the number of buckets
2032    if (new_nelems > old_nbuckets) {
2033        int new_nbuckets = i32_Max(algo::BumpToPow2(new_nelems), u32(4));
2034        u32 old_size = old_nbuckets * sizeof(abt::FSrcfile*);
2035        u32 new_size = new_nbuckets * sizeof(abt::FSrcfile*);
2036        // allocate new array. we don't use Realloc since copying is not needed and factor of 2 probably
2037        // means new memory will have to be allocated anyway
2038        abt::FSrcfile* *new_buckets = (abt::FSrcfile**)abt::lpool_AllocMem(new_size);
2039        if (UNLIKELY(!new_buckets)) {
2040            FatalErrorExit("abt.out_of_memory  field:abt.FDb.ind_srcfile");
2041        }
2042        memset(new_buckets, 0, new_size); // clear pointers
2043        // rehash all entries
2044        for (int i = 0; i < _db.ind_srcfile_buckets_n; i++) {
2045            abt::FSrcfile* elem = _db.ind_srcfile_buckets_elems[i];
2046            while (elem) {
2047                abt::FSrcfile &row        = *elem;
2048                abt::FSrcfile* next       = row.ind_srcfile_next;
2049                u32 index          = algo::Smallstr200_Hash(0, row.srcfile) & (new_nbuckets-1);
2050                row.ind_srcfile_next     = new_buckets[index];
2051                new_buckets[index] = &row;
2052                elem               = next;
2053            }
2054        }
2055        // free old array
2056        abt::lpool_FreeMem(_db.ind_srcfile_buckets_elems, old_size);
2057        _db.ind_srcfile_buckets_elems = new_buckets;
2058        _db.ind_srcfile_buckets_n = new_nbuckets;
2059    }
2060}

2062// --- abt.FDb.cfg.Alloc
2063// Allocate memory for new default row.
2064// If out of memory, process is killed.
2065abt::FCfg& abt::cfg_Alloc() {
2066    abt::FCfg* row = cfg_AllocMaybe();
2067    if (UNLIKELY(row == NULL)) {
2068        FatalErrorExit("abt.out_of_mem  field:abt.FDb.cfg  comment:'Alloc failed'");
2069    }
2070    return *row;
2071}
2072
2073// --- abt.FDb.cfg.AllocMaybe
2074// Allocate memory for new element. If out of memory, return NULL.
2075abt::FCfg* abt::cfg_AllocMaybe() {
2076    abt::FCfg *row = (abt::FCfg*)cfg_AllocMem();
2077    if (row) {
2078        new (row) abt::FCfg; // call constructor
2079    }
2080    return row;
2081}
2082
2083// --- abt.FDb.cfg.InsertMaybe
2084// Create new row from struct.
2085// Return pointer to new element, or NULL if insertion failed (due to out-of-memory, duplicate key, etc)
2086abt::FCfg* abt::cfg_InsertMaybe(const dev::Cfg &value) {
2087    abt::FCfg *row = &cfg_Alloc(); // if out of memory, process dies. if input error, return NULL.
2088    cfg_CopyIn(*row,const_cast<dev::Cfg&>(value));
2089    bool ok = cfg_XrefMaybe(*row); // this may return false
2090    if (!ok) {
2091        cfg_RemoveLast(); // delete offending row, any existing xrefs are cleared
2092        row = NULL; // forget this ever happened
2093    }
2094    return row;
2095}
2096
2097// --- abt.FDb.cfg.AllocMem
2098// Allocate space for one element. If no memory available, return NULL.
2099void* abt::cfg_AllocMem() {
2100    u64 new_nelems     = _db.cfg_n+1;
2101    // compute level and index on level
2102    u64 bsr   = algo::u64_BitScanReverse(new_nelems);
2103    u64 base  = u64(1)<<bsr;
2104    u64 index = new_nelems-base;
2105    void *ret = NULL;
2106    // if level doesn't exist yet, create it
2107    abt::FCfg*  lev   = NULL;
2108    if (bsr < 32) {
2109        lev = _db.cfg_lary[bsr];
2110        if (!lev) {
2111            lev=(abt::FCfg*)abt::lpool_AllocMem(sizeof(abt::FCfg) * (u64(1)<<bsr));
2112            _db.cfg_lary[bsr] = lev;
2113        }
2114    }
2115    // allocate element from this level
2116    if (lev) {
2117        _db.cfg_n = i32(new_nelems);
2118        ret = lev + index;
2119    }
2120    return ret;
2121}
2122
2123// --- abt.FDb.cfg.RemoveLast
2124// Delete last element of array. Do nothing if array is empty.
2125void abt::cfg_RemoveLast() {
2126    u64 n = _db.cfg_n;
2127    if (n > 0) {
2128        n -= 1;
2129        cfg_qFind(u64(n)).~FCfg();
2130        _db.cfg_n = i32(n);
2131    }
2132}
2133
2134// --- abt.FDb.cfg.InputMaybe
2135static bool abt::cfg_InputMaybe(dev::Cfg &elem) {
2136    bool retval = true;
2137    retval = cfg_InsertMaybe(elem) != nullptr;
2138    return retval;
2139}
2140
2141// --- abt.FDb.cfg.XrefMaybe
2142// Insert row into all appropriate indices. If error occurs, store error
2143// in algo_lib::_db.errtext and return false. Caller must Delete or Unref such row.
2144bool abt::cfg_XrefMaybe(abt::FCfg &row) {
2145    bool retval = true;
2146    (void)row;
2147    // insert cfg into index ind_cfg
2148    if (true) { // user-defined insert condition
2149        bool success = ind_cfg_InsertMaybe(row);
2150        if (UNLIKELY(!success)) {
2151            ch_RemoveAll(algo_lib::_db.errtext);
2152            algo_lib::_db.errtext << "abt.duplicate_key  xref:abt.FDb.ind_cfg"; // check for duplicate key
2153            return false;
2154        }
2155    }
2156    return retval;
2157}
2158
2159// --- abt.FDb.ind_cfg.Find
2160// Find row by key. Return NULL if not found.
2161abt::FCfg* abt::ind_cfg_Find(const algo::strptr& key) {
2162    u32 index = algo::Smallstr50_Hash(0, key) & (_db.ind_cfg_buckets_n - 1);
2163    abt::FCfg* *e = &_db.ind_cfg_buckets_elems[index];
2164    abt::FCfg* ret=NULL;
2165    do {
2166        ret       = *e;
2167        bool done = !ret || (*ret).cfg == key;
2168        if (done) break;
2169        e         = &ret->ind_cfg_next;
2170    } while (true);
2171    return ret;
2172}
2173
2174// --- abt.FDb.ind_cfg.GetOrCreate
2175// Find row by key. If not found, create and x-reference a new row with with this key.
2176abt::FCfg& abt::ind_cfg_GetOrCreate(const algo::strptr& key) {
2177    abt::FCfg* ret = ind_cfg_Find(key);
2178    if (!ret) { //  if memory alloc fails, process dies; if insert fails, function returns NULL.
2179        ret         = &cfg_Alloc();
2180        (*ret).cfg = key;
2181        bool good = cfg_XrefMaybe(*ret);
2182        if (!good) {
2183            cfg_RemoveLast(); // delete offending row, any existing xrefs are cleared
2184            ret = NULL;
2185        }
2186    }
2187    vrfy(ret, tempstr() << "abt.create_error  table:ind_cfg  key:'"<<key<<"'  comment:'bad xref'");
2188    return *ret;
2189}
2190
2191// --- abt.FDb.ind_cfg.InsertMaybe
2192// Insert row into hash table. Return true if row is reachable through the hash after the function completes.
2193bool abt::ind_cfg_InsertMaybe(abt::FCfg& row) {
2194    ind_cfg_Reserve(1);
2195    bool retval = true; // if already in hash, InsertMaybe returns true
2196    if (LIKELY(row.ind_cfg_next == (abt::FCfg*)-1)) {// check if in hash already
2197        u32 index = algo::Smallstr50_Hash(0, row.cfg) & (_db.ind_cfg_buckets_n - 1);
2198        abt::FCfg* *prev = &_db.ind_cfg_buckets_elems[index];
2199        do {
2200            abt::FCfg* ret = *prev;
2201            if (!ret) { // exit condition 1: reached the end of the list
2202                break;
2203            }
2204            if ((*ret).cfg == row.cfg) { // exit condition 2: found matching key
2205                retval = false;
2206                break;
2207            }
2208            prev = &ret->ind_cfg_next;
2209        } while (true);
2210        if (retval) {
2211            row.ind_cfg_next = *prev;
2212            _db.ind_cfg_n++;
2213            *prev = &row;
2214        }
2215    }
2216    return retval;
2217}
2218
2219// --- abt.FDb.ind_cfg.Remove
2220// Remove reference to element from hash index. If element is not in hash, do nothing
2221void abt::ind_cfg_Remove(abt::FCfg& row) {
2222    if (LIKELY(row.ind_cfg_next != (abt::FCfg*)-1)) {// check if in hash already
2223        u32 index = algo::Smallstr50_Hash(0, row.cfg) & (_db.ind_cfg_buckets_n - 1);
2224        abt::FCfg* *prev = &_db.ind_cfg_buckets_elems[index]; // addr of pointer to current element
2225        while (abt::FCfg *next = *prev) {                          // scan the collision chain for our element
2226            if (next == &row) {        // found it?
2227                *prev = next->ind_cfg_next; // unlink (singly linked list)
2228                _db.ind_cfg_n--;
2229                row.ind_cfg_next = (abt::FCfg*)-1;// not-in-hash
2230                break;
2231            }
2232            prev = &next->ind_cfg_next;
2233        }
2234    }
2235}

2237// --- abt.FDb.ind_cfg.Reserve
2238// Reserve enough room in the hash for N more elements. Return success code.
2239void abt::ind_cfg_Reserve(int n) {
2240    u32 old_nbuckets = _db.ind_cfg_buckets_n;
2241    u32 new_nelems   = _db.ind_cfg_n + n;
2242    // # of elements has to be roughly equal to the number of buckets
2243    if (new_nelems > old_nbuckets) {
2244        int new_nbuckets = i32_Max(algo::BumpToPow2(new_nelems), u32(4));
2245        u32 old_size = old_nbuckets * sizeof(abt::FCfg*);
2246        u32 new_size = new_nbuckets * sizeof(abt::FCfg*);
2247        // allocate new array. we don't use Realloc since copying is not needed and factor of 2 probably
2248        // means new memory will have to be allocated anyway
2249        abt::FCfg* *new_buckets = (abt::FCfg**)abt::lpool_AllocMem(new_size);
2250        if (UNLIKELY(!new_buckets)) {
2251            FatalErrorExit("abt.out_of_memory  field:abt.FDb.ind_cfg");
2252        }
2253        memset(new_buckets, 0, new_size); // clear pointers
2254        // rehash all entries
2255        for (int i = 0; i < _db.ind_cfg_buckets_n; i++) {
2256            abt::FCfg* elem = _db.ind_cfg_buckets_elems[i];
2257            while (elem) {
2258                abt::FCfg &row        = *elem;
2259                abt::FCfg* next       = row.ind_cfg_next;
2260                u32 index          = algo::Smallstr50_Hash(0, row.cfg) & (new_nbuckets-1);
2261                row.ind_cfg_next     = new_buckets[index];
2262                new_buckets[index] = &row;
2263                elem               = next;
2264            }
2265        }
2266        // free old array
2267        abt::lpool_FreeMem(_db.ind_cfg_buckets_elems, old_size);
2268        _db.ind_cfg_buckets_elems = new_buckets;
2269        _db.ind_cfg_buckets_n = new_nbuckets;
2270    }
2271}

2370// --- abt.FDb.ind_uname.Find
2371// Find row by key. Return NULL if not found.
2372abt::FUname* abt::ind_uname_Find(const algo::strptr& key) {
2373    u32 index = algo::Smallstr50_Hash(0, key) & (_db.ind_uname_buckets_n - 1);
2374    abt::FUname* *e = &_db.ind_uname_buckets_elems[index];
2375    abt::FUname* ret=NULL;
2376    do {
2377        ret       = *e;
2378        bool done = !ret || (*ret).uname == key;
2379        if (done) break;
2380        e         = &ret->ind_uname_next;
2381    } while (true);
2382    return ret;

2385// --- abt.FDb.ind_uname.GetOrCreate
2386// Find row by key. If not found, create and x-reference a new row with with this key.
2387abt::FUname& abt::ind_uname_GetOrCreate(const algo::strptr& key) {
2388    abt::FUname* ret = ind_uname_Find(key);
2389    if (!ret) { //  if memory alloc fails, process dies; if insert fails, function returns NULL.
2390        ret         = &uname_Alloc();
2391        (*ret).uname = key;
2392        bool good = uname_XrefMaybe(*ret);
2393        if (!good) {
2394            uname_RemoveLast(); // delete offending row, any existing xrefs are cleared
2395            ret = NULL;
2396        }
2397    }
2398    vrfy(ret, tempstr() << "abt.create_error  table:ind_uname  key:'"<<key<<"'  comment:'bad xref'");
2399    return *ret;
2400}

2402// --- abt.FDb.ind_uname.InsertMaybe
2403// Insert row into hash table. Return true if row is reachable through the hash after the function completes.
2404bool abt::ind_uname_InsertMaybe(abt::FUname& row) {
2405    ind_uname_Reserve(1);
2406    bool retval = true; // if already in hash, InsertMaybe returns true
2407    if (LIKELY(row.ind_uname_next == (abt::FUname*)-1)) {// check if in hash already
2408        u32 index = algo::Smallstr50_Hash(0, row.uname) & (_db.ind_uname_buckets_n - 1);
2409        abt::FUname* *prev = &_db.ind_uname_buckets_elems[index];
2410        do {
2411            abt::FUname* ret = *prev;
2412            if (!ret) { // exit condition 1: reached the end of the list
2413                break;
2414            }
2415            if ((*ret).uname == row.uname) { // exit condition 2: found matching key
2416                retval = false;
2417                break;
2418            }
2419            prev = &ret->ind_uname_next;
2420        } while (true);
2421        if (retval) {
2422            row.ind_uname_next = *prev;
2423            _db.ind_uname_n++;
2424            *prev = &row;
2425        }
2426    }
2427    return retval;
2428}

2432void abt::ind_uname_Remove(abt::FUname& row) {

2435        abt::FUname* *prev = &_db.ind_uname_buckets_elems[index]; // addr of pointer to current element
2436        while (abt::FUname *next = *prev) {                          // scan the collision chain for our element
2437            if (next == &row) {        // found it?
2438                *prev = next->ind_uname_next; // unlink (singly linked list)
2439                _db.ind_uname_n--;
2440                row.ind_uname_next = (abt::FUname*)-1;// not-in-hash
2441                break;
2442            }
2443            prev = &next->ind_uname_next;
2444        }
2445    }
2446}
