2448// --- abt.FDb.ind_uname.Reserve
2449// Reserve enough room in the hash for N more elements. Return success code.
2450void abt::ind_uname_Reserve(int n) {
2451    u32 old_nbuckets = _db.ind_uname_buckets_n;
2452    u32 new_nelems   = _db.ind_uname_n + n;
2453    // # of elements has to be roughly equal to the number of buckets
2454    if (new_nelems > old_nbuckets) {
2455        int new_nbuckets = i32_Max(algo::BumpToPow2(new_nelems), u32(4));
2456        u32 old_size = old_nbuckets * sizeof(abt::FUname*);
2457        u32 new_size = new_nbuckets * sizeof(abt::FUname*);
2458        // allocate new array. we don't use Realloc since copying is not needed and factor of 2 probably
2459        // means new memory will have to be allocated anyway
2460        abt::FUname* *new_buckets = (abt::FUname**)abt::lpool_AllocMem(new_size);
2461        if (UNLIKELY(!new_buckets)) {
2462            FatalErrorExit("abt.out_of_memory  field:abt.FDb.ind_uname");
2463        }
2464        memset(new_buckets, 0, new_size); // clear pointers
2465        // rehash all entries
2466        for (int i = 0; i < _db.ind_uname_buckets_n; i++) {
2467            abt::FUname* elem = _db.ind_uname_buckets_elems[i];
2468            while (elem) {
2469                abt::FUname &row        = *elem;
2470                abt::FUname* next       = row.ind_uname_next;
2471                u32 index          = algo::Smallstr50_Hash(0, row.uname) & (new_nbuckets-1);
2472                row.ind_uname_next     = new_buckets[index];
2473                new_buckets[index] = &row;
2474                elem               = next;
2475            }
2476        }
2477        // free old array
2478        abt::lpool_FreeMem(_db.ind_uname_buckets_elems, old_size);
2479        _db.ind_uname_buckets_elems = new_buckets;
2480        _db.ind_uname_buckets_n = new_nbuckets;
2481    }
2482}

2506// Create new row from struct.
2507// Return pointer to new element, or NULL if insertion failed (due to out-of-memory, duplicate key, etc)
2508abt::FCompiler* abt::compiler_InsertMaybe(const dev::Compiler &value) {
2509    abt::FCompiler *row = &compiler_Alloc(); // if out of memory, process dies. if input error, return NULL.
2510    compiler_CopyIn(*row,const_cast<dev::Compiler&>(value));
2511    bool ok = compiler_XrefMaybe(*row); // this may return false
2512    if (!ok) {
2513        compiler_RemoveLast(); // delete offending row, any existing xrefs are cleared
2514        row = NULL; // forget this ever happened
2515    }
2516    return row;
2517}
2518
2519// --- abt.FDb.compiler.AllocMem
2520// Allocate space for one element. If no memory available, return NULL.
2521void* abt::compiler_AllocMem() {
2522    u64 new_nelems     = _db.compiler_n+1;
2523    // compute level and index on level
2524    u64 bsr   = algo::u64_BitScanReverse(new_nelems);
2525    u64 base  = u64(1)<<bsr;
2526    u64 index = new_nelems-base;
2527    void *ret = NULL;
2528    // if level doesn't exist yet, create it
2529    abt::FCompiler*  lev   = NULL;
2530    if (bsr < 32) {
2531        lev = _db.compiler_lary[bsr];
2532        if (!lev) {
2533            lev=(abt::FCompiler*)abt::lpool_AllocMem(sizeof(abt::FCompiler) * (u64(1)<<bsr));
2534            _db.compiler_lary[bsr] = lev;
2535        }
2536    }
2537    // allocate element from this level
2538    if (lev) {
2539        _db.compiler_n = i32(new_nelems);
2540        ret = lev + index;
2541    }
2542    return ret;
2543}
2544
2545// --- abt.FDb.compiler.RemoveLast
2546// Delete last element of array. Do nothing if array is empty.
2547void abt::compiler_RemoveLast() {
2548    u64 n = _db.compiler_n;
2549    if (n > 0) {
2550        n -= 1;
2551        compiler_qFind(u64(n)).~FCompiler();
2552        _db.compiler_n = i32(n);
2553    }
2554}
2555
2556// --- abt.FDb.compiler.InputMaybe
2557static bool abt::compiler_InputMaybe(dev::Compiler &elem) {
2558    bool retval = true;
2559    retval = compiler_InsertMaybe(elem) != nullptr;
2560    return retval;
2561}
2562
2563// --- abt.FDb.compiler.XrefMaybe
2564// Insert row into all appropriate indices. If error occurs, store error
2565// in algo_lib::_db.errtext and return false. Caller must Delete or Unref such row.
2566bool abt::compiler_XrefMaybe(abt::FCompiler &row) {
2567    bool retval = true;
2568    (void)row;
2569    // insert compiler into index ind_compiler
2570    if (true) { // user-defined insert condition
2571        bool success = ind_compiler_InsertMaybe(row);
2572        if (UNLIKELY(!success)) {
2573            ch_RemoveAll(algo_lib::_db.errtext);
2574            algo_lib::_db.errtext << "abt.duplicate_key  xref:abt.FDb.ind_compiler"; // check for duplicate key
2575            return false;
2576        }
2577    }
2578    return retval;
2579}
2580
2581// --- abt.FDb.ind_compiler.Find
2582// Find row by key. Return NULL if not found.
2583abt::FCompiler* abt::ind_compiler_Find(const algo::strptr& key) {
2584    u32 index = algo::Smallstr50_Hash(0, key) & (_db.ind_compiler_buckets_n - 1);
2585    abt::FCompiler* *e = &_db.ind_compiler_buckets_elems[index];
2586    abt::FCompiler* ret=NULL;
2587    do {
2588        ret       = *e;
2589        bool done = !ret || (*ret).compiler == key;
2590        if (done) break;
2591        e         = &ret->ind_compiler_next;
2592    } while (true);
2593    return ret;
2594}
2595
2596// --- abt.FDb.ind_compiler.GetOrCreate
2597// Find row by key. If not found, create and x-reference a new row with with this key.
2598abt::FCompiler& abt::ind_compiler_GetOrCreate(const algo::strptr& key) {
2599    abt::FCompiler* ret = ind_compiler_Find(key);
2600    if (!ret) { //  if memory alloc fails, process dies; if insert fails, function returns NULL.
2601        ret         = &compiler_Alloc();
2602        (*ret).compiler = key;
2603        bool good = compiler_XrefMaybe(*ret);
2604        if (!good) {
2605            compiler_RemoveLast(); // delete offending row, any existing xrefs are cleared
2606            ret = NULL;
2607        }
2608    }
2609    vrfy(ret, tempstr() << "abt.create_error  table:ind_compiler  key:'"<<key<<"'  comment:'bad xref'");
2610    return *ret;
2611}
2612
2613// --- abt.FDb.ind_compiler.InsertMaybe
2614// Insert row into hash table. Return true if row is reachable through the hash after the function completes.
2615bool abt::ind_compiler_InsertMaybe(abt::FCompiler& row) {
2616    ind_compiler_Reserve(1);
2617    bool retval = true; // if already in hash, InsertMaybe returns true
2618    if (LIKELY(row.ind_compiler_next == (abt::FCompiler*)-1)) {// check if in hash already
2619        u32 index = algo::Smallstr50_Hash(0, row.compiler) & (_db.ind_compiler_buckets_n - 1);
2620        abt::FCompiler* *prev = &_db.ind_compiler_buckets_elems[index];
2621        do {
2622            abt::FCompiler* ret = *prev;
2623            if (!ret) { // exit condition 1: reached the end of the list
2624                break;
2625            }
2626            if ((*ret).compiler == row.compiler) { // exit condition 2: found matching key
2627                retval = false;
2628                break;
2629            }
2630            prev = &ret->ind_compiler_next;
2631        } while (true);
2632        if (retval) {
2633            row.ind_compiler_next = *prev;
2634            _db.ind_compiler_n++;
2635            *prev = &row;
2636        }
2637    }
2638    return retval;
2639}
2640
2641// --- abt.FDb.ind_compiler.Remove
2642// Remove reference to element from hash index. If element is not in hash, do nothing
2643void abt::ind_compiler_Remove(abt::FCompiler& row) {
2644    if (LIKELY(row.ind_compiler_next != (abt::FCompiler*)-1)) {// check if in hash already
2645        u32 index = algo::Smallstr50_Hash(0, row.compiler) & (_db.ind_compiler_buckets_n - 1);
2646        abt::FCompiler* *prev = &_db.ind_compiler_buckets_elems[index]; // addr of pointer to current element
2647        while (abt::FCompiler *next = *prev) {                          // scan the collision chain for our element
2648            if (next == &row) {        // found it?
2649                *prev = next->ind_compiler_next; // unlink (singly linked list)
2650                _db.ind_compiler_n--;
2651                row.ind_compiler_next = (abt::FCompiler*)-1;// not-in-hash
2652                break;
2653            }
2654            prev = &next->ind_compiler_next;
2655        }
2656    }
2657}
2658
2659// --- abt.FDb.ind_compiler.Reserve
2660// Reserve enough room in the hash for N more elements. Return success code.
2661void abt::ind_compiler_Reserve(int n) {
2662    u32 old_nbuckets = _db.ind_compiler_buckets_n;
2663    u32 new_nelems   = _db.ind_compiler_n + n;
2664    // # of elements has to be roughly equal to the number of buckets
2665    if (new_nelems > old_nbuckets) {
2666        int new_nbuckets = i32_Max(algo::BumpToPow2(new_nelems), u32(4));
2667        u32 old_size = old_nbuckets * sizeof(abt::FCompiler*);
2668        u32 new_size = new_nbuckets * sizeof(abt::FCompiler*);
2669        // allocate new array. we don't use Realloc since copying is not needed and factor of 2 probably
2670        // means new memory will have to be allocated anyway
2671        abt::FCompiler* *new_buckets = (abt::FCompiler**)abt::lpool_AllocMem(new_size);
2672        if (UNLIKELY(!new_buckets)) {
2673            FatalErrorExit("abt.out_of_memory  field:abt.FDb.ind_compiler");
2674        }
2675        memset(new_buckets, 0, new_size); // clear pointers
2676        // rehash all entries
2677        for (int i = 0; i < _db.ind_compiler_buckets_n; i++) {
2678            abt::FCompiler* elem = _db.ind_compiler_buckets_elems[i];
2679            while (elem) {
2680                abt::FCompiler &row        = *elem;
2681                abt::FCompiler* next       = row.ind_compiler_next;
2682                u32 index          = algo::Smallstr50_Hash(0, row.compiler) & (new_nbuckets-1);
2683                row.ind_compiler_next     = new_buckets[index];
2684                new_buckets[index] = &row;
2685                elem               = next;
2686            }
2687        }
2688        // free old array
2689        abt::lpool_FreeMem(_db.ind_compiler_buckets_elems, old_size);
2690        _db.ind_compiler_buckets_elems = new_buckets;
2691        _db.ind_compiler_buckets_n = new_nbuckets;
2692    }
2693}

2695// --- abt.FDb.arch.Alloc
2696// Allocate memory for new default row.
2697// If out of memory, process is killed.
2698abt::FArch& abt::arch_Alloc() {
2699    abt::FArch* row = arch_AllocMaybe();
2700    if (UNLIKELY(row == NULL)) {
2701        FatalErrorExit("abt.out_of_mem  field:abt.FDb.arch  comment:'Alloc failed'");
2702    }
2703    return *row;
2704}
2705
2706// --- abt.FDb.arch.AllocMaybe
2707// Allocate memory for new element. If out of memory, return NULL.
2708abt::FArch* abt::arch_AllocMaybe() {
2709    abt::FArch *row = (abt::FArch*)arch_AllocMem();
2710    if (row) {
2711        new (row) abt::FArch; // call constructor
2712    }
2713    return row;
2714}

2716// --- abt.FDb.arch.InsertMaybe
2717// Create new row from struct.
2718// Return pointer to new element, or NULL if insertion failed (due to out-of-memory, duplicate key, etc)
2719abt::FArch* abt::arch_InsertMaybe(const dev::Arch &value) {
2720    abt::FArch *row = &arch_Alloc(); // if out of memory, process dies. if input error, return NULL.
2721    arch_CopyIn(*row,const_cast<dev::Arch&>(value));
2722    bool ok = arch_XrefMaybe(*row); // this may return false
2723    if (!ok) {
2724        arch_RemoveLast(); // delete offending row, any existing xrefs are cleared
2725        row = NULL; // forget this ever happened
2726    }
2727    return row;
2728}

2730// --- abt.FDb.arch.AllocMem
2731// Allocate space for one element. If no memory available, return NULL.
2732void* abt::arch_AllocMem() {
2733    u64 new_nelems     = _db.arch_n+1;
2734    // compute level and index on level
2735    u64 bsr   = algo::u64_BitScanReverse(new_nelems);
2736    u64 base  = u64(1)<<bsr;
2737    u64 index = new_nelems-base;
2738    void *ret = NULL;
2739    // if level doesn't exist yet, create it
2740    abt::FArch*  lev   = NULL;
2741    if (bsr < 32) {
2742        lev = _db.arch_lary[bsr];
2743        if (!lev) {
2744            lev=(abt::FArch*)abt::lpool_AllocMem(sizeof(abt::FArch) * (u64(1)<<bsr));
2745            _db.arch_lary[bsr] = lev;
2746        }
2747    }
2748    // allocate element from this level
2749    if (lev) {
2750        _db.arch_n = i32(new_nelems);
2751        ret = lev + index;
2752    }
2753    return ret;
2754}

2756// --- abt.FDb.arch.RemoveLast
2757// Delete last element of array. Do nothing if array is empty.
2758void abt::arch_RemoveLast() {
2759    u64 n = _db.arch_n;
2760    if (n > 0) {
2761        n -= 1;
2762        arch_qFind(u64(n)).~FArch();
2763        _db.arch_n = i32(n);
2764    }
2765}

2774// --- abt.FDb.arch.XrefMaybe
2775// Insert row into all appropriate indices. If error occurs, store error
2776// in algo_lib::_db.errtext and return false. Caller must Delete or Unref such row.
2777bool abt::arch_XrefMaybe(abt::FArch &row) {
2778    bool retval = true;
2779    (void)row;
2780    // insert arch into index ind_arch
2781    if (true) { // user-defined insert condition
2782        bool success = ind_arch_InsertMaybe(row);
2783        if (UNLIKELY(!success)) {
2784            ch_RemoveAll(algo_lib::_db.errtext);
2785            algo_lib::_db.errtext << "abt.duplicate_key  xref:abt.FDb.ind_arch"; // check for duplicate key
2786            return false;
2787        }
2788    }
2789    return retval;
2790}

2792// --- abt.FDb.ind_arch.Find
2793// Find row by key. Return NULL if not found.
2794abt::FArch* abt::ind_arch_Find(const algo::strptr& key) {
2795    u32 index = algo::Smallstr50_Hash(0, key) & (_db.ind_arch_buckets_n - 1);
2796    abt::FArch* *e = &_db.ind_arch_buckets_elems[index];
2797    abt::FArch* ret=NULL;
2798    do {
2799        ret       = *e;
2800        bool done = !ret || (*ret).arch == key;
2801        if (done) break;
2802        e         = &ret->ind_arch_next;
2803    } while (true);
2804    return ret;
2805}

2807// --- abt.FDb.ind_arch.GetOrCreate
2808// Find row by key. If not found, create and x-reference a new row with with this key.
2809abt::FArch& abt::ind_arch_GetOrCreate(const algo::strptr& key) {
2810    abt::FArch* ret = ind_arch_Find(key);
2811    if (!ret) { //  if memory alloc fails, process dies; if insert fails, function returns NULL.
2812        ret         = &arch_Alloc();
2813        (*ret).arch = key;
2814        bool good = arch_XrefMaybe(*ret);
2815        if (!good) {
2816            arch_RemoveLast(); // delete offending row, any existing xrefs are cleared
2817            ret = NULL;
2818        }
2819    }
2820    vrfy(ret, tempstr() << "abt.create_error  table:ind_arch  key:'"<<key<<"'  comment:'bad xref'");
2821    return *ret;
2822}

2824// --- abt.FDb.ind_arch.InsertMaybe
2825// Insert row into hash table. Return true if row is reachable through the hash after the function completes.
2826bool abt::ind_arch_InsertMaybe(abt::FArch& row) {
2827    ind_arch_Reserve(1);
2828    bool retval = true; // if already in hash, InsertMaybe returns true
2829    if (LIKELY(row.ind_arch_next == (abt::FArch*)-1)) {// check if in hash already
2830        u32 index = algo::Smallstr50_Hash(0, row.arch) & (_db.ind_arch_buckets_n - 1);
2831        abt::FArch* *prev = &_db.ind_arch_buckets_elems[index];
2832        do {
2833            abt::FArch* ret = *prev;
2834            if (!ret) { // exit condition 1: reached the end of the list
2835                break;
2836            }
2837            if ((*ret).arch == row.arch) { // exit condition 2: found matching key
2838                retval = false;
2839                break;
2840            }
2841            prev = &ret->ind_arch_next;
2842        } while (true);
2843        if (retval) {
2844            row.ind_arch_next = *prev;
2845            _db.ind_arch_n++;
2846            *prev = &row;
2847        }
2848    }
2849    return retval;
2850}

2852// --- abt.FDb.ind_arch.Remove
2853// Remove reference to element from hash index. If element is not in hash, do nothing
2854void abt::ind_arch_Remove(abt::FArch& row) {
2855    if (LIKELY(row.ind_arch_next != (abt::FArch*)-1)) {// check if in hash already
2856        u32 index = algo::Smallstr50_Hash(0, row.arch) & (_db.ind_arch_buckets_n - 1);
2857        abt::FArch* *prev = &_db.ind_arch_buckets_elems[index]; // addr of pointer to current element
2858        while (abt::FArch *next = *prev) {                          // scan the collision chain for our element
2859            if (next == &row) {        // found it?
2860                *prev = next->ind_arch_next; // unlink (singly linked list)
2861                _db.ind_arch_n--;
2862                row.ind_arch_next = (abt::FArch*)-1;// not-in-hash
2863                break;
2864            }
2865            prev = &next->ind_arch_next;
2866        }
2867    }
2868}
2869
2870// --- abt.FDb.ind_arch.Reserve
2871// Reserve enough room in the hash for N more elements. Return success code.
2872void abt::ind_arch_Reserve(int n) {
2873    u32 old_nbuckets = _db.ind_arch_buckets_n;
2874    u32 new_nelems   = _db.ind_arch_n + n;
2875    // # of elements has to be roughly equal to the number of buckets
2876    if (new_nelems > old_nbuckets) {
2877        int new_nbuckets = i32_Max(algo::BumpToPow2(new_nelems), u32(4));
2878        u32 old_size = old_nbuckets * sizeof(abt::FArch*);
2879        u32 new_size = new_nbuckets * sizeof(abt::FArch*);
2880        // allocate new array. we don't use Realloc since copying is not needed and factor of 2 probably
2881        // means new memory will have to be allocated anyway
2882        abt::FArch* *new_buckets = (abt::FArch**)abt::lpool_AllocMem(new_size);
2883        if (UNLIKELY(!new_buckets)) {
2884            FatalErrorExit("abt.out_of_memory  field:abt.FDb.ind_arch");
2885        }
2886        memset(new_buckets, 0, new_size); // clear pointers
2887        // rehash all entries
2888        for (int i = 0; i < _db.ind_arch_buckets_n; i++) {
2889            abt::FArch* elem = _db.ind_arch_buckets_elems[i];
2890            while (elem) {
2891                abt::FArch &row        = *elem;
2892                abt::FArch* next       = row.ind_arch_next;
2893                u32 index          = algo::Smallstr50_Hash(0, row.arch) & (new_nbuckets-1);
2894                row.ind_arch_next     = new_buckets[index];
2895                new_buckets[index] = &row;
2896                elem               = next;
2897            }
2898        }
2899        // free old array
2900        abt::lpool_FreeMem(_db.ind_arch_buckets_elems, old_size);
2901        _db.ind_arch_buckets_elems = new_buckets;
2902        _db.ind_arch_buckets_n = new_nbuckets;
2903    }
2904}
2905
2906// --- abt.FDb.bh_syscmd.Dealloc
2907// Remove all elements from heap and free memory used by the array.
2908void abt::bh_syscmd_Dealloc() {
2909    bh_syscmd_RemoveAll();
2910    abt::lpool_FreeMem(_db.bh_syscmd_elems, sizeof(abt::FSyscmd*)*_db.bh_syscmd_max);
2911    _db.bh_syscmd_max   = 0;
2912    _db.bh_syscmd_elems = NULL;
2913}
2914
2915// --- abt.FDb.bh_syscmd.Downheap
2916// Find new location for ROW starting at IDX
2917// NOTE: Rest of heap is rearranged, but pointer to ROW is NOT stored in array.
2918static int abt::bh_syscmd_Downheap(abt::FSyscmd& row, int idx) {
2919    abt::FSyscmd* *elems = _db.bh_syscmd_elems;
2920    int n = _db.bh_syscmd_n;
2921    int child = idx*2+1;
2922    while (child < n) {
2923        abt::FSyscmd* p = elems[child]; // left child
2924        int rchild = child+1;
2925        if (rchild < n) {
2926            abt::FSyscmd* q = elems[rchild]; // right child
2927            if (bh_syscmd_ElemLt(*q,*p)) {
2928                child = rchild;
2929                p     = q;
2930            }
2931        }
2932        if (!bh_syscmd_ElemLt(*p,row)) {
2933            break;
2934        }
2935        p->bh_syscmd_idx   = idx;
2936        elems[idx]     = p;
2937        idx            = child;
2938        child          = idx*2+1;
2939    }
2940    return idx;
2941}
2942
2943// --- abt.FDb.bh_syscmd.Insert
2944// Insert row. Row must not already be in index. If row is already in index, do nothing.
2945void abt::bh_syscmd_Insert(abt::FSyscmd& row) {
2946    if (LIKELY(row.bh_syscmd_idx == -1)) {
2947        bh_syscmd_Reserve(1);
2948        int n = _db.bh_syscmd_n;
2949        _db.bh_syscmd_n = n + 1;
2950        int new_idx = bh_syscmd_Upheap(row, n);
2951        row.bh_syscmd_idx = new_idx;
2952        _db.bh_syscmd_elems[new_idx] = &row;
2953    }
2954}
2955
2956// --- abt.FDb.bh_syscmd.Reheap
2957// If row is in heap, update its position. If row is not in heap, insert it.
2958// Return new position of item in the heap (0=top)
2959i32 abt::bh_syscmd_Reheap(abt::FSyscmd& row) {
2960    int old_idx = row.bh_syscmd_idx;
2961    bool isnew = old_idx == -1;
2962    if (isnew) {
2963        bh_syscmd_Reserve(1);
2964        old_idx = _db.bh_syscmd_n++;
2965    }
2966    int new_idx = bh_syscmd_Upheap(row, old_idx);
2967    if (!isnew && new_idx == old_idx) {
2968        new_idx = bh_syscmd_Downheap(row, old_idx);
2969    }
2970    row.bh_syscmd_idx = new_idx;
2971    _db.bh_syscmd_elems[new_idx] = &row;
2972    return new_idx;
2973}
2974
2975// --- abt.FDb.bh_syscmd.ReheapFirst
2976// Key of first element in the heap changed. Move it.
2977// This function does not check the insert condition.
2978// Return new position of item in the heap (0=top).
2979// Heap must be non-empty or behavior is undefined.
2980i32 abt::bh_syscmd_ReheapFirst() {
2981    abt::FSyscmd &row = *_db.bh_syscmd_elems[0];
2982    i32 new_idx = bh_syscmd_Downheap(row, 0);
2983    row.bh_syscmd_idx = new_idx;
2984    _db.bh_syscmd_elems[new_idx] = &row;
2985    return new_idx;
2986}
2987
2988// --- abt.FDb.bh_syscmd.Remove
2989// Remove element from index. If element is not in index, do nothing.
2990void abt::bh_syscmd_Remove(abt::FSyscmd& row) {
2991    if (bh_syscmd_InBheapQ(row)) {
2992        int old_idx = row.bh_syscmd_idx;
2993        if (_db.bh_syscmd_elems[old_idx] == &row) { // sanity check: heap points back to row
2994            row.bh_syscmd_idx = -1;           // mark not in heap
2995            i32 n = _db.bh_syscmd_n - 1; // index of last element in heap
2996            _db.bh_syscmd_n = n;         // decrease count
2997            if (old_idx != n) {
2998                abt::FSyscmd *elem = _db.bh_syscmd_elems[n];
2999                int new_idx = bh_syscmd_Upheap(*elem, old_idx);
3000                if (new_idx == old_idx) {
3001                    new_idx = bh_syscmd_Downheap(*elem, old_idx);
3002                }
3003                elem->bh_syscmd_idx = new_idx;
3004                _db.bh_syscmd_elems[new_idx] = elem;
3005            }
3006        }
3007    }
3008}
3009
3010// --- abt.FDb.bh_syscmd.RemoveAll
3011// Remove all elements from binary heap
3012void abt::bh_syscmd_RemoveAll() {
3013    int n = _db.bh_syscmd_n;
3014    for (int i = n - 1; i>=0; i--) {
3015        _db.bh_syscmd_elems[i]->bh_syscmd_idx = -1; // mark not-in-heap
3016    }
3017    _db.bh_syscmd_n = 0;
3018}
3019
3020// --- abt.FDb.bh_syscmd.RemoveFirst
3021// If index is empty, return NULL. Otherwise remove and return first key in index.
3022//  Call 'head changed' trigger.
3023abt::FSyscmd* abt::bh_syscmd_RemoveFirst() {
3024    abt::FSyscmd *row = NULL;
3025    if (_db.bh_syscmd_n > 0) {
3026        row = _db.bh_syscmd_elems[0];
3027        row->bh_syscmd_idx = -1;           // mark not in heap
3028        i32 n = _db.bh_syscmd_n - 1; // index of last element in heap
3029        _db.bh_syscmd_n = n;         // decrease count
3030        if (n) {
3031            abt::FSyscmd &elem = *_db.bh_syscmd_elems[n];
3032            int new_idx = bh_syscmd_Downheap(elem, 0);
3033            elem.bh_syscmd_idx = new_idx;
3034            _db.bh_syscmd_elems[new_idx] = &elem;
3035        }
3036    }
3037    return row;
3038}
3039
3040// --- abt.FDb.bh_syscmd.Reserve
3041// Reserve space in index for N more elements
3042void abt::bh_syscmd_Reserve(int n) {
3043    i32 old_max = _db.bh_syscmd_max;
3044    if (UNLIKELY(_db.bh_syscmd_n + n > old_max)) {
3045        u32 new_max  = u32_Max(4, old_max * 2);
3046        u32 old_size = old_max * sizeof(abt::FSyscmd*);
3047        u32 new_size = new_max * sizeof(abt::FSyscmd*);
3048        void *new_mem = abt::lpool_ReallocMem(_db.bh_syscmd_elems, old_size, new_size);
3049        if (UNLIKELY(!new_mem)) {
3050            FatalErrorExit("abt.out_of_memory  field:abt.FDb.bh_syscmd");
3051        }
3052        _db.bh_syscmd_elems = (abt::FSyscmd**)new_mem;
3053        _db.bh_syscmd_max = new_max;
3054    }
3055}
3056
3057// --- abt.FDb.bh_syscmd.Upheap
3058// Find and return index of new location for element ROW in the heap, starting at index IDX.
3059// Move any elements along the way but do not modify ROW.
3060static int abt::bh_syscmd_Upheap(abt::FSyscmd& row, int idx) {
3061    abt::FSyscmd* *elems = _db.bh_syscmd_elems;
3062    while (idx>0) {
3063        int j = (idx-1)/2;
3064        abt::FSyscmd* p = elems[j];
3065        if (!bh_syscmd_ElemLt(row, *p)) {
3066            break;
3067        }
3068        p->bh_syscmd_idx = idx;
3069        elems[idx] = p;
3070        idx = j;
3071    }
3072    return idx;
3073}
3074
3075// --- abt.FDb.bh_syscmd.ElemLt
3076inline static bool abt::bh_syscmd_ElemLt(abt::FSyscmd &a, abt::FSyscmd &b) {
3077    (void)_db;
3078    return execkey_Get(a) < execkey_Get(b);
3079}

3081// --- abt.FDb.zs_srcfile_read.Insert
3082// Insert row into linked list. If row is already in linked list, do nothing.
3083void abt::zs_srcfile_read_Insert(abt::FSrcfile& row) {
3084    if (!zs_srcfile_read_InLlistQ(row)) {
3085        abt::FSrcfile* old_tail       = _db.zs_srcfile_read_tail;
3086        row.zs_srcfile_read_next  = NULL;
3087        _db.zs_srcfile_read_tail = &row;
3088        abt::FSrcfile **new_row_a = &old_tail->zs_srcfile_read_next;
3089        abt::FSrcfile **new_row_b = &_db.zs_srcfile_read_head;
3090        abt::FSrcfile **new_row = old_tail ? new_row_a : new_row_b;
3091        *new_row = &row;
3092    }
3093}
3094
3095// --- abt.FDb.zs_srcfile_read.Remove
3096// Remove element from index. If element is not in index, do nothing.
3097// Since the list is singly-linked, use linear search to locate the element.
3098void abt::zs_srcfile_read_Remove(abt::FSrcfile& row) {
3099    if (zs_srcfile_read_InLlistQ(row)) {
3100        abt::FSrcfile* old_head       = _db.zs_srcfile_read_head;
3101        (void)old_head; // in case it's not used
3102        abt::FSrcfile* prev=NULL;
3103        abt::FSrcfile* cur     = _db.zs_srcfile_read_head;
3104        while (cur) {  // search for element by pointer
3105            abt::FSrcfile* next = cur->zs_srcfile_read_next;
3106            if (cur == &row) {
3107
3108                if (!next) {
3109                    _db.zs_srcfile_read_tail = prev;  // adjust tail pointer
3110                }
3111                // disconnect element from linked list
3112                if (prev) {
3113                    prev->zs_srcfile_read_next = next;
3114                } else {
3115                    _db.zs_srcfile_read_head = next;
3116                }
3117                row.zs_srcfile_read_next = (abt::FSrcfile*)-1; // not-in-list
3118                break;
3119            }
3120            prev = cur;
3121            cur  = next;
3122        }
3123    }
3124}
3125
3126// --- abt.FDb.zs_srcfile_read.RemoveAll
3127// Empty the index. (The rows are not deleted)
3128void abt::zs_srcfile_read_RemoveAll() {
3129    abt::FSrcfile* row = _db.zs_srcfile_read_head;
3130    _db.zs_srcfile_read_head = NULL;
3131    _db.zs_srcfile_read_tail = NULL;
3132    while (row) {
3133        abt::FSrcfile* row_next = row->zs_srcfile_read_next;
3134        row->zs_srcfile_read_next  = (abt::FSrcfile*)-1;
3135        row = row_next;
3136    }
3137}

3139// --- abt.FDb.zs_srcfile_read.RemoveFirst
3140// If linked list is empty, return NULL. Otherwise unlink and return pointer to first element.
3141abt::FSrcfile* abt::zs_srcfile_read_RemoveFirst() {
3142    abt::FSrcfile *row = NULL;
3143    row = _db.zs_srcfile_read_head;
3144    if (row) {
3145        abt::FSrcfile *next = row->zs_srcfile_read_next;
3146        _db.zs_srcfile_read_head = next;
3147        // clear list's tail pointer if list is empty.
3148        if (!next) {
3149            _db.zs_srcfile_read_tail = NULL;
3150        }
3151        row->zs_srcfile_read_next = (abt::FSrcfile*)-1; // mark as not-in-list
3152    }
3153    return row;
3154}

3184

3187                }

3191                } else {
3192                    _db.zs_sel_target_head = next;
3193                }
3194                row.zs_sel_target_next = (abt::FTarget*)-1; // not-in-list
3195                break;

3198            cur  = next;
3199        }
3200    }
3201}

3235// --- abt.FDb.targsyslib.Alloc

3237// If out of memory, process is killed.
3238abt::FTargsyslib& abt::targsyslib_Alloc() {
3239    abt::FTargsyslib* row = targsyslib_AllocMaybe();
3240    if (UNLIKELY(row == NULL)) {
3241        FatalErrorExit("abt.out_of_mem  field:abt.FDb.targsyslib  comment:'Alloc failed'");
3242    }

3246// --- abt.FDb.targsyslib.AllocMaybe
3247// Allocate memory for new element. If out of memory, return NULL.
3248abt::FTargsyslib* abt::targsyslib_AllocMaybe() {
3249    abt::FTargsyslib *row = (abt::FTargsyslib*)targsyslib_AllocMem();
3250    if (row) {
3251        new (row) abt::FTargsyslib; // call constructor
3252    }
3253    return row;
3254}

3256// --- abt.FDb.targsyslib.InsertMaybe
3257// Create new row from struct.
3258// Return pointer to new element, or NULL if insertion failed (due to out-of-memory, duplicate key, etc)
3259abt::FTargsyslib* abt::targsyslib_InsertMaybe(const dev::Targsyslib &value) {
3260    abt::FTargsyslib *row = &targsyslib_Alloc(); // if out of memory, process dies. if input error, return NULL.
3261    targsyslib_CopyIn(*row,const_cast<dev::Targsyslib&>(value));
3262    bool ok = targsyslib_XrefMaybe(*row); // this may return false
3263    if (!ok) {
3264        targsyslib_RemoveLast(); // delete offending row, any existing xrefs are cleared
3265        row = NULL; // forget this ever happened
3266    }
3267    return row;
3268}
3269
3270// --- abt.FDb.targsyslib.AllocMem
3271// Allocate space for one element. If no memory available, return NULL.
3272void* abt::targsyslib_AllocMem() {
3273    u64 new_nelems     = _db.targsyslib_n+1;
3274    // compute level and index on level
3275    u64 bsr   = algo::u64_BitScanReverse(new_nelems);
3276    u64 base  = u64(1)<<bsr;
3277    u64 index = new_nelems-base;
3278    void *ret = NULL;
3279    // if level doesn't exist yet, create it
3280    abt::FTargsyslib*  lev   = NULL;
3281    if (bsr < 32) {
3282        lev = _db.targsyslib_lary[bsr];
3283        if (!lev) {
3284            lev=(abt::FTargsyslib*)abt::lpool_AllocMem(sizeof(abt::FTargsyslib) * (u64(1)<<bsr));
3285            _db.targsyslib_lary[bsr] = lev;
3286        }
3287    }
3288    // allocate element from this level
3289    if (lev) {
3290        _db.targsyslib_n = i32(new_nelems);
3291        ret = lev + index;
3292    }
3293    return ret;
3294}
3295
3296// --- abt.FDb.targsyslib.RemoveLast
3297// Delete last element of array. Do nothing if array is empty.
3298void abt::targsyslib_RemoveLast() {
3299    u64 n = _db.targsyslib_n;
3300    if (n > 0) {
3301        n -= 1;
3302        targsyslib_qFind(u64(n)).~FTargsyslib();
3303        _db.targsyslib_n = i32(n);
3304    }
3305}
3306
3307// --- abt.FDb.targsyslib.InputMaybe
3308static bool abt::targsyslib_InputMaybe(dev::Targsyslib &elem) {
3309    bool retval = true;
3310    retval = targsyslib_InsertMaybe(elem) != nullptr;
3311    return retval;
3312}

3314// --- abt.FDb.targsyslib.XrefMaybe
3315// Insert row into all appropriate indices. If error occurs, store error
3316// in algo_lib::_db.errtext and return false. Caller must Delete or Unref such row.
3317bool abt::targsyslib_XrefMaybe(abt::FTargsyslib &row) {
3318    bool retval = true;
3319    (void)row;
3320    abt::FTarget* p_target = abt::ind_target_Find(target_Get(row));
3321    if (UNLIKELY(!p_target)) {
3322        algo_lib::ResetErrtext() << "abt.bad_xref  index:abt.FDb.ind_target" << Keyval("key", target_Get(row));
3323        return false;
3324    }
3325    // insert targsyslib into index c_targsyslib
3326    if (true) { // user-defined insert condition
3327        c_targsyslib_Insert(*p_target, row);
3328    }
3329    abt::FSyslib* p_syslib = abt::ind_syslib_Find(syslib_Get(row));
3330    if (UNLIKELY(!p_syslib)) {
3331        algo_lib::ResetErrtext() << "abt.bad_xref  index:abt.FDb.ind_syslib" << Keyval("key", syslib_Get(row));
3332        return false;
3333    }
3334    // targsyslib: save pointer to syslib
3335    if (true) { // user-defined insert condition
3336        row.p_syslib = p_syslib;
3337    }
3338    return retval;
3339}

3406    if (n > 0) {

3420// --- abt.FDb.syslib.XrefMaybe
3421// Insert row into all appropriate indices. If error occurs, store error
3422// in algo_lib::_db.errtext and return false. Caller must Delete or Unref such row.
3423bool abt::syslib_XrefMaybe(abt::FSyslib &row) {
3424    bool retval = true;
3425    (void)row;
3426    // insert syslib into index ind_syslib
3427    if (true) { // user-defined insert condition
3428        bool success = ind_syslib_InsertMaybe(row);
3429        if (UNLIKELY(!success)) {
3430            ch_RemoveAll(algo_lib::_db.errtext);
3431            algo_lib::_db.errtext << "abt.duplicate_key  xref:abt.FDb.ind_syslib"; // check for duplicate key
3432            return false;
3433        }
3434    }
3435    return retval;
3436}
3437
3438// --- abt.FDb.ind_syslib.Find
3439// Find row by key. Return NULL if not found.
3440abt::FSyslib* abt::ind_syslib_Find(const algo::strptr& key) {
3441    u32 index = algo::Smallstr50_Hash(0, key) & (_db.ind_syslib_buckets_n - 1);
3442    abt::FSyslib* *e = &_db.ind_syslib_buckets_elems[index];
3443    abt::FSyslib* ret=NULL;
3444    do {
3445        ret       = *e;
3446        bool done = !ret || (*ret).syslib == key;
3447        if (done) break;
3448        e         = &ret->ind_syslib_next;
3449    } while (true);
3450    return ret;
3451}
3452
3453// --- abt.FDb.ind_syslib.GetOrCreate
3454// Find row by key. If not found, create and x-reference a new row with with this key.
3455abt::FSyslib& abt::ind_syslib_GetOrCreate(const algo::strptr& key) {
3456    abt::FSyslib* ret = ind_syslib_Find(key);
3457    if (!ret) { //  if memory alloc fails, process dies; if insert fails, function returns NULL.
3458        ret         = &syslib_Alloc();
3459        (*ret).syslib = key;
3460        bool good = syslib_XrefMaybe(*ret);
3461        if (!good) {
3462            syslib_RemoveLast(); // delete offending row, any existing xrefs are cleared
3463            ret = NULL;
3464        }
3465    }
3466    vrfy(ret, tempstr() << "abt.create_error  table:ind_syslib  key:'"<<key<<"'  comment:'bad xref'");
3467    return *ret;
3468}
3469
3470// --- abt.FDb.ind_syslib.InsertMaybe
3471// Insert row into hash table. Return true if row is reachable through the hash after the function completes.
3472bool abt::ind_syslib_InsertMaybe(abt::FSyslib& row) {
3473    ind_syslib_Reserve(1);
3474    bool retval = true; // if already in hash, InsertMaybe returns true
3475    if (LIKELY(row.ind_syslib_next == (abt::FSyslib*)-1)) {// check if in hash already
3476        u32 index = algo::Smallstr50_Hash(0, row.syslib) & (_db.ind_syslib_buckets_n - 1);
3477        abt::FSyslib* *prev = &_db.ind_syslib_buckets_elems[index];
3478        do {
3479            abt::FSyslib* ret = *prev;
3480            if (!ret) { // exit condition 1: reached the end of the list
3481                break;
3482            }
3483            if ((*ret).syslib == row.syslib) { // exit condition 2: found matching key
3484                retval = false;
3485                break;
3486            }
3487            prev = &ret->ind_syslib_next;
3488        } while (true);
3489        if (retval) {
3490            row.ind_syslib_next = *prev;
3491            _db.ind_syslib_n++;
3492            *prev = &row;
3493        }
3494    }
3495    return retval;
3496}
3497
3498// --- abt.FDb.ind_syslib.Remove
3499// Remove reference to element from hash index. If element is not in hash, do nothing
3500void abt::ind_syslib_Remove(abt::FSyslib& row) {
3501    if (LIKELY(row.ind_syslib_next != (abt::FSyslib*)-1)) {// check if in hash already
3502        u32 index = algo::Smallstr50_Hash(0, row.syslib) & (_db.ind_syslib_buckets_n - 1);
3503        abt::FSyslib* *prev = &_db.ind_syslib_buckets_elems[index]; // addr of pointer to current element
3504        while (abt::FSyslib *next = *prev) {                          // scan the collision chain for our element
3505            if (next == &row) {        // found it?
3506                *prev = next->ind_syslib_next; // unlink (singly linked list)
3507                _db.ind_syslib_n--;
3508                row.ind_syslib_next = (abt::FSyslib*)-1;// not-in-hash
3509                break;
3510            }
3511            prev = &next->ind_syslib_next;
3512        }
3513    }
3514}
3515
3516// --- abt.FDb.ind_syslib.Reserve
3517// Reserve enough room in the hash for N more elements. Return success code.
3518void abt::ind_syslib_Reserve(int n) {
3519    u32 old_nbuckets = _db.ind_syslib_buckets_n;
3520    u32 new_nelems   = _db.ind_syslib_n + n;
3521    // # of elements has to be roughly equal to the number of buckets
3522    if (new_nelems > old_nbuckets) {
3523        int new_nbuckets = i32_Max(algo::BumpToPow2(new_nelems), u32(4));
3524        u32 old_size = old_nbuckets * sizeof(abt::FSyslib*);
3525        u32 new_size = new_nbuckets * sizeof(abt::FSyslib*);
3526        // allocate new array. we don't use Realloc since copying is not needed and factor of 2 probably
3527        // means new memory will have to be allocated anyway
3528        abt::FSyslib* *new_buckets = (abt::FSyslib**)abt::lpool_AllocMem(new_size);
3529        if (UNLIKELY(!new_buckets)) {
3530            FatalErrorExit("abt.out_of_memory  field:abt.FDb.ind_syslib");
3531        }
3532        memset(new_buckets, 0, new_size); // clear pointers
3533        // rehash all entries
3534        for (int i = 0; i < _db.ind_syslib_buckets_n; i++) {
3535            abt::FSyslib* elem = _db.ind_syslib_buckets_elems[i];
3536            while (elem) {
3537                abt::FSyslib &row        = *elem;
3538                abt::FSyslib* next       = row.ind_syslib_next;
3539                u32 index          = algo::Smallstr50_Hash(0, row.syslib) & (new_nbuckets-1);
3540                row.ind_syslib_next     = new_buckets[index];
3541                new_buckets[index] = &row;
3542                elem               = next;
3543            }
3544        }
3545        // free old array
3546        abt::lpool_FreeMem(_db.ind_syslib_buckets_elems, old_size);
3547        _db.ind_syslib_buckets_elems = new_buckets;
3548        _db.ind_syslib_buckets_n = new_nbuckets;
3549    }
3550}
3551
3552// --- abt.FDb.include.Alloc
3553// Allocate memory for new default row.
3554// If out of memory, process is killed.
3555abt::FInclude& abt::include_Alloc() {
3556    abt::FInclude* row = include_AllocMaybe();
3557    if (UNLIKELY(row == NULL)) {
3558        FatalErrorExit("abt.out_of_mem  field:abt.FDb.include  comment:'Alloc failed'");
3559    }
3560    return *row;
3561}
3562
3563// --- abt.FDb.include.AllocMaybe
3564// Allocate memory for new element. If out of memory, return NULL.
3565abt::FInclude* abt::include_AllocMaybe() {
3566    abt::FInclude *row = (abt::FInclude*)include_AllocMem();
3567    if (row) {
3568        new (row) abt::FInclude; // call constructor
3569    }
3570    return row;
3571}
3572
3573// --- abt.FDb.include.InsertMaybe
3574// Create new row from struct.
3575// Return pointer to new element, or NULL if insertion failed (due to out-of-memory, duplicate key, etc)
3576abt::FInclude* abt::include_InsertMaybe(const dev::Include &value) {
3577    abt::FInclude *row = &include_Alloc(); // if out of memory, process dies. if input error, return NULL.
3578    include_CopyIn(*row,const_cast<dev::Include&>(value));
3579    bool ok = include_XrefMaybe(*row); // this may return false
3580    if (!ok) {
3581        include_RemoveLast(); // delete offending row, any existing xrefs are cleared
3582        row = NULL; // forget this ever happened
3583    }
3584    return row;
3585}
3586
3587// --- abt.FDb.include.AllocMem
3588// Allocate space for one element. If no memory available, return NULL.
3589void* abt::include_AllocMem() {
3590    u64 new_nelems     = _db.include_n+1;
3591    // compute level and index on level
3592    u64 bsr   = algo::u64_BitScanReverse(new_nelems);
3593    u64 base  = u64(1)<<bsr;
3594    u64 index = new_nelems-base;
3595    void *ret = NULL;
3596    // if level doesn't exist yet, create it
3597    abt::FInclude*  lev   = NULL;
3598    if (bsr < 32) {
3599        lev = _db.include_lary[bsr];
3600        if (!lev) {
3601            lev=(abt::FInclude*)abt::lpool_AllocMem(sizeof(abt::FInclude) * (u64(1)<<bsr));
3602            _db.include_lary[bsr] = lev;
3603        }
3604    }
3605    // allocate element from this level
3606    if (lev) {
3607        _db.include_n = i32(new_nelems);
3608        ret = lev + index;
3609    }
3610    return ret;
3611}
3612
3613// --- abt.FDb.include.RemoveLast
3614// Delete last element of array. Do nothing if array is empty.
3615void abt::include_RemoveLast() {
3616    u64 n = _db.include_n;
3617    if (n > 0) {
3618        n -= 1;
3619        include_qFind(u64(n)).~FInclude();
3620        _db.include_n = i32(n);
3621    }
3622}
3623
3624// --- abt.FDb.include.InputMaybe
3625static bool abt::include_InputMaybe(dev::Include &elem) {
3626    bool retval = true;
3627    retval = include_InsertMaybe(elem) != nullptr;
3628    return retval;
3629}
3630
3631// --- abt.FDb.include.XrefMaybe
3632// Insert row into all appropriate indices. If error occurs, store error
3633// in algo_lib::_db.errtext and return false. Caller must Delete or Unref such row.
3634bool abt::include_XrefMaybe(abt::FInclude &row) {
3635    bool retval = true;
3636    (void)row;
3637    // insert include into index ind_include
3638    if (true) { // user-defined insert condition
3639        bool success = ind_include_InsertMaybe(row);
3640        if (UNLIKELY(!success)) {
3641            ch_RemoveAll(algo_lib::_db.errtext);
3642            algo_lib::_db.errtext << "abt.duplicate_key  xref:abt.FDb.ind_include"; // check for duplicate key
3643            return false;
3644        }
3645    }
3646    abt::FSrcfile* p_srcfile = abt::ind_srcfile_Find(srcfile_Get(row));
3647    if (UNLIKELY(!p_srcfile)) {
3648        algo_lib::ResetErrtext() << "abt.bad_xref  index:abt.FDb.ind_srcfile" << Keyval("key", srcfile_Get(row));
3649        return false;
3650    }
3651    // insert include into index zd_include
3652    if (true) { // user-defined insert condition
3653        zd_include_Insert(*p_srcfile, row);
3654    }
3655    abt::FSrcfile* p_filename = abt::ind_srcfile_Find(filename_Get(row));
3656    if (UNLIKELY(!p_filename)) {
3657        algo_lib::ResetErrtext() << "abt.bad_xref  index:abt.FDb.ind_srcfile" << Keyval("key", filename_Get(row));
3658        return false;
3659    }
3660    // include: save pointer to filename
3661    if (true) { // user-defined insert condition
3662        row.p_header = p_filename;
3663    }
3664    return retval;
3665}
3666
3667// --- abt.FDb.ind_include.Find
3668// Find row by key. Return NULL if not found.
3669abt::FInclude* abt::ind_include_Find(const algo::strptr& key) {
3670    u32 index = algo::Smallstr200_Hash(0, key) & (_db.ind_include_buckets_n - 1);
3671    abt::FInclude* *e = &_db.ind_include_buckets_elems[index];
3672    abt::FInclude* ret=NULL;
3673    do {
3674        ret       = *e;
3675        bool done = !ret || (*ret).include == key;
3676        if (done) break;
3677        e         = &ret->ind_include_next;
3678    } while (true);
3679    return ret;
3680}
3681
3682// --- abt.FDb.ind_include.GetOrCreate
3683// Find row by key. If not found, create and x-reference a new row with with this key.
3684abt::FInclude& abt::ind_include_GetOrCreate(const algo::strptr& key) {
3685    abt::FInclude* ret = ind_include_Find(key);
3686    if (!ret) { //  if memory alloc fails, process dies; if insert fails, function returns NULL.
3687        ret         = &include_Alloc();
3688        (*ret).include = key;
3689        bool good = include_XrefMaybe(*ret);
3690        if (!good) {
3691            include_RemoveLast(); // delete offending row, any existing xrefs are cleared
3692            ret = NULL;
3693        }
3694    }
3695    vrfy(ret, tempstr() << "abt.create_error  table:ind_include  key:'"<<key<<"'  comment:'bad xref'");
3696    return *ret;
3697}
3698
3699// --- abt.FDb.ind_include.InsertMaybe
3700// Insert row into hash table. Return true if row is reachable through the hash after the function completes.
3701bool abt::ind_include_InsertMaybe(abt::FInclude& row) {
3702    ind_include_Reserve(1);
3703    bool retval = true; // if already in hash, InsertMaybe returns true
3704    if (LIKELY(row.ind_include_next == (abt::FInclude*)-1)) {// check if in hash already
3705        u32 index = algo::Smallstr200_Hash(0, row.include) & (_db.ind_include_buckets_n - 1);
3706        abt::FInclude* *prev = &_db.ind_include_buckets_elems[index];
3707        do {
3708            abt::FInclude* ret = *prev;
3709            if (!ret) { // exit condition 1: reached the end of the list
3710                break;
3711            }
3712            if ((*ret).include == row.include) { // exit condition 2: found matching key
3713                retval = false;
3714                break;
3715            }
3716            prev = &ret->ind_include_next;
3717        } while (true);
3718        if (retval) {
3719            row.ind_include_next = *prev;
3720            _db.ind_include_n++;
3721            *prev = &row;
3722        }
3723    }
3724    return retval;
3725}
3726
3727// --- abt.FDb.ind_include.Remove
3728// Remove reference to element from hash index. If element is not in hash, do nothing
3729void abt::ind_include_Remove(abt::FInclude& row) {
3730    if (LIKELY(row.ind_include_next != (abt::FInclude*)-1)) {// check if in hash already
3731        u32 index = algo::Smallstr200_Hash(0, row.include) & (_db.ind_include_buckets_n - 1);
3732        abt::FInclude* *prev = &_db.ind_include_buckets_elems[index]; // addr of pointer to current element
3733        while (abt::FInclude *next = *prev) {                          // scan the collision chain for our element
3734            if (next == &row) {        // found it?
3735                *prev = next->ind_include_next; // unlink (singly linked list)
3736                _db.ind_include_n--;
3737                row.ind_include_next = (abt::FInclude*)-1;// not-in-hash
3738                break;
3739            }
3740            prev = &next->ind_include_next;
3741        }
3742    }
3743}
3744
3745// --- abt.FDb.ind_include.Reserve
3746// Reserve enough room in the hash for N more elements. Return success code.
3747void abt::ind_include_Reserve(int n) {
3748    u32 old_nbuckets = _db.ind_include_buckets_n;
3749    u32 new_nelems   = _db.ind_include_n + n;
3750    // # of elements has to be roughly equal to the number of buckets
3751    if (new_nelems > old_nbuckets) {
3752        int new_nbuckets = i32_Max(algo::BumpToPow2(new_nelems), u32(4));
3753        u32 old_size = old_nbuckets * sizeof(abt::FInclude*);
3754        u32 new_size = new_nbuckets * sizeof(abt::FInclude*);
3755        // allocate new array. we don't use Realloc since copying is not needed and factor of 2 probably
3756        // means new memory will have to be allocated anyway
3757        abt::FInclude* *new_buckets = (abt::FInclude**)abt::lpool_AllocMem(new_size);
3758        if (UNLIKELY(!new_buckets)) {
3759            FatalErrorExit("abt.out_of_memory  field:abt.FDb.ind_include");
3760        }
3761        memset(new_buckets, 0, new_size); // clear pointers
3762        // rehash all entries
3763        for (int i = 0; i < _db.ind_include_buckets_n; i++) {
3764            abt::FInclude* elem = _db.ind_include_buckets_elems[i];
3765            while (elem) {
3766                abt::FInclude &row        = *elem;
3767                abt::FInclude* next       = row.ind_include_next;
3768                u32 index          = algo::Smallstr200_Hash(0, row.include) & (new_nbuckets-1);
3769                row.ind_include_next     = new_buckets[index];
3770                new_buckets[index] = &row;
3771                elem               = next;
3772            }
3773        }
3774        // free old array
3775        abt::lpool_FreeMem(_db.ind_include_buckets_elems, old_size);
3776        _db.ind_include_buckets_elems = new_buckets;
3777        _db.ind_include_buckets_n = new_nbuckets;
3778    }
3779}
3780
3781// --- abt.FDb.sysincl.Addary
3782// Reserve space (this may move memory). Insert N element at the end.
3783// Return aryptr to newly inserted block.
3784// If the RHS argument aliases the array (refers to the same memory), exit program with fatal error.
3785algo::aryptr<algo::cstring> abt::sysincl_Addary(algo::aryptr<algo::cstring> rhs) {
3786    bool overlaps = rhs.n_elems>0 && rhs.elems >= _db.sysincl_elems && rhs.elems < _db.sysincl_elems + _db.sysincl_max;
3787    if (UNLIKELY(overlaps)) {
3788        FatalErrorExit("abt.tary_alias  field:abt.FDb.sysincl  comment:'alias error: sub-array is being appended to the whole'");
3789    }
3790    int nnew = rhs.n_elems;
3791    sysincl_Reserve(nnew); // reserve space
3792    int at = _db.sysincl_n;
3793    for (int i = 0; i < nnew; i++) {
3794        new (_db.sysincl_elems + at + i) algo::cstring(rhs[i]);
3795        _db.sysincl_n++;
3796    }
3797    return algo::aryptr<algo::cstring>(_db.sysincl_elems + at, nnew);
3798}
3799
3800// --- abt.FDb.sysincl.Alloc
3801// Reserve space. Insert element at the end
3802// The new element is initialized to a default value
3803algo::cstring& abt::sysincl_Alloc() {
3804    sysincl_Reserve(1);
3805    int n  = _db.sysincl_n;
3806    int at = n;
3807    algo::cstring *elems = _db.sysincl_elems;
3808    new (elems + at) algo::cstring(); // construct new element, default initializer
3809    _db.sysincl_n = n+1;
3810    return elems[at];
3811}
3812
3813// --- abt.FDb.sysincl.AllocAt
3814// Reserve space for new element, reallocating the array if necessary
3815// Insert new element at specified index. Index must be in range or a fatal error occurs.
3816algo::cstring& abt::sysincl_AllocAt(int at) {
3817    sysincl_Reserve(1);
3818    int n  = _db.sysincl_n;
3819    if (UNLIKELY(u64(at) >= u64(n+1))) {
3820        FatalErrorExit("abt.bad_alloc_at  field:abt.FDb.sysincl  comment:'index out of range'");
3821    }
3822    algo::cstring *elems = _db.sysincl_elems;
3823    memmove(elems + at + 1, elems + at, (n - at) * sizeof(algo::cstring));
3824    new (elems + at) algo::cstring(); // construct element, default initializer
3825    _db.sysincl_n = n+1;
3826    return elems[at];
3827}
3828
3829// --- abt.FDb.sysincl.AllocN
3830// Reserve space. Insert N elements at the end of the array, return pointer to array
3831algo::aryptr<algo::cstring> abt::sysincl_AllocN(int n_elems) {
3832    sysincl_Reserve(n_elems);
3833    int old_n  = _db.sysincl_n;
3834    int new_n = old_n + n_elems;
3835    algo::cstring *elems = _db.sysincl_elems;
3836    for (int i = old_n; i < new_n; i++) {
3837        new (elems + i) algo::cstring(); // construct new element, default initialize
3838    }
3839    _db.sysincl_n = new_n;
3840    return algo::aryptr<algo::cstring>(elems + old_n, n_elems);
3841}
3842
3843// --- abt.FDb.sysincl.Remove
3844// Remove item by index. If index outside of range, do nothing.
3845void abt::sysincl_Remove(u32 i) {
3846    u32 lim = _db.sysincl_n;
3847    algo::cstring *elems = _db.sysincl_elems;
3848    if (i < lim) {
3849        elems[i].~cstring(); // destroy element
3850        memmove(elems + i, elems + (i + 1), sizeof(algo::cstring) * (lim - (i + 1)));
3851        _db.sysincl_n = lim - 1;
3852    }
3853}
3854
3855// --- abt.FDb.sysincl.RemoveAll
3856void abt::sysincl_RemoveAll() {
3857    u32 n = _db.sysincl_n;
3858    while (n > 0) {
3859        n -= 1;
3860        _db.sysincl_elems[n].~cstring();
3861        _db.sysincl_n = n;
3862    }
3863}
3864
3865// --- abt.FDb.sysincl.RemoveLast
3866// Delete last element of array. Do nothing if array is empty.
3867void abt::sysincl_RemoveLast() {
3868    u64 n = _db.sysincl_n;
3869    if (n > 0) {
3870        n -= 1;
3871        sysincl_qFind(u64(n)).~cstring();
3872        _db.sysincl_n = n;
3873    }
3874}
3875
3876// --- abt.FDb.sysincl.AbsReserve
3877// Make sure N elements fit in array. Process dies if out of memory
3878void abt::sysincl_AbsReserve(int n) {
3879    u32 old_max  = _db.sysincl_max;
3880    if (n > i32(old_max)) {
3881        u32 new_max  = i32_Max(i32_Max(old_max * 2, n), 4);
3882        void *new_mem = abt::lpool_ReallocMem(_db.sysincl_elems, old_max * sizeof(algo::cstring), new_max * sizeof(algo::cstring));
3883        if (UNLIKELY(!new_mem)) {
3884            FatalErrorExit("abt.tary_nomem  field:abt.FDb.sysincl  comment:'out of memory'");
3885        }
3886        _db.sysincl_elems = (algo::cstring*)new_mem;
3887        _db.sysincl_max = new_max;
3888    }
3889}
3890
3891// --- abt.FDb.sysincl.AllocNVal
3892// Reserve space. Insert N elements at the end of the array, return pointer to array
3893algo::aryptr<algo::cstring> abt::sysincl_AllocNVal(int n_elems, const algo::cstring& val) {
3894    sysincl_Reserve(n_elems);
3895    int old_n  = _db.sysincl_n;
3896    int new_n = old_n + n_elems;
3897    algo::cstring *elems = _db.sysincl_elems;
3898    for (int i = old_n; i < new_n; i++) {
3899        new (elems + i) algo::cstring(val);
3900    }
3901    _db.sysincl_n = new_n;
3902    return algo::aryptr<algo::cstring>(elems + old_n, n_elems);
3903}

3905// --- abt.FDb.sysincl.ReadStrptrMaybe
3906// A single element is read from input string and appended to the array.
3907// If the string contains an error, the array is untouched.
3908// Function returns success value.
3909bool abt::sysincl_ReadStrptrMaybe(algo::strptr in_str) {
3910    bool retval = true;
3911    algo::cstring &elem = sysincl_Alloc();
3912    retval = algo::cstring_ReadStrptrMaybe(elem, in_str);
3913    if (!retval) {
3914        sysincl_RemoveLast();
3915    }
3916    return retval;
3917}
3918
3919// --- abt.FDb.zs_origsel_target.Insert
3920// Insert row into linked list. If row is already in linked list, do nothing.
3921void abt::zs_origsel_target_Insert(abt::FTarget& row) {
3922    if (!zs_origsel_target_InLlistQ(row)) {
3923        abt::FTarget* old_tail       = _db.zs_origsel_target_tail;
3924        row.zs_origsel_target_next  = NULL;
3925        _db.zs_origsel_target_tail = &row;
3926        abt::FTarget **new_row_a = &old_tail->zs_origsel_target_next;
3927        abt::FTarget **new_row_b = &_db.zs_origsel_target_head;
3928        abt::FTarget **new_row = old_tail ? new_row_a : new_row_b;
3929        *new_row = &row;
3930    }
3931}
3932
3933// --- abt.FDb.zs_origsel_target.Remove
3934// Remove element from index. If element is not in index, do nothing.
3935// Since the list is singly-linked, use linear search to locate the element.
3936void abt::zs_origsel_target_Remove(abt::FTarget& row) {
3937    if (zs_origsel_target_InLlistQ(row)) {
3938        abt::FTarget* old_head       = _db.zs_origsel_target_head;
3939        (void)old_head; // in case it's not used
3940        abt::FTarget* prev=NULL;
3941        abt::FTarget* cur     = _db.zs_origsel_target_head;
3942        while (cur) {  // search for element by pointer
3943            abt::FTarget* next = cur->zs_origsel_target_next;
3944            if (cur == &row) {
3945
3946                if (!next) {
3947                    _db.zs_origsel_target_tail = prev;  // adjust tail pointer
3948                }
3949                // disconnect element from linked list
3950                if (prev) {
3951                    prev->zs_origsel_target_next = next;
3952                } else {
3953                    _db.zs_origsel_target_head = next;
3954                }
3955                row.zs_origsel_target_next = (abt::FTarget*)-1; // not-in-list
3956                break;
3957            }
3958            prev = cur;
3959            cur  = next;
3960        }
3961    }
3962}
3963
3964// --- abt.FDb.zs_origsel_target.RemoveAll
3965// Empty the index. (The rows are not deleted)
3966void abt::zs_origsel_target_RemoveAll() {
3967    abt::FTarget* row = _db.zs_origsel_target_head;
3968    _db.zs_origsel_target_head = NULL;
3969    _db.zs_origsel_target_tail = NULL;
3970    while (row) {
3971        abt::FTarget* row_next = row->zs_origsel_target_next;
3972        row->zs_origsel_target_next  = (abt::FTarget*)-1;
3973        row = row_next;
3974    }
3975}
3976
3977// --- abt.FDb.zs_origsel_target.RemoveFirst
3978// If linked list is empty, return NULL. Otherwise unlink and return pointer to first element.
3979abt::FTarget* abt::zs_origsel_target_RemoveFirst() {
3980    abt::FTarget *row = NULL;
3981    row = _db.zs_origsel_target_head;
3982    if (row) {
3983        abt::FTarget *next = row->zs_origsel_target_next;
3984        _db.zs_origsel_target_head = next;
3985        // clear list's tail pointer if list is empty.
3986        if (!next) {
3987            _db.zs_origsel_target_tail = NULL;
3988        }
3989        row->zs_origsel_target_next = (abt::FTarget*)-1; // mark as not-in-list
3990    }
3991    return row;
3992}
3993
3994// --- abt.FDb.ns.Alloc
3995// Allocate memory for new default row.
3996// If out of memory, process is killed.
3997abt::FNs& abt::ns_Alloc() {
3998    abt::FNs* row = ns_AllocMaybe();
3999    if (UNLIKELY(row == NULL)) {
4000        FatalErrorExit("abt.out_of_mem  field:abt.FDb.ns  comment:'Alloc failed'");
4001    }
4002    return *row;
4003}
4004
4005// --- abt.FDb.ns.AllocMaybe
4006// Allocate memory for new element. If out of memory, return NULL.
4007abt::FNs* abt::ns_AllocMaybe() {
4008    abt::FNs *row = (abt::FNs*)ns_AllocMem();
4009    if (row) {
4010        new (row) abt::FNs; // call constructor
4011    }
4012    return row;
4013}
4014
4015// --- abt.FDb.ns.InsertMaybe
4016// Create new row from struct.
4017// Return pointer to new element, or NULL if insertion failed (due to out-of-memory, duplicate key, etc)
4018abt::FNs* abt::ns_InsertMaybe(const dmmeta::Ns &value) {
4019    abt::FNs *row = &ns_Alloc(); // if out of memory, process dies. if input error, return NULL.
4020    ns_CopyIn(*row,const_cast<dmmeta::Ns&>(value));
4021    bool ok = ns_XrefMaybe(*row); // this may return false
4022    if (!ok) {
4023        ns_RemoveLast(); // delete offending row, any existing xrefs are cleared
4024        row = NULL; // forget this ever happened
4025    }
4026    return row;
4027}
4028
4029// --- abt.FDb.ns.AllocMem
4030// Allocate space for one element. If no memory available, return NULL.
4031void* abt::ns_AllocMem() {
4032    u64 new_nelems     = _db.ns_n+1;
4033    // compute level and index on level
4034    u64 bsr   = algo::u64_BitScanReverse(new_nelems);
4035    u64 base  = u64(1)<<bsr;
4036    u64 index = new_nelems-base;
4037    void *ret = NULL;
4038    // if level doesn't exist yet, create it
4039    abt::FNs*  lev   = NULL;
4040    if (bsr < 32) {
4041        lev = _db.ns_lary[bsr];
4042        if (!lev) {
4043            lev=(abt::FNs*)abt::lpool_AllocMem(sizeof(abt::FNs) * (u64(1)<<bsr));
4044            _db.ns_lary[bsr] = lev;
4045        }
4046    }
4047    // allocate element from this level
4048    if (lev) {
4049        _db.ns_n = i32(new_nelems);
4050        ret = lev + index;
4051    }
4052    return ret;
4053}
4054
4055// --- abt.FDb.ns.RemoveLast
4056// Delete last element of array. Do nothing if array is empty.
4057void abt::ns_RemoveLast() {
4058    u64 n = _db.ns_n;
4059    if (n > 0) {
4060        n -= 1;
4061        ns_qFind(u64(n)).~FNs();
4062        _db.ns_n = i32(n);
4063    }
4064}
4065
4066// --- abt.FDb.ns.InputMaybe
4067static bool abt::ns_InputMaybe(dmmeta::Ns &elem) {
4068    bool retval = true;
4069    retval = ns_InsertMaybe(elem) != nullptr;
4070    return retval;
4071}
4072
4073// --- abt.FDb.ns.XrefMaybe
4074// Insert row into all appropriate indices. If error occurs, store error
4075// in algo_lib::_db.errtext and return false. Caller must Delete or Unref such row.
4076bool abt::ns_XrefMaybe(abt::FNs &row) {
4077    bool retval = true;
4078    (void)row;
4079    // insert ns into index ind_ns
4080    if (true) { // user-defined insert condition
4081        bool success = ind_ns_InsertMaybe(row);
4082        if (UNLIKELY(!success)) {
4083            ch_RemoveAll(algo_lib::_db.errtext);
4084            algo_lib::_db.errtext << "abt.duplicate_key  xref:abt.FDb.ind_ns"; // check for duplicate key
4085            return false;
4086        }
4087    }
4088    return retval;
4089}
4090
4091// --- abt.FDb.ind_ns.Find
4092// Find row by key. Return NULL if not found.
4093abt::FNs* abt::ind_ns_Find(const algo::strptr& key) {
4094    u32 index = algo::Smallstr16_Hash(0, key) & (_db.ind_ns_buckets_n - 1);
4095    abt::FNs* *e = &_db.ind_ns_buckets_elems[index];
4096    abt::FNs* ret=NULL;
4097    do {
4098        ret       = *e;
4099        bool done = !ret || (*ret).ns == key;
4100        if (done) break;
4101        e         = &ret->ind_ns_next;
4102    } while (true);
4103    return ret;
4104}
4105
4106// --- abt.FDb.ind_ns.GetOrCreate
4107// Find row by key. If not found, create and x-reference a new row with with this key.
4108abt::FNs& abt::ind_ns_GetOrCreate(const algo::strptr& key) {
4109    abt::FNs* ret = ind_ns_Find(key);
4110    if (!ret) { //  if memory alloc fails, process dies; if insert fails, function returns NULL.
4111        ret         = &ns_Alloc();
4112        (*ret).ns = key;
4113        bool good = ns_XrefMaybe(*ret);
4114        if (!good) {
4115            ns_RemoveLast(); // delete offending row, any existing xrefs are cleared
4116            ret = NULL;
4117        }
4118    }
4119    vrfy(ret, tempstr() << "abt.create_error  table:ind_ns  key:'"<<key<<"'  comment:'bad xref'");
4120    return *ret;
4121}
4122
4123// --- abt.FDb.ind_ns.InsertMaybe
4124// Insert row into hash table. Return true if row is reachable through the hash after the function completes.
4125bool abt::ind_ns_InsertMaybe(abt::FNs& row) {
4126    ind_ns_Reserve(1);
4127    bool retval = true; // if already in hash, InsertMaybe returns true
4128    if (LIKELY(row.ind_ns_next == (abt::FNs*)-1)) {// check if in hash already
4129        u32 index = algo::Smallstr16_Hash(0, row.ns) & (_db.ind_ns_buckets_n - 1);
4130        abt::FNs* *prev = &_db.ind_ns_buckets_elems[index];
4131        do {
4132            abt::FNs* ret = *prev;
4133            if (!ret) { // exit condition 1: reached the end of the list
4134                break;
4135            }
4136            if ((*ret).ns == row.ns) { // exit condition 2: found matching key
4137                retval = false;
4138                break;
4139            }
4140            prev = &ret->ind_ns_next;
4141        } while (true);
4142        if (retval) {
4143            row.ind_ns_next = *prev;
4144            _db.ind_ns_n++;
4145            *prev = &row;
4146        }
4147    }
4148    return retval;
4149}
4150
4151// --- abt.FDb.ind_ns.Remove
4152// Remove reference to element from hash index. If element is not in hash, do nothing
4153void abt::ind_ns_Remove(abt::FNs& row) {
4154    if (LIKELY(row.ind_ns_next != (abt::FNs*)-1)) {// check if in hash already
4155        u32 index = algo::Smallstr16_Hash(0, row.ns) & (_db.ind_ns_buckets_n - 1);
4156        abt::FNs* *prev = &_db.ind_ns_buckets_elems[index]; // addr of pointer to current element
4157        while (abt::FNs *next = *prev) {                          // scan the collision chain for our element
4158            if (next == &row) {        // found it?
4159                *prev = next->ind_ns_next; // unlink (singly linked list)
4160                _db.ind_ns_n--;
4161                row.ind_ns_next = (abt::FNs*)-1;// not-in-hash
4162                break;
4163            }
4164            prev = &next->ind_ns_next;
4165        }
4166    }
4167}
4168
4169// --- abt.FDb.ind_ns.Reserve
4170// Reserve enough room in the hash for N more elements. Return success code.
4171void abt::ind_ns_Reserve(int n) {
4172    u32 old_nbuckets = _db.ind_ns_buckets_n;
4173    u32 new_nelems   = _db.ind_ns_n + n;
4174    // # of elements has to be roughly equal to the number of buckets
4175    if (new_nelems > old_nbuckets) {
4176        int new_nbuckets = i32_Max(algo::BumpToPow2(new_nelems), u32(4));
4177        u32 old_size = old_nbuckets * sizeof(abt::FNs*);
4178        u32 new_size = new_nbuckets * sizeof(abt::FNs*);
4179        // allocate new array. we don't use Realloc since copying is not needed and factor of 2 probably
4180        // means new memory will have to be allocated anyway
4181        abt::FNs* *new_buckets = (abt::FNs**)abt::lpool_AllocMem(new_size);
4182        if (UNLIKELY(!new_buckets)) {
4183            FatalErrorExit("abt.out_of_memory  field:abt.FDb.ind_ns");
4184        }
4185        memset(new_buckets, 0, new_size); // clear pointers
4186        // rehash all entries
4187        for (int i = 0; i < _db.ind_ns_buckets_n; i++) {
4188            abt::FNs* elem = _db.ind_ns_buckets_elems[i];
4189            while (elem) {
4190                abt::FNs &row        = *elem;
4191                abt::FNs* next       = row.ind_ns_next;
4192                u32 index          = algo::Smallstr16_Hash(0, row.ns) & (new_nbuckets-1);
4193                row.ind_ns_next     = new_buckets[index];
4194                new_buckets[index] = &row;
4195                elem               = next;
4196            }
4197        }
4198        // free old array
4199        abt::lpool_FreeMem(_db.ind_ns_buckets_elems, old_size);
4200        _db.ind_ns_buckets_elems = new_buckets;
4201        _db.ind_ns_buckets_n = new_nbuckets;
4202    }
4203}

4205// --- abt.FDb.filestat.Alloc
4206// Allocate memory for new default row.
4207// If out of memory, process is killed.
4208abt::FFilestat& abt::filestat_Alloc() {
4209    abt::FFilestat* row = filestat_AllocMaybe();
4210    if (UNLIKELY(row == NULL)) {
4211        FatalErrorExit("abt.out_of_mem  field:abt.FDb.filestat  comment:'Alloc failed'");
4212    }
4213    return *row;
4214}

4218abt::FFilestat* abt::filestat_AllocMaybe() {

4220    if (row) {
4221        new (row) abt::FFilestat; // call constructor
4222    }
4223    return row;
4224}

4230    // compute level and index on level
4231    u64 bsr   = algo::u64_BitScanReverse(new_nelems);
4232    u64 base  = u64(1)<<bsr;
4233    u64 index = new_nelems-base;
4234    void *ret = NULL;
4235    // if level doesn't exist yet, create it
4236    abt::FFilestat*  lev   = NULL;
4237    if (bsr < 32) {
4238        lev = _db.filestat_lary[bsr];
4239        if (!lev) {
4240            lev=(abt::FFilestat*)abt::lpool_AllocMem(sizeof(abt::FFilestat) * (u64(1)<<bsr));
4241            _db.filestat_lary[bsr] = lev;
4242        }
4243    }
4244    // allocate element from this level
4245    if (lev) {
4246        _db.filestat_n = i32(new_nelems);
4247        ret = lev + index;
4248    }
4249    return ret;
4250}

4252// --- abt.FDb.filestat.RemoveAll
4253// Remove all elements from Lary
4254void abt::filestat_RemoveAll() {
4255    for (u64 n = _db.filestat_n; n>0; ) {
4256        n--;
4257        filestat_qFind(u64(n)).~FFilestat(); // destroy last element
4258        _db.filestat_n = i32(n);
4259    }
4260}
4261
4262// --- abt.FDb.filestat.RemoveLast
4263// Delete last element of array. Do nothing if array is empty.
4264void abt::filestat_RemoveLast() {
4265    u64 n = _db.filestat_n;
4266    if (n > 0) {
4267        n -= 1;
4268        filestat_qFind(u64(n)).~FFilestat();
4269        _db.filestat_n = i32(n);
4270    }
4271}

4276bool abt::filestat_XrefMaybe(abt::FFilestat &row) {

4278    (void)row;
4279    // insert filestat into index ind_filestat
4280    if (true) { // user-defined insert condition
4281        bool success = ind_filestat_InsertMaybe(row);

4284            algo_lib::_db.errtext << "abt.duplicate_key  xref:abt.FDb.ind_filestat"; // check for duplicate key
4285            return false;

4291// --- abt.FDb.ind_filestat.Find
4292// Find row by key. Return NULL if not found.
4293abt::FFilestat* abt::ind_filestat_Find(const algo::strptr& key) {
4294    u32 index = algo::cstring_Hash(0, key) & (_db.ind_filestat_buckets_n - 1);
4295    abt::FFilestat* *e = &_db.ind_filestat_buckets_elems[index];
4296    abt::FFilestat* ret=NULL;
4297    do {
4298        ret       = *e;
4299        bool done = !ret || (*ret).filename == key;
4300        if (done) break;
4301        e         = &ret->ind_filestat_next;
4302    } while (true);
4303    return ret;
4304}

4306// --- abt.FDb.ind_filestat.GetOrCreate
4307// Find row by key. If not found, create and x-reference a new row with with this key.
4308abt::FFilestat& abt::ind_filestat_GetOrCreate(const algo::strptr& key) {
4309    abt::FFilestat* ret = ind_filestat_Find(key);
4310    if (!ret) { //  if memory alloc fails, process dies; if insert fails, function returns NULL.
4311        ret         = &filestat_Alloc();
4312        (*ret).filename = key;
4313        bool good = filestat_XrefMaybe(*ret);
4314        if (!good) {
4315            filestat_RemoveLast(); // delete offending row, any existing xrefs are cleared
4316            ret = NULL;
4317        }
4318    }
4319    vrfy(ret, tempstr() << "abt.create_error  table:ind_filestat  key:'"<<key<<"'  comment:'bad xref'");
4320    return *ret;
4321}

4323// --- abt.FDb.ind_filestat.InsertMaybe
4324// Insert row into hash table. Return true if row is reachable through the hash after the function completes.
4325bool abt::ind_filestat_InsertMaybe(abt::FFilestat& row) {
4326    ind_filestat_Reserve(1);
4327    bool retval = true; // if already in hash, InsertMaybe returns true
4328    if (LIKELY(row.ind_filestat_next == (abt::FFilestat*)-1)) {// check if in hash already
4329        u32 index = algo::cstring_Hash(0, row.filename) & (_db.ind_filestat_buckets_n - 1);
4330        abt::FFilestat* *prev = &_db.ind_filestat_buckets_elems[index];
4331        do {
4332            abt::FFilestat* ret = *prev;
4333            if (!ret) { // exit condition 1: reached the end of the list
4334                break;
4335            }
4336            if ((*ret).filename == row.filename) { // exit condition 2: found matching key
4337                retval = false;
4338                break;
4339            }
4340            prev = &ret->ind_filestat_next;
4341        } while (true);
4342        if (retval) {
4343            row.ind_filestat_next = *prev;
4344            _db.ind_filestat_n++;
4345            *prev = &row;
4346        }
4347    }
4348    return retval;
4349}

4351// --- abt.FDb.ind_filestat.Remove
4352// Remove reference to element from hash index. If element is not in hash, do nothing
4353void abt::ind_filestat_Remove(abt::FFilestat& row) {
4354    if (LIKELY(row.ind_filestat_next != (abt::FFilestat*)-1)) {// check if in hash already
4355        u32 index = algo::cstring_Hash(0, row.filename) & (_db.ind_filestat_buckets_n - 1);
4356        abt::FFilestat* *prev = &_db.ind_filestat_buckets_elems[index]; // addr of pointer to current element
4357        while (abt::FFilestat *next = *prev) {                          // scan the collision chain for our element
4358            if (next == &row) {        // found it?
4359                *prev = next->ind_filestat_next; // unlink (singly linked list)
4360                _db.ind_filestat_n--;
4361                row.ind_filestat_next = (abt::FFilestat*)-1;// not-in-hash
4362                break;
4363            }
4364            prev = &next->ind_filestat_next;
4365        }
4366    }
4367}

4369// --- abt.FDb.ind_filestat.Reserve
4370// Reserve enough room in the hash for N more elements. Return success code.
4371void abt::ind_filestat_Reserve(int n) {
4372    u32 old_nbuckets = _db.ind_filestat_buckets_n;
4373    u32 new_nelems   = _db.ind_filestat_n + n;
4374    // # of elements has to be roughly equal to the number of buckets
4375    if (new_nelems > old_nbuckets) {
4376        int new_nbuckets = i32_Max(algo::BumpToPow2(new_nelems), u32(4));
4377        u32 old_size = old_nbuckets * sizeof(abt::FFilestat*);
4378        u32 new_size = new_nbuckets * sizeof(abt::FFilestat*);
4379        // allocate new array. we don't use Realloc since copying is not needed and factor of 2 probably
4380        // means new memory will have to be allocated anyway
4381        abt::FFilestat* *new_buckets = (abt::FFilestat**)abt::lpool_AllocMem(new_size);
4382        if (UNLIKELY(!new_buckets)) {
4383            FatalErrorExit("abt.out_of_memory  field:abt.FDb.ind_filestat");
4384        }
4385        memset(new_buckets, 0, new_size); // clear pointers
4386        // rehash all entries
4387        for (int i = 0; i < _db.ind_filestat_buckets_n; i++) {
4388            abt::FFilestat* elem = _db.ind_filestat_buckets_elems[i];
4389            while (elem) {
4390                abt::FFilestat &row        = *elem;
4391                abt::FFilestat* next       = row.ind_filestat_next;
4392                u32 index          = algo::cstring_Hash(0, row.filename) & (new_nbuckets-1);
4393                row.ind_filestat_next     = new_buckets[index];
4394                new_buckets[index] = &row;
4395                elem               = next;
4396            }
4397        }
4398        // free old array
4399        abt::lpool_FreeMem(_db.ind_filestat_buckets_elems, old_size);
4400        _db.ind_filestat_buckets_elems = new_buckets;
4401        _db.ind_filestat_buckets_n = new_nbuckets;
4402    }
4403}
4404
4405// --- abt.FDb.zd_inclstack.Insert
4406// Insert row into linked list. If row is already in linked list, do nothing.
4407void abt::zd_inclstack_Insert(abt::FSrcfile& row) {
4408    if (!zd_inclstack_InLlistQ(row)) {
4409        abt::FSrcfile* old_tail = _db.zd_inclstack_tail;
4410        row.zd_inclstack_next = NULL;
4411        row.zd_inclstack_prev = old_tail;
4412        _db.zd_inclstack_tail = &row;
4413        abt::FSrcfile **new_row_a = &old_tail->zd_inclstack_next;
4414        abt::FSrcfile **new_row_b = &_db.zd_inclstack_head;
4415        abt::FSrcfile **new_row = old_tail ? new_row_a : new_row_b;
4416        *new_row = &row;
4417        _db.zd_inclstack_n++;
4418    }
4419}
4420
4421// --- abt.FDb.zd_inclstack.Remove
4422// Remove element from index. If element is not in index, do nothing.
4423void abt::zd_inclstack_Remove(abt::FSrcfile& row) {
4424    if (zd_inclstack_InLlistQ(row)) {
4425        abt::FSrcfile* old_head       = _db.zd_inclstack_head;
4426        (void)old_head; // in case it's not used
4427        abt::FSrcfile* prev = row.zd_inclstack_prev;
4428        abt::FSrcfile* next = row.zd_inclstack_next;
4429        // if element is first, adjust list head; otherwise, adjust previous element's next
4430        abt::FSrcfile **new_next_a = &prev->zd_inclstack_next;
4431        abt::FSrcfile **new_next_b = &_db.zd_inclstack_head;
4432        abt::FSrcfile **new_next = prev ? new_next_a : new_next_b;
4433        *new_next = next;
4434        // if element is last, adjust list tail; otherwise, adjust next element's prev
4435        abt::FSrcfile **new_prev_a = &next->zd_inclstack_prev;
4436        abt::FSrcfile **new_prev_b = &_db.zd_inclstack_tail;
4437        abt::FSrcfile **new_prev = next ? new_prev_a : new_prev_b;
4438        *new_prev = prev;
4439        _db.zd_inclstack_n--;
4440        row.zd_inclstack_next=(abt::FSrcfile*)-1; // not-in-list
4441    }
4442}
4443
4444// --- abt.FDb.zd_inclstack.RemoveAll
4445// Empty the index. (The rows are not deleted)
4446void abt::zd_inclstack_RemoveAll() {
4447    abt::FSrcfile* row = _db.zd_inclstack_head;
4448    _db.zd_inclstack_head = NULL;
4449    _db.zd_inclstack_tail = NULL;
4450    _db.zd_inclstack_n = 0;
4451    while (row) {
4452        abt::FSrcfile* row_next = row->zd_inclstack_next;
4453        row->zd_inclstack_next  = (abt::FSrcfile*)-1;
4454        row->zd_inclstack_prev  = NULL;
4455        row = row_next;
4456    }
4457}
4458
4459// --- abt.FDb.zd_inclstack.RemoveFirst
4460// If linked list is empty, return NULL. Otherwise unlink and return pointer to first element.
4461abt::FSrcfile* abt::zd_inclstack_RemoveFirst() {
4462    abt::FSrcfile *row = NULL;
4463    row = _db.zd_inclstack_head;
4464    if (row) {
4465        abt::FSrcfile *next = row->zd_inclstack_next;
4466        _db.zd_inclstack_head = next;
4467        abt::FSrcfile **new_end_a = &next->zd_inclstack_prev;
4468        abt::FSrcfile **new_end_b = &_db.zd_inclstack_tail;
4469        abt::FSrcfile **new_end = next ? new_end_a : new_end_b;
4470        *new_end = NULL;
4471        _db.zd_inclstack_n--;
4472        row->zd_inclstack_next = (abt::FSrcfile*)-1; // mark as not-in-list
4473    }
4474    return row;
4475}

4477// --- abt.FDb.trace.RowidFind
4478// find trace by row id (used to implement reflection)
4479static algo::ImrowPtr abt::trace_RowidFind(int t) {
4480    return algo::ImrowPtr(t==0 ? u64(&_db.trace) : u64(0));
4481}
