4483// --- abt.FDb.trace.N
4484// Function return 1
4485inline static i32 abt::trace_N() {
4486    return 1;
4487}
4488
4489// --- abt.FDb.bh_syscmd_curs.Add
4490static void abt::_db_bh_syscmd_curs_Add(_db_bh_syscmd_curs &curs, abt::FSyscmd& row) {
4491    u32 n = curs.temp_n;
4492    int i = n;
4493    curs.temp_n = n+1;
4494    abt::FSyscmd* *elems = curs.temp_elems;
4495    while (i>0) {
4496        int j = (i-1)/2;
4497        abt::FSyscmd* p = elems[j];
4498        if (!bh_syscmd_ElemLt(row,*p)) {
4499            break;
4500        }
4501        elems[i]=p;
4502        i=j;
4503    }
4504    elems[i]=&row;
4505}
4506
4507// --- abt.FDb.bh_syscmd_curs.Reserve
4508void abt::_db_bh_syscmd_curs_Reserve(_db_bh_syscmd_curs &curs, int n) {
4509    if (n > curs.temp_max) {
4510        size_t old_size   = sizeof(void*) * curs.temp_max;
4511        size_t new_size   = sizeof(void*) * bh_syscmd_N();
4512        curs.temp_elems   = (abt::FSyscmd**)abt::lpool_ReallocMem(curs.temp_elems, old_size, new_size);
4513        if (!curs.temp_elems) {
4514            algo::FatalErrorExit("abt.cursor_out_of_memory  func:abt.FDb.bh_syscmd_curs.Reserve");
4515        }
4516        curs.temp_max       = bh_syscmd_N();
4517    }
4518}
4519
4520// --- abt.FDb.bh_syscmd_curs.Reset
4521// Reset cursor. If HEAP is non-empty, add its top element to CURS.
4522void abt::_db_bh_syscmd_curs_Reset(_db_bh_syscmd_curs &curs, abt::FDb &parent) {
4523    curs.parent       = &parent;
4524    _db_bh_syscmd_curs_Reserve(curs, bh_syscmd_N());
4525    curs.temp_n = 0;
4526    if (parent.bh_syscmd_n > 0) {
4527        abt::FSyscmd &first = *parent.bh_syscmd_elems[0];
4528        curs.temp_elems[0] = &first; // insert first element in heap
4529        curs.temp_n = 1;
4530    }
4531}
4532
4533// --- abt.FDb.bh_syscmd_curs.Next
4534// Advance cursor.
4535void abt::_db_bh_syscmd_curs_Next(_db_bh_syscmd_curs &curs) {
4536    abt::FSyscmd* *elems = curs.temp_elems;
4537    int n = curs.temp_n;
4538    if (n > 0) {
4539        // remove top element from heap
4540        abt::FSyscmd* dead = elems[0];
4541        int i       = 0;
4542        abt::FSyscmd* last = curs.temp_elems[n-1];
4543        // downheap last elem
4544        do {
4545            abt::FSyscmd* choose = last;
4546            int l         = i*2+1;
4547            if (l<n) {
4548                abt::FSyscmd* el = elems[l];
4549                int r     = l+1;
4550                r        -= r==n;
4551                abt::FSyscmd* er = elems[r];
4552                if (bh_syscmd_ElemLt(*er,*el)) {
4553                    el  = er;
4554                    l   = r;
4555                }
4556                bool b = bh_syscmd_ElemLt(*el,*last);
4557                if (b) choose = el;
4558                if (!b) l = n;
4559            }
4560            elems[i] = choose;
4561            i = l;
4562        } while (i < n);
4563        curs.temp_n = n-1;
4564        int index = dead->bh_syscmd_idx;
4565        i = (index*2+1);
4566        if (i < bh_syscmd_N()) {
4567            abt::FSyscmd &elem = *curs.parent->bh_syscmd_elems[i];
4568            _db_bh_syscmd_curs_Add(curs, elem);
4569        }
4570        if (i+1 < bh_syscmd_N()) {
4571            abt::FSyscmd &elem = *curs.parent->bh_syscmd_elems[i + 1];
4572            _db_bh_syscmd_curs_Add(curs, elem);
4573        }
4574    }
4575}

4851    _db.ind_ns_buckets_elems 	= (abt::FNs**)abt::lpool_AllocMem(sizeof(abt::FNs*)*_db.ind_ns_buckets_n); // initial buckets (abt.FDb.ind_ns)
4852    if (!_db.ind_ns_buckets_elems) {
4853        FatalErrorExit("out of memory"); // (abt.FDb.ind_ns)
4854    }
4855    memset(_db.ind_ns_buckets_elems, 0, sizeof(abt::FNs*)*_db.ind_ns_buckets_n); // (abt.FDb.ind_ns)
4856    _db.ccache = bool(false);
4857    _db.gcache = bool(false);
4858    // initialize LAry filestat (abt.FDb.filestat)
4859    _db.filestat_n = 0;
4860    memset(_db.filestat_lary, 0, sizeof(_db.filestat_lary)); // zero out all level pointers
4861    abt::FFilestat* filestat_first = (abt::FFilestat*)abt::lpool_AllocMem(sizeof(abt::FFilestat) * (u64(1)<<4));
4862    if (!filestat_first) {
4863        FatalErrorExit("out of memory");
4864    }
4865    for (int i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
4866        _db.filestat_lary[i]  = filestat_first;
4867        filestat_first    += 1ULL<<i;
4868    }
4869    // initialize hash table for abt::FFilestat;
4870    _db.ind_filestat_n             	= 0; // (abt.FDb.ind_filestat)
4871    _db.ind_filestat_buckets_n     	= 4; // (abt.FDb.ind_filestat)
4872    _db.ind_filestat_buckets_elems 	= (abt::FFilestat**)abt::lpool_AllocMem(sizeof(abt::FFilestat*)*_db.ind_filestat_buckets_n); // initial buckets (abt.FDb.ind_filestat)
4873    if (!_db.ind_filestat_buckets_elems) {
4874        FatalErrorExit("out of memory"); // (abt.FDb.ind_filestat)
4875    }
4876    memset(_db.ind_filestat_buckets_elems, 0, sizeof(abt::FFilestat*)*_db.ind_filestat_buckets_n); // (abt.FDb.ind_filestat)
4877    _db.zd_inclstack_head = NULL; // (abt.FDb.zd_inclstack)
4878    _db.zd_inclstack_n = 0; // (abt.FDb.zd_inclstack)
4879    _db.zd_inclstack_tail = NULL; // (abt.FDb.zd_inclstack)
4880    _db.tty = bool(false);
4881
4882    abt::InitReflection();
4883}

5072// --- abt.FSrcfile.zd_include.Insert
5073// Insert row into linked list. If row is already in linked list, do nothing.
5074void abt::zd_include_Insert(abt::FSrcfile& srcfile, abt::FInclude& row) {
5075    if (!zd_include_InLlistQ(row)) {
5076        abt::FInclude* old_tail = srcfile.zd_include_tail;
5077        row.zd_include_next = NULL;
5078        row.zd_include_prev = old_tail;
5079        srcfile.zd_include_tail = &row;
5080        abt::FInclude **new_row_a = &old_tail->zd_include_next;
5081        abt::FInclude **new_row_b = &srcfile.zd_include_head;
5082        abt::FInclude **new_row = old_tail ? new_row_a : new_row_b;
5083        *new_row = &row;
5084        srcfile.zd_include_n++;
5085    }
5086}
5087
5088// --- abt.FSrcfile.zd_include.Remove
5089// Remove element from index. If element is not in index, do nothing.
5090void abt::zd_include_Remove(abt::FSrcfile& srcfile, abt::FInclude& row) {
5091    if (zd_include_InLlistQ(row)) {
5092        abt::FInclude* old_head       = srcfile.zd_include_head;
5093        (void)old_head; // in case it's not used
5094        abt::FInclude* prev = row.zd_include_prev;
5095        abt::FInclude* next = row.zd_include_next;
5096        // if element is first, adjust list head; otherwise, adjust previous element's next
5097        abt::FInclude **new_next_a = &prev->zd_include_next;
5098        abt::FInclude **new_next_b = &srcfile.zd_include_head;
5099        abt::FInclude **new_next = prev ? new_next_a : new_next_b;
5100        *new_next = next;
5101        // if element is last, adjust list tail; otherwise, adjust next element's prev
5102        abt::FInclude **new_prev_a = &next->zd_include_prev;
5103        abt::FInclude **new_prev_b = &srcfile.zd_include_tail;
5104        abt::FInclude **new_prev = next ? new_prev_a : new_prev_b;
5105        *new_prev = prev;
5106        srcfile.zd_include_n--;
5107        row.zd_include_next=(abt::FInclude*)-1; // not-in-list
5108    }
5109}
5110
5111// --- abt.FSrcfile.zd_include.RemoveAll
5112// Empty the index. (The rows are not deleted)
5113void abt::zd_include_RemoveAll(abt::FSrcfile& srcfile) {
5114    abt::FInclude* row = srcfile.zd_include_head;
5115    srcfile.zd_include_head = NULL;
5116    srcfile.zd_include_tail = NULL;
5117    srcfile.zd_include_n = 0;
5118    while (row) {
5119        abt::FInclude* row_next = row->zd_include_next;
5120        row->zd_include_next  = (abt::FInclude*)-1;
5121        row->zd_include_prev  = NULL;
5122        row = row_next;
5123    }
5124}
5125
5126// --- abt.FSrcfile.zd_include.RemoveFirst
5127// If linked list is empty, return NULL. Otherwise unlink and return pointer to first element.
5128abt::FInclude* abt::zd_include_RemoveFirst(abt::FSrcfile& srcfile) {
5129    abt::FInclude *row = NULL;
5130    row = srcfile.zd_include_head;
5131    if (row) {
5132        abt::FInclude *next = row->zd_include_next;
5133        srcfile.zd_include_head = next;
5134        abt::FInclude **new_end_a = &next->zd_include_prev;
5135        abt::FInclude **new_end_b = &srcfile.zd_include_tail;
5136        abt::FInclude **new_end = next ? new_end_a : new_end_b;
5137        *new_end = NULL;
5138        srcfile.zd_include_n--;
5139        row->zd_include_next = (abt::FInclude*)-1; // mark as not-in-list
5140    }
5141    return row;
5142}

5196// --- abt.FSyscmd.c_prior.Insert
5197// Insert pointer to row into array. Row must not already be in array.
5198// If pointer is already in the array, it may be inserted twice.
5199void abt::c_prior_Insert(abt::FSyscmd& syscmd, abt::FSyscmddep& row) {
5200    if (bool_Update(row.syscmd_c_prior_in_ary,true)) {
5201        // reserve space
5202        c_prior_Reserve(syscmd, 1);
5203        u32 n  = syscmd.c_prior_n;
5204        u32 at = n;
5205        abt::FSyscmddep* *elems = syscmd.c_prior_elems;
5206        elems[at] = &row;
5207        syscmd.c_prior_n = n+1;
5208
5209    }
5210}
5211
5212// --- abt.FSyscmd.c_prior.InsertMaybe
5213// Insert pointer to row in array.
5214// If row is already in the array, do nothing.
5215// Return value: whether element was inserted into array.
5216bool abt::c_prior_InsertMaybe(abt::FSyscmd& syscmd, abt::FSyscmddep& row) {
5217    bool retval = !row.syscmd_c_prior_in_ary;
5218    c_prior_Insert(syscmd,row); // check is performed in _Insert again
5219    return retval;
5220}
5221
5222// --- abt.FSyscmd.c_prior.Remove
5223// Find element using linear scan. If element is in array, remove, otherwise do nothing
5224void abt::c_prior_Remove(abt::FSyscmd& syscmd, abt::FSyscmddep& row) {
5225    if (bool_Update(row.syscmd_c_prior_in_ary,false)) {
5226        int lim = syscmd.c_prior_n;
5227        abt::FSyscmddep* *elems = syscmd.c_prior_elems;
5228        // search backward, so that most recently added element is found first.
5229        // if found, shift array.
5230        for (int i = lim-1; i>=0; i--) {
5231            abt::FSyscmddep* elem = elems[i]; // fetch element
5232            if (elem == &row) {
5233                int j = i + 1;
5234                size_t nbytes = sizeof(abt::FSyscmddep*) * (lim - j);
5235                memmove(elems + i, elems + j, nbytes);
5236                syscmd.c_prior_n = lim - 1;
5237                break;
5238            }
5239        }
5240    }
5241}
5242
5243// --- abt.FSyscmd.c_prior.Reserve
5244// Reserve space in index for N more elements;
5245void abt::c_prior_Reserve(abt::FSyscmd& syscmd, u32 n) {
5246    u32 old_max = syscmd.c_prior_max;
5247    if (UNLIKELY(syscmd.c_prior_n + n > old_max)) {
5248        u32 new_max  = u32_Max(4, old_max * 2);
5249        u32 old_size = old_max * sizeof(abt::FSyscmddep*);
5250        u32 new_size = new_max * sizeof(abt::FSyscmddep*);
5251        void *new_mem = abt::lpool_ReallocMem(syscmd.c_prior_elems, old_size, new_size);
5252        if (UNLIKELY(!new_mem)) {
5253            FatalErrorExit("abt.out_of_memory  field:abt.FSyscmd.c_prior");
5254        }
5255        syscmd.c_prior_elems = (abt::FSyscmddep**)new_mem;
5256        syscmd.c_prior_max = new_max;
5257    }
5258}
5259
5260// --- abt.FSyscmd.c_next.Insert
5261// Insert pointer to row into array. Row must not already be in array.
5262// If pointer is already in the array, it may be inserted twice.
5263void abt::c_next_Insert(abt::FSyscmd& syscmd, abt::FSyscmddep& row) {
5264    if (bool_Update(row.syscmd_c_next_in_ary,true)) {
5265        // reserve space
5266        c_next_Reserve(syscmd, 1);
5267        u32 n  = syscmd.c_next_n;
5268        u32 at = n;
5269        abt::FSyscmddep* *elems = syscmd.c_next_elems;
5270        elems[at] = &row;
5271        syscmd.c_next_n = n+1;
5272
5273    }
5274}
5275
5276// --- abt.FSyscmd.c_next.InsertMaybe
5277// Insert pointer to row in array.
5278// If row is already in the array, do nothing.
5279// Return value: whether element was inserted into array.
5280bool abt::c_next_InsertMaybe(abt::FSyscmd& syscmd, abt::FSyscmddep& row) {
5281    bool retval = !row.syscmd_c_next_in_ary;
5282    c_next_Insert(syscmd,row); // check is performed in _Insert again
5283    return retval;
5284}

5286// --- abt.FSyscmd.c_next.Remove
5287// Find element using linear scan. If element is in array, remove, otherwise do nothing
5288void abt::c_next_Remove(abt::FSyscmd& syscmd, abt::FSyscmddep& row) {
5289    if (bool_Update(row.syscmd_c_next_in_ary,false)) {
5290        int lim = syscmd.c_next_n;
5291        abt::FSyscmddep* *elems = syscmd.c_next_elems;
5292        // search backward, so that most recently added element is found first.
5293        // if found, shift array.
5294        for (int i = lim-1; i>=0; i--) {
5295            abt::FSyscmddep* elem = elems[i]; // fetch element
5296            if (elem == &row) {
5297                int j = i + 1;
5298                size_t nbytes = sizeof(abt::FSyscmddep*) * (lim - j);
5299                memmove(elems + i, elems + j, nbytes);
5300                syscmd.c_next_n = lim - 1;
5301                break;
5302            }
5303        }
5304    }
5305}
5306
5307// --- abt.FSyscmd.c_next.Reserve
5308// Reserve space in index for N more elements;
5309void abt::c_next_Reserve(abt::FSyscmd& syscmd, u32 n) {
5310    u32 old_max = syscmd.c_next_max;
5311    if (UNLIKELY(syscmd.c_next_n + n > old_max)) {
5312        u32 new_max  = u32_Max(4, old_max * 2);
5313        u32 old_size = old_max * sizeof(abt::FSyscmddep*);
5314        u32 new_size = new_max * sizeof(abt::FSyscmddep*);
5315        void *new_mem = abt::lpool_ReallocMem(syscmd.c_next_elems, old_size, new_size);
5316        if (UNLIKELY(!new_mem)) {
5317            FatalErrorExit("abt.out_of_memory  field:abt.FSyscmd.c_next");
5318        }
5319        syscmd.c_next_elems = (abt::FSyscmddep**)new_mem;
5320        syscmd.c_next_max = new_max;
5321    }
5322}

5326void abt::FSyscmd_Init(abt::FSyscmd& syscmd) {
5327    syscmd.syscmd = i64(0);
5328    syscmd.pid = i32(0);
5329    syscmd.status = i32(0);
5330    syscmd.nprereq = i32(0);
5331    syscmd.fail_prereq = bool(false);
5332    syscmd.completed = bool(false);
5333    syscmd.maxtime = i32(0);
5334    syscmd.c_prior_elems = NULL; // (abt.FSyscmd.c_prior)
5335    syscmd.c_prior_n = 0; // (abt.FSyscmd.c_prior)
5336    syscmd.c_prior_max = 0; // (abt.FSyscmd.c_prior)
5337    syscmd.c_next_elems = NULL; // (abt.FSyscmd.c_next)
5338    syscmd.c_next_n = 0; // (abt.FSyscmd.c_next)
5339    syscmd.c_next_max = 0; // (abt.FSyscmd.c_next)
5340    syscmd.rowid = i32(0);
5341    syscmd.line_n = u64(0);
5342    syscmd.redirect = bool(true);
5343    syscmd.ind_syscmd_next = (abt::FSyscmd*)-1; // (abt.FDb.ind_syscmd) not-in-hash
5344    syscmd.ind_running_next = (abt::FSyscmd*)-1; // (abt.FDb.ind_running) not-in-hash
5345    syscmd.bh_syscmd_idx = -1; // (abt.FDb.bh_syscmd) not-in-heap
5346}
5347
5348// --- abt.FSyscmd..Uninit
5349void abt::FSyscmd_Uninit(abt::FSyscmd& syscmd) {
5350    abt::FSyscmd &row = syscmd; (void)row;
5351    ind_syscmd_Remove(row); // remove syscmd from index ind_syscmd
5352    ind_running_Remove(row); // remove syscmd from index ind_running
5353    bh_syscmd_Remove(row); // remove syscmd from index bh_syscmd
5354
5355    // abt.FSyscmd.c_next.Uninit (Ptrary)  //
5356    abt::lpool_FreeMem(syscmd.c_next_elems, sizeof(abt::FSyscmddep*)*syscmd.c_next_max); // (abt.FSyscmd.c_next)
5357
5358    // abt.FSyscmd.c_prior.Uninit (Ptrary)  //
5359    abt::lpool_FreeMem(syscmd.c_prior_elems, sizeof(abt::FSyscmddep*)*syscmd.c_prior_max); // (abt.FSyscmd.c_prior)
5360}

5366    out.parent = row.parent;

5372    row.child = in.child;
5373    row.parent = in.parent;
5374}

5376// --- abt.FSyscmddep..Uninit
5377void abt::FSyscmddep_Uninit(abt::FSyscmddep& syscmddep) {
5378    abt::FSyscmddep &row = syscmddep; (void)row;
5379    abt::FSyscmd* p_child = abt::ind_syscmd_Find(row.child);
5380    if (p_child)  {
5381        c_prior_Remove(*p_child, row);// remove syscmddep from index c_prior
5382    }
5383    abt::FSyscmd* p_parent = abt::ind_syscmd_Find(row.parent);
5384    if (p_parent)  {
5385        c_next_Remove(*p_parent, row);// remove syscmddep from index c_next
5386    }
5387}

5456// --- abt.FTarget.c_targsrc.Insert
5457// Insert pointer to row into array. Row must not already be in array.
5458// If pointer is already in the array, it may be inserted twice.
5459void abt::c_targsrc_Insert(abt::FTarget& target, abt::FTargsrc& row) {
5460    if (bool_Update(row.target_c_targsrc_in_ary,true)) {
5461        // reserve space
5462        c_targsrc_Reserve(target, 1);
5463        u32 n  = target.c_targsrc_n;
5464        u32 at = n;
5465        abt::FTargsrc* *elems = target.c_targsrc_elems;
5466        elems[at] = &row;
5467        target.c_targsrc_n = n+1;
5468
5469    }
5470}
5471
5472// --- abt.FTarget.c_targsrc.InsertMaybe
5473// Insert pointer to row in array.
5474// If row is already in the array, do nothing.
5475// Return value: whether element was inserted into array.
5476bool abt::c_targsrc_InsertMaybe(abt::FTarget& target, abt::FTargsrc& row) {
5477    bool retval = !row.target_c_targsrc_in_ary;
5478    c_targsrc_Insert(target,row); // check is performed in _Insert again
5479    return retval;
5480}
5481
5482// --- abt.FTarget.c_targsrc.Remove
5483// Find element using linear scan. If element is in array, remove, otherwise do nothing
5484void abt::c_targsrc_Remove(abt::FTarget& target, abt::FTargsrc& row) {
5485    if (bool_Update(row.target_c_targsrc_in_ary,false)) {
5486        int lim = target.c_targsrc_n;
5487        abt::FTargsrc* *elems = target.c_targsrc_elems;
5488        // search backward, so that most recently added element is found first.
5489        // if found, shift array.
5490        for (int i = lim-1; i>=0; i--) {
5491            abt::FTargsrc* elem = elems[i]; // fetch element
5492            if (elem == &row) {
5493                int j = i + 1;
5494                size_t nbytes = sizeof(abt::FTargsrc*) * (lim - j);
5495                memmove(elems + i, elems + j, nbytes);
5496                target.c_targsrc_n = lim - 1;
5497                break;
5498            }
5499        }
5500    }
5501}
5502
5503// --- abt.FTarget.c_targsrc.Reserve
5504// Reserve space in index for N more elements;
5505void abt::c_targsrc_Reserve(abt::FTarget& target, u32 n) {
5506    u32 old_max = target.c_targsrc_max;
5507    if (UNLIKELY(target.c_targsrc_n + n > old_max)) {
5508        u32 new_max  = u32_Max(4, old_max * 2);
5509        u32 old_size = old_max * sizeof(abt::FTargsrc*);
5510        u32 new_size = new_max * sizeof(abt::FTargsrc*);
5511        void *new_mem = abt::lpool_ReallocMem(target.c_targsrc_elems, old_size, new_size);
5512        if (UNLIKELY(!new_mem)) {
5513            FatalErrorExit("abt.out_of_memory  field:abt.FTarget.c_targsrc");
5514        }
5515        target.c_targsrc_elems = (abt::FTargsrc**)new_mem;
5516        target.c_targsrc_max = new_max;
5517    }
5518}
5519
5520// --- abt.FTarget.c_srcfile.Insert
5521// Insert pointer to row into array. Row must not already be in array.
5522// If pointer is already in the array, it may be inserted twice.
5523void abt::c_srcfile_Insert(abt::FTarget& target, abt::FSrcfile& row) {
5524    // reserve space
5525    c_srcfile_Reserve(target, 1);
5526    u32 n  = target.c_srcfile_n;
5527    u32 at = n;
5528    abt::FSrcfile* *elems = target.c_srcfile_elems;
5529    elems[at] = &row;
5530    target.c_srcfile_n = n+1;
5531
5532}

5534// --- abt.FTarget.c_srcfile.ScanInsertMaybe
5535// Insert pointer to row in array.
5536// If row is already in the array, do nothing.
5537// Linear search is used to locate the element.
5538// Return value: whether element was inserted into array.
5539bool abt::c_srcfile_ScanInsertMaybe(abt::FTarget& target, abt::FSrcfile& row) {
5540    bool retval = true;
5541    u32 n  = target.c_srcfile_n;
5542    for (u32 i = 0; i < n; i++) {
5543        if (target.c_srcfile_elems[i] == &row) {
5544            retval = false;
5545            break;
5546        }
5547    }
5548    if (retval) {
5549        // reserve space
5550        c_srcfile_Reserve(target, 1);
5551        target.c_srcfile_elems[n] = &row;
5552        target.c_srcfile_n = n+1;
5553    }
5554    return retval;
5555}

5561    abt::FSrcfile* *elems = target.c_srcfile_elems;
5562    // search backward, so that most recently added element is found first.
5563    // if found, shift array.
5564    for (int i = lim-1; i>=0; i--) {
5565        abt::FSrcfile* elem = elems[i]; // fetch element
5566        if (elem == &row) {
5567            int j = i + 1;
5568            size_t nbytes = sizeof(abt::FSrcfile*) * (lim - j);
5569            memmove(elems + i, elems + j, nbytes);
5570            target.c_srcfile_n = lim - 1;
5571            break;
5572        }
5573    }
5574}

5810// If row is already in the array, do nothing.
5811// Linear search is used to locate the element.
5812// Return value: whether element was inserted into array.
5813bool abt::c_alllib_ScanInsertMaybe(abt::FTarget& target, abt::FSyslib& row) {
5814    bool retval = true;
5815    u32 n  = target.c_alllib_n;
5816    for (u32 i = 0; i < n; i++) {
5817        if (target.c_alllib_elems[i] == &row) {
5818            retval = false;
5819            break;
5820        }
5821    }
5822    if (retval) {
5823        // reserve space
5824        c_alllib_Reserve(target, 1);
5825        target.c_alllib_elems[n] = &row;
5826        target.c_alllib_n = n+1;
5827    }
5828    return retval;
5829}
5830
5831// --- abt.FTarget.c_alllib.Remove
5832// Find element using linear scan. If element is in array, remove, otherwise do nothing
5833void abt::c_alllib_Remove(abt::FTarget& target, abt::FSyslib& row) {
5834    int lim = target.c_alllib_n;
5835    abt::FSyslib* *elems = target.c_alllib_elems;
5836    // search backward, so that most recently added element is found first.
5837    // if found, shift array.
5838    for (int i = lim-1; i>=0; i--) {
5839        abt::FSyslib* elem = elems[i]; // fetch element
5840        if (elem == &row) {
5841            int j = i + 1;
5842            size_t nbytes = sizeof(abt::FSyslib*) * (lim - j);
5843            memmove(elems + i, elems + j, nbytes);
5844            target.c_alllib_n = lim - 1;
5845            break;
5846        }
5847    }
5848}
5849
5850// --- abt.FTarget.c_alllib.Reserve
5851// Reserve space in index for N more elements;
5852void abt::c_alllib_Reserve(abt::FTarget& target, u32 n) {
5853    u32 old_max = target.c_alllib_max;
5854    if (UNLIKELY(target.c_alllib_n + n > old_max)) {
5855        u32 new_max  = u32_Max(4, old_max * 2);
5856        u32 old_size = old_max * sizeof(abt::FSyslib*);
5857        u32 new_size = new_max * sizeof(abt::FSyslib*);
5858        void *new_mem = abt::lpool_ReallocMem(target.c_alllib_elems, old_size, new_size);
5859        if (UNLIKELY(!new_mem)) {
5860            FatalErrorExit("abt.out_of_memory  field:abt.FTarget.c_alllib");
5861        }
5862        target.c_alllib_elems = (abt::FSyslib**)new_mem;
5863        target.c_alllib_max = new_max;
5864    }
5865}
5866
5867// --- abt.FTarget..Init
5868// Set all fields to initial values.
5869void abt::FTarget_Init(abt::FTarget& target) {
5870    target.ood = bool(false);
5871    target.targ_start = NULL;
5872    target.targ_compile = NULL;
5873    target.targ_link = NULL;
5874    target.targ_end = NULL;
5875    target.c_targsrc_elems = NULL; // (abt.FTarget.c_targsrc)
5876    target.c_targsrc_n = 0; // (abt.FTarget.c_targsrc)
5877    target.c_targsrc_max = 0; // (abt.FTarget.c_targsrc)
5878    target.c_srcfile_elems = NULL; // (abt.FTarget.c_srcfile)
5879    target.c_srcfile_n = 0; // (abt.FTarget.c_srcfile)
5880    target.c_srcfile_max = 0; // (abt.FTarget.c_srcfile)
5881    target.c_targdep_elems = NULL; // (abt.FTarget.c_targdep)
5882    target.c_targdep_n = 0; // (abt.FTarget.c_targdep)
5883    target.c_targdep_max = 0; // (abt.FTarget.c_targdep)
5884    target.ood_visited = bool(false);
5885    target.c_targsyslib_elems = NULL; // (abt.FTarget.c_targsyslib)
5886    target.c_targsyslib_n = 0; // (abt.FTarget.c_targsyslib)
5887    target.c_targsyslib_max = 0; // (abt.FTarget.c_targsyslib)
5888    target.c_alldep_elems = NULL; // (abt.FTarget.c_alldep)
5889    target.c_alldep_n = 0; // (abt.FTarget.c_alldep)
5890    target.c_alldep_max = 0; // (abt.FTarget.c_alldep)
5891    target.c_alllib_elems = NULL; // (abt.FTarget.c_alllib)
5892    target.c_alllib_n = 0; // (abt.FTarget.c_alllib)
5893    target.c_alllib_max = 0; // (abt.FTarget.c_alllib)
5894    target.p_ns = NULL;
5895    target.libdep_visited = bool(false);
5896    target.ind_target_next = (abt::FTarget*)-1; // (abt.FDb.ind_target) not-in-hash
5897    target.zs_sel_target_next = (abt::FTarget*)-1; // (abt.FDb.zs_sel_target) not-in-list
5898    target.zs_origsel_target_next = (abt::FTarget*)-1; // (abt.FDb.zs_origsel_target) not-in-list
5899}
5900
5901// --- abt.FTarget..Uninit
5902void abt::FTarget_Uninit(abt::FTarget& target) {
5903    abt::FTarget &row = target; (void)row;
5904    ind_target_Remove(row); // remove target from index ind_target
5905    zs_sel_target_Remove(row); // remove target from index zs_sel_target
5906    zs_origsel_target_Remove(row); // remove target from index zs_origsel_target
5907
5908    // abt.FTarget.c_alllib.Uninit (Ptrary)  //Transitive closure of all libs for this target
5909    abt::lpool_FreeMem(target.c_alllib_elems, sizeof(abt::FSyslib*)*target.c_alllib_max); // (abt.FTarget.c_alllib)
5910
5911    // abt.FTarget.c_alldep.Uninit (Ptrary)  //Transitive closure of all dependencies for this target
5912    abt::lpool_FreeMem(target.c_alldep_elems, sizeof(abt::FTarget*)*target.c_alldep_max); // (abt.FTarget.c_alldep)
5913
5914    // abt.FTarget.c_targsyslib.Uninit (Ptrary)  //
5915    abt::lpool_FreeMem(target.c_targsyslib_elems, sizeof(abt::FTargsyslib*)*target.c_targsyslib_max); // (abt.FTarget.c_targsyslib)
5916
5917    // abt.FTarget.c_targdep.Uninit (Ptrary)  //
5918    abt::lpool_FreeMem(target.c_targdep_elems, sizeof(abt::FTargdep*)*target.c_targdep_max); // (abt.FTarget.c_targdep)
5919
5920    // abt.FTarget.c_srcfile.Uninit (Ptrary)  //
5921    abt::lpool_FreeMem(target.c_srcfile_elems, sizeof(abt::FSrcfile*)*target.c_srcfile_max); // (abt.FTarget.c_srcfile)
5922
5923    // abt.FTarget.c_targsrc.Uninit (Ptrary)  //
5924    abt::lpool_FreeMem(target.c_targsrc_elems, sizeof(abt::FTargsrc*)*target.c_targsrc_max); // (abt.FTarget.c_targsrc)
5925}

6110// --- abt.FieldId.value.ToCstr
6111// Convert numeric value of field to one of predefined string constants.
6112// If string is found, return a static C string. Otherwise, return NULL.
6113const char* abt::value_ToCstr(const abt::FieldId& parent) {
6114    const char *ret = NULL;
6115    switch(value_GetEnum(parent)) {
6116        case abt_FieldId_value             : ret = "value";  break;
6117    }
6118    return ret;
6119}
6120
6121// --- abt.FieldId.value.Print
6122// Convert value to a string. First, attempt conversion to a known string.
6123// If no string matches, print value as a numeric value.
6124void abt::value_Print(const abt::FieldId& parent, algo::cstring &lhs) {
6125    const char *strval = value_ToCstr(parent);
6126    if (strval) {
6127        lhs << strval;
6128    } else {
6129        lhs << parent.value;
6130    }
6131}
6132
6133// --- abt.FieldId.value.SetStrptrMaybe
6134// Convert string to field.
6135// If the string is invalid, do not modify field and return false.
6136// In case of success, return true
6137bool abt::value_SetStrptrMaybe(abt::FieldId& parent, algo::strptr rhs) {
6138    bool ret = false;
6139    switch (elems_N(rhs)) {
6140        case 5: {
6141            switch (u64(algo::ReadLE32(rhs.elems))|(u64(rhs[4])<<32)) {
6142                case LE_STR5('v','a','l','u','e'): {
6143                    value_SetEnum(parent,abt_FieldId_value); ret = true; break;
6144                }
6145            }
6146            break;
6147        }
6148    }
6149    return ret;
6150}
6151
6152// --- abt.FieldId.value.SetStrptr
6153// Convert string to field.
6154// If the string is invalid, set numeric value to DFLT
6155void abt::value_SetStrptr(abt::FieldId& parent, algo::strptr rhs, abt_FieldIdEnum dflt) {
6156    if (!value_SetStrptrMaybe(parent,rhs)) value_SetEnum(parent,dflt);
6157}
6158
6159// --- abt.FieldId.value.ReadStrptrMaybe
6160// Convert string to field. Return success value
6161bool abt::value_ReadStrptrMaybe(abt::FieldId& parent, algo::strptr rhs) {
6162    bool retval = false;
6163    retval = value_SetStrptrMaybe(parent,rhs); // try symbol conversion
6164    if (!retval) { // didn't work? try reading as underlying type
6165        retval = i32_ReadStrptrMaybe(parent.value,rhs);
6166    }
6167    return retval;
6168}
6169
6170// --- abt.FieldId..ReadStrptrMaybe
6171// Read fields of abt::FieldId from an ascii string.
6172// The format of the string is the format of the abt::FieldId's only field
6173bool abt::FieldId_ReadStrptrMaybe(abt::FieldId &parent, algo::strptr in_str) {
6174    bool retval = true;
6175    retval = retval && value_ReadStrptrMaybe(parent, in_str);
6176    return retval;
6177}

6182void abt::FieldId_Print(abt::FieldId& row, algo::cstring& str) {

6186// --- abt.TableId.value.ToCstr
6187// Convert numeric value of field to one of predefined string constants.
6188// If string is found, return a static C string. Otherwise, return NULL.
6189const char* abt::value_ToCstr(const abt::TableId& parent) {
6190    const char *ret = NULL;
6191    switch(value_GetEnum(parent)) {
6192        case abt_TableId_dev_Arch          : ret = "dev.Arch";  break;
6193        case abt_TableId_dev_Cfg           : ret = "dev.Cfg";  break;
6194        case abt_TableId_dev_Compiler      : ret = "dev.Compiler";  break;
6195        case abt_TableId_dev_Include       : ret = "dev.Include";  break;
6196        case abt_TableId_dmmeta_Ns         : ret = "dmmeta.Ns";  break;
6197        case abt_TableId_dev_Syscmd        : ret = "dev.Syscmd";  break;
6198        case abt_TableId_dev_Syscmddep     : ret = "dev.Syscmddep";  break;
6199        case abt_TableId_dev_Syslib        : ret = "dev.Syslib";  break;
6200        case abt_TableId_dev_Targdep       : ret = "dev.Targdep";  break;
6201        case abt_TableId_dev_Target        : ret = "dev.Target";  break;
6202        case abt_TableId_dev_Targsrc       : ret = "dev.Targsrc";  break;
6203        case abt_TableId_dev_Targsyslib    : ret = "dev.Targsyslib";  break;
6204        case abt_TableId_dev_ToolOpt       : ret = "dev.ToolOpt";  break;
6205        case abt_TableId_dev_Uname         : ret = "dev.Uname";  break;
6206    }

6210// --- abt.TableId.value.Print
6211// Convert value to a string. First, attempt conversion to a known string.
6212// If no string matches, print value as a numeric value.
6213void abt::value_Print(const abt::TableId& parent, algo::cstring &lhs) {
6214    const char *strval = value_ToCstr(parent);
6215    if (strval) {
6216        lhs << strval;
6217    } else {
6218        lhs << parent.value;
6219    }

6221
6222// --- abt.TableId.value.SetStrptrMaybe
6223// Convert string to field.
6224// If the string is invalid, do not modify field and return false.
6225// In case of success, return true
6226bool abt::value_SetStrptrMaybe(abt::TableId& parent, algo::strptr rhs) {
6227    bool ret = false;
6228    switch (elems_N(rhs)) {
6229        case 7: {
6230            switch (u64(algo::ReadLE32(rhs.elems))|(u64(algo::ReadLE16(rhs.elems+4))<<32)|(u64(rhs[6])<<48)) {
6231                case LE_STR7('d','e','v','.','C','f','g'): {
6232                    value_SetEnum(parent,abt_TableId_dev_Cfg); ret = true; break;
6233                }
6234                case LE_STR7('d','e','v','.','c','f','g'): {
6235                    value_SetEnum(parent,abt_TableId_dev_cfg); ret = true; break;
6236                }
6237            }
6238            break;
6239        }
6240        case 8: {
6241            switch (algo::ReadLE64(rhs.elems)) {
6242                case LE_STR8('d','e','v','.','A','r','c','h'): {
6243                    value_SetEnum(parent,abt_TableId_dev_Arch); ret = true; break;
6244                }
6245                case LE_STR8('d','e','v','.','a','r','c','h'): {
6246                    value_SetEnum(parent,abt_TableId_dev_arch); ret = true; break;
6247                }
6248            }
6249            break;
6250        }
6251        case 9: {
6252            switch (algo::ReadLE64(rhs.elems)) {
6253                case LE_STR8('d','e','v','.','U','n','a','m'): {
6254                    if (memcmp(rhs.elems+8,"e",1)==0) { value_SetEnum(parent,abt_TableId_dev_Uname); ret = true; break; }
6255                    break;
6256                }
6257                case LE_STR8('d','e','v','.','u','n','a','m'): {
6258                    if (memcmp(rhs.elems+8,"e",1)==0) { value_SetEnum(parent,abt_TableId_dev_uname); ret = true; break; }
6259                    break;
6260                }
6261                case LE_STR8('d','m','m','e','t','a','.','N'): {
6262                    if (memcmp(rhs.elems+8,"s",1)==0) { value_SetEnum(parent,abt_TableId_dmmeta_Ns); ret = true; break; }
6263                    break;
6264                }
6265                case LE_STR8('d','m','m','e','t','a','.','n'): {
6266                    if (memcmp(rhs.elems+8,"s",1)==0) { value_SetEnum(parent,abt_TableId_dmmeta_ns); ret = true; break; }
6267                    break;
6268                }
6269            }
6270            break;
6271        }
6272        case 10: {
6273            switch (algo::ReadLE64(rhs.elems)) {
6274                case LE_STR8('d','e','v','.','S','y','s','c'): {
6275                    if (memcmp(rhs.elems+8,"md",2)==0) { value_SetEnum(parent,abt_TableId_dev_Syscmd); ret = true; break; }
6276                    break;
6277                }
6278                case LE_STR8('d','e','v','.','S','y','s','l'): {
6279                    if (memcmp(rhs.elems+8,"ib",2)==0) { value_SetEnum(parent,abt_TableId_dev_Syslib); ret = true; break; }
6280                    break;
6281                }
6282                case LE_STR8('d','e','v','.','T','a','r','g'): {
6283                    if (memcmp(rhs.elems+8,"et",2)==0) { value_SetEnum(parent,abt_TableId_dev_Target); ret = true; break; }
6284                    break;
6285                }
6286                case LE_STR8('d','e','v','.','s','y','s','c'): {
6287                    if (memcmp(rhs.elems+8,"md",2)==0) { value_SetEnum(parent,abt_TableId_dev_syscmd); ret = true; break; }
6288                    break;
6289                }
6290                case LE_STR8('d','e','v','.','s','y','s','l'): {
6291                    if (memcmp(rhs.elems+8,"ib",2)==0) { value_SetEnum(parent,abt_TableId_dev_syslib); ret = true; break; }
6292                    break;
6293                }
6294                case LE_STR8('d','e','v','.','t','a','r','g'): {
6295                    if (memcmp(rhs.elems+8,"et",2)==0) { value_SetEnum(parent,abt_TableId_dev_target); ret = true; break; }
6296                    break;
6297                }
6298            }
6299            break;
6300        }
6301        case 11: {
6302            switch (algo::ReadLE64(rhs.elems)) {
6303                case LE_STR8('d','e','v','.','I','n','c','l'): {
6304                    if (memcmp(rhs.elems+8,"ude",3)==0) { value_SetEnum(parent,abt_TableId_dev_Include); ret = true; break; }
6305                    break;
6306                }
6307                case LE_STR8('d','e','v','.','T','a','r','g'): {
6308                    if (memcmp(rhs.elems+8,"dep",3)==0) { value_SetEnum(parent,abt_TableId_dev_Targdep); ret = true; break; }
6309                    if (memcmp(rhs.elems+8,"src",3)==0) { value_SetEnum(parent,abt_TableId_dev_Targsrc); ret = true; break; }
6310                    break;
6311                }
6312                case LE_STR8('d','e','v','.','T','o','o','l'): {
6313                    if (memcmp(rhs.elems+8,"Opt",3)==0) { value_SetEnum(parent,abt_TableId_dev_ToolOpt); ret = true; break; }
6314                    break;
6315                }
6316                case LE_STR8('d','e','v','.','i','n','c','l'): {
6317                    if (memcmp(rhs.elems+8,"ude",3)==0) { value_SetEnum(parent,abt_TableId_dev_include); ret = true; break; }
6318                    break;
6319                }
6320                case LE_STR8('d','e','v','.','t','a','r','g'): {
6321                    if (memcmp(rhs.elems+8,"dep",3)==0) { value_SetEnum(parent,abt_TableId_dev_targdep); ret = true; break; }
6322                    if (memcmp(rhs.elems+8,"src",3)==0) { value_SetEnum(parent,abt_TableId_dev_targsrc); ret = true; break; }
6323                    break;
6324                }
6325            }
6326            break;
6327        }
6328        case 12: {
6329            switch (algo::ReadLE64(rhs.elems)) {
6330                case LE_STR8('d','e','v','.','C','o','m','p'): {
6331                    if (memcmp(rhs.elems+8,"iler",4)==0) { value_SetEnum(parent,abt_TableId_dev_Compiler); ret = true; break; }
6332                    break;
6333                }
6334                case LE_STR8('d','e','v','.','c','o','m','p'): {
6335                    if (memcmp(rhs.elems+8,"iler",4)==0) { value_SetEnum(parent,abt_TableId_dev_compiler); ret = true; break; }
6336                    break;
6337                }

6339                    if (memcmp(rhs.elems+8,"_opt",4)==0) { value_SetEnum(parent,abt_TableId_dev_tool_opt); ret = true; break; }
6340                    break;
6341                }
6342            }
6343            break;
6344        }
6345        case 13: {
6346            switch (algo::ReadLE64(rhs.elems)) {
6347                case LE_STR8('d','e','v','.','S','y','s','c'): {
6348                    if (memcmp(rhs.elems+8,"mddep",5)==0) { value_SetEnum(parent,abt_TableId_dev_Syscmddep); ret = true; break; }
6349                    break;
6350                }
6351                case LE_STR8('d','e','v','.','s','y','s','c'): {
6352                    if (memcmp(rhs.elems+8,"mddep",5)==0) { value_SetEnum(parent,abt_TableId_dev_syscmddep); ret = true; break; }
6353                    break;
6354                }
6355            }
6356            break;
6357        }
6358        case 14: {
6359            switch (algo::ReadLE64(rhs.elems)) {
6360                case LE_STR8('d','e','v','.','T','a','r','g'): {
6361                    if (memcmp(rhs.elems+8,"syslib",6)==0) { value_SetEnum(parent,abt_TableId_dev_Targsyslib); ret = true; break; }
6362                    break;
6363                }
6364                case LE_STR8('d','e','v','.','t','a','r','g'): {
6365                    if (memcmp(rhs.elems+8,"syslib",6)==0) { value_SetEnum(parent,abt_TableId_dev_targsyslib); ret = true; break; }
6366                    break;
6367                }
6368            }
6369            break;
6370        }
6371    }
6372    return ret;
6373}
6374
6375// --- abt.TableId.value.SetStrptr
6376// Convert string to field.
6377// If the string is invalid, set numeric value to DFLT
6378void abt::value_SetStrptr(abt::TableId& parent, algo::strptr rhs, abt_TableIdEnum dflt) {
6379    if (!value_SetStrptrMaybe(parent,rhs)) value_SetEnum(parent,dflt);
6380}
6381
6382// --- abt.TableId.value.ReadStrptrMaybe
6383// Convert string to field. Return success value
6384bool abt::value_ReadStrptrMaybe(abt::TableId& parent, algo::strptr rhs) {
6385    bool retval = false;
6386    retval = value_SetStrptrMaybe(parent,rhs); // try symbol conversion
6387    if (!retval) { // didn't work? try reading as underlying type
6388        retval = i32_ReadStrptrMaybe(parent.value,rhs);
6389    }
6390    return retval;
6391}
6392
6393// --- abt.TableId..ReadStrptrMaybe
6394// Read fields of abt::TableId from an ascii string.
6395// The format of the string is the format of the abt::TableId's only field
6396bool abt::TableId_ReadStrptrMaybe(abt::TableId &parent, algo::strptr in_str) {
6397    bool retval = true;
6398    retval = retval && value_ReadStrptrMaybe(parent, in_str);
6399    return retval;
6400}

6403// print string representation of ROW to string STR
6404// cfmt:abt.TableId.String  printfmt:Raw
6405void abt::TableId_Print(abt::TableId& row, algo::cstring& str) {
6406    abt::value_Print(row, str);
6407}

6411}

6413// --- abt...StaticCheck
6414void abt::StaticCheck() {
6415    algo_assert(_offset_of(abt::FieldId, value) + sizeof(((abt::FieldId*)0)->value) == sizeof(abt::FieldId));
6416}

6418// --- abt...main
6419int main(int argc, char **argv) {
6420    try {
6421        lib_json::FDb_Init();
6422        algo_lib::FDb_Init();
6423        abt::FDb_Init();
6424        algo_lib::_db.argc = argc;
6425        algo_lib::_db.argv = argv;
6426        algo_lib::IohookInit();
6427        abt::ReadArgv(); // dmmeta.main:abt
6428        abt::Main(); // user-defined main
6429    } catch(algo_lib::ErrorX &x) {
6430        prerr("abt.error  " << x); // there may be additional hints in DetachBadTags
6431        algo_lib::_db.exit_code = 1;
6432    }
6433    if (algo_lib::_db.last_signal) {
6434        algo_lib::_db.exit_code = 1;
6435    }
6436    try {
6437        abt::FDb_Uninit();
6438        algo_lib::FDb_Uninit();
6439        lib_json::FDb_Uninit();
6440    } catch(algo_lib::ErrorX &) {
6441        // don't print anything, might crash
6442        algo_lib::_db.exit_code = 1;
6443    }
6444    // only the lower 1 byte makes it to the outside world
6445    (void)i32_UpdateMin(algo_lib::_db.exit_code,255);
6446    return algo_lib::_db.exit_code;
6447}
